StationName 站名:
Munich Lohhof - Linde Hydrogen Center (LH2C)
慕尼黑 Lohhof - 林德氢气中心 (LH2C)
Goal 目标:
Test facilities, show room for Linde Technology, Refueling Station with puplic access.
测试设施、林德技术展示厅、可通行的加油站。
Description 描述:
vacuum insulated tank for 17 600 liters deep cold liquid hydrogen with dispenser, hydrogen conditioner; hydrogen compressor station (up to 450 bar) with dispenser for LH2 and CGH2;   CGH2 refueling capacity 250 Nm3/h, 5000 Nm3/d, 20 kg/h, 400 kg/d  LH2 refueling capacity max 3000l/h, 215 kg/h, 50 kg/h, 1000 kg/d   2012: 70 MPa upgrade refueling is in test phase  2013: 70 MPa refueling in regular operation.  The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class: 35 MPa no.   The station is accepted by major car companies. 2017: station is not longer open for public refuelling because Linde makes experiments with new technology components. 2018: plans to make a public dispenser 2021: plans were cancelled. Station only for tests of new technology
可容纳 17 600 升深冷液氢的真空绝热罐，配有加注机、氢气调节器；氢气压缩机站（最高 450 巴），配有 LH2 和 CGH2 加注机；CGH2 加注能力为 250 Nm3/h、5000 Nm3/d、20 kg/h、400 kg/d LH2 最大加注能力为 3000l/h、215 kg/h、50 kg/h、1000 kg/d 2012 年： 70 兆帕升级加油处于测试阶段 2013 年： 70 兆帕正常运行。 该加油站是戴姆勒为 FC B 级车型推荐的加油站： 没有 35 兆帕。  主要汽车公司均接受该加油站。2017 年：由于林德对新技术组件进行试验，该加气站不再对公众开放。2018 年：计划制造公共加气机 2021 年：计划取消。加气站仅用于测试新技术
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
vacuum-isolated tank for 17,600 litres (1200 kg H2)
可容纳 17600 升（1200 千克 H2）的真空隔热箱

Res2H2
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Street2 街道 2:
CRES demonstration wind park
CRES 示范风场
Goal 目标:
The aim of the installation is: 1. to investigate the operation of H2 production and storage technologies under the variable power produced by a wind turbine and 2. to demonstrate the potential of hydrogen to become an alternative product for wind park de
该装置的目的是：1.研究在风力涡轮机产生的可变功率下氢气生产和储存技术的运行情况；2.展示氢气成为风力发电厂替代产品的潜力。
Description 描述:
The installation consists of:500 kW Enercon E40 wind turbine, 25 kW alkaline electrolyser delivering H2 at 20 bar and 99.98% purity, 40Nm3 H2 storage in metal hydride tanks, single stage 15-220 bar compressor, filling station, central control and data logging unit,peripherals (air compressor, cooling unit, water heater, etc). The electrolyser is build with suitable power electronics and materials in the cell stack to allow for 20-120% of nominal power changes in 1 sec. interval. Hydrogen is compressed from 15 to 220 bar in a 1-stage membrane compressor and stored in a cylinder stack (100 Nm3 capacity).  Since end of 2010: the station is "under maintenance".
设备包括：500 千瓦 Enercon E40 风力涡轮机、25 千瓦碱性电解槽（提供 20 巴、纯度 99.98% 的 H2）、40Nm3 H2 金属氢化物储罐、单级 15-220 巴压缩机、充气站、中央控制和数据记录装置以及外围设备（空气压缩机、冷却装置、热水器等）。电解槽采用合适的电力电子设备和电池组材料，可在 1 秒钟间隔内实现 20-120% 的额定功率变化。氢气在一级膜压缩机中从 15 巴压缩到 220 巴，然后储存在一个气瓶堆中（容量为 100 立方米）。 自 2010 年底起：该站处于 "维护中"。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
electricity by wind power; Hydrogen is produced by a 25 kW electrolysis unit operating at a pressure of up to 20 bar that has been connected to a 500 kW Enercon E40 wind turbine. Hydrogen is purified to 99.98% purity. 
风力发电；氢气由一个 25 千瓦的电解装置生产，该装置与一个 500 千瓦的 Enercon E40 风力涡轮机相连，工作压力高达 20 巴。氢气纯度为 99.98%。
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
Hydrogen is stored in metal hydride tanks with a capacity of 40 Nm3. A cooling unit and a water heater are also installed for cooling/heating the tanks during discharging/ charging respectively. The storage / delivery pressure is 15 bar.
氢气储存在容量为 40 Nm3 的金属氢化物储罐中。此外，还安装了一个冷却装置和一个热水器，分别用于在卸载/充填过程中冷却/加热储氢罐。储存/输送压力为 15 巴。
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
Vehicle used for transporting visitors of the wind park
用于接送风力公园游客的车辆
Contact 联系方式:
Dr. Manos Zoulias mzoulias@cres.gr
Manos Zoulias 博士 mzoulias@cres.gr
Comments 评论:
This installation allows the testing of various strategies for utilising excess energy from a wind park in the form of hydrogen production. Such systems could well be used in the numerous non-grid connected Greek islands.
通过这一装置，可以测试以制氢形式利用风力发电厂多余能源的各种策略。这种系统完全可以用于希腊众多未并网的岛屿。

Description 描述:
Project has been aggred on Dec 12, 2006;  project duration 2007- 2010. funded by OMV Futur Eenergy Fund: „Wasserstofftankstelle in Stuttgart“ Project durationr: 2007 bis 2010 Project volum4 e: EUR 1,72 Mio OMV share minus other subsidies and other project partners: EUR 620.000 thereof OMV Future Energy Fund: EUR 206.667   The new hydrogen station at Stuttgart Airport incorporates ion-compressor technology developed by Linde. With this new compression process, cars and electric buses powered by fuel cells can be refuelled within a matter of minutes.   The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa no.   The station is accepted by major car companies.
由 OMV Futur Eenergy Fund 提供资金： "项目期限：2007 年至 2010 年 项目金额4e： 172万欧元 OMV份额减去其他补贴和其他项目合作伙伴： 620.000 欧元，其中包括 OMV 未来能源基金： 斯图加特机场的新氢气站采用了林德开发的离子压缩技术。采用这种新的压缩工艺，由燃料电池驱动的汽车和电动巴士可在几分钟内完成加氢。  该加气站是戴姆勒推荐的 FC B 级加气站，压力为 70 兆帕，35 兆帕。  该加气站已被各大汽车公司所接受。

Goal 目标:
The refuelling station is part of the hydrogen demonstration project H2argemuc. The goal is to gain insight into the routine use and economic feasibility of hydrogen as a fuel. Since the practical tests gave extensive knowledge for further development, it
该加气站是氢气示范项目 H2argemuc 的一部分。其目的是深入了解氢作为燃料的日常使用和经济可行性。由于实际测试为进一步开发提供了广泛的知识，因此
Description 描述:
The fourth phase of the H2argemuc project, which is sponsored by the Bavarian Ministry of Transport, has started in spring 2005 after the third phase was successfully completed. The main objectives of the project - the operational use of hydrogen and the presentation of an enclosed hydrogen circuit - have clearly been achieved. Today, in the Munich area both a rigid bus with hydrogen-powered internal-combustion engine and a fuel-cell bus are used on a commuter route.CGH2: high-pressure cylinders: 10 m3 @ 35 Mpa;  LH2: 12,000 l vessel  Steam reformer (hydrogen production capacity 100 Nm3/h);  hydrid based intermediate storage unit;  refuelling robot for liquid hydrogen    Vehicles served:   CGH2:  3 MAN low-floor articulated buses with an internal hydrogen combustion engine and a CGH2 hydrogen storage system, which are in daily use at the airport   PEMFC forklift with 24kW and8 h range;  expansion to local public transport using a MAN fuel-cell bus (68 kW from a PEM fuel-cell system and over 140 kW from an energy storage system) and MAN hydrogen-powered internal-combustion engine H 2866 UH and the optimised engine H 2876 UH (monovalent engine);  LH2: BMW 7series in field test (bivalent engine) 
H2argemuc 项目的第四阶段由巴伐利亚州交通部赞助，在第三阶段顺利完成后，于 2005 年春季开始实施。该项目的主要目标--氢气的实际使用和封闭式氢气回路的展示--已经明确实现。如今，在慕尼黑地区的一条通勤线路上，既使用了装有氢动力内燃机的硬质公共汽车，也使用了燃料电池公共汽车： CGH2：高压气瓶：10 m3 @ 35 Mpa；LH2：12,000 升容器 蒸汽重整器（制氢能力 100 Nm3/h）；基于氢化物的中间储存装置；液氢加注机器人 服务的车辆：   CGH2：3 辆 MAN 低地板铰接式公共汽车，配有氢内燃机和 CGH2 储氢系统，在机场日常使用 PEMFC 铲车，功率为 24 千瓦，续航时间为 8 小时；使用 MAN 燃料电池公共汽车（PEM 燃料电池系统的功率为 68 千瓦，储能系统的功率超过 140 千瓦）和 MAN 氢动力内燃机 H 2866 UH 及优化发动机 H 2876 UH（单价发动机），扩展到当地公共交通；LH2： 实地测试中的宝马 7 系（二价发动机）

Description 描述:
The hydrogen filling station is fully integrated into a conventional filling station.    Phase 1:  At the station both liquefied hydrogen (LH2) and compressed gaseous hydrogen (CGH2) can be refilled. Compressor and dispenser for gaseous hydrogen are designed for pressures up to 350 bars and 700 bar. Liquified hydrogen too can be vaporized, compressed and refilled as CGH2.       supply: LH2delivery, steam reforming; CGH2: vaporisation of LH2 and on-site steam reforming of liquefied petroleum gas (since May 13, 2007) max. 100 Nm³/h ( 7 buses a day), reforming Bio-Dimethylether DME with CO2 capture is planned   Phase 2:  Up-grade to 70 MPa in 2008:  infrared interface for data communication between car and station ultra-low cold-fill (-40°C)    Phase3:  CGH2 delivery; CGH2 by electrolysis with electricity from wind power  refilling 5kg H2 within 3 minutes  since Q4/2010 no LH2 any longer    18.04.2012. first refueling with "green" H2 from wind power Prenzlau  The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class: 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa no. The station is accepted by major car companies.
加氢站与传统加氢站完全集成。   第一阶段：加氢站既可加注液化氢（LH2），也可加注压缩气态氢（CGH2）。气态氢的压缩机和分配器可承受 350 巴和 700 巴的压力。液化氢也可以作为 CGH2 进行气化、压缩和加注： LH2输送、蒸汽转化；CGH2：LH2气化和液化石油气现场蒸汽转化（自2007年5月13日起），最大100 Nm³/h （7台）。第 2 阶段：2008 年将压力提升至 70 兆帕：用于车厢和站房之间数据通信的红外接口，超低温填充（-40°C）第 3 阶段：  自 2010 年第 4 季度起，3 分钟内加注 5 千克 H2，不再使用 LH2 2012 年 4 月 18 日：首次使用风力发电的 "绿色 "H2 加气 普伦茨劳 加气站由戴姆勒推荐用于 FC B 级： 70 兆帕 是，35 兆帕 否。该加气站已被各大汽车公司接受。

StationName 站名:
Bavarian Bus Demonstration Project
巴伐利亚巴士示范项目
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Goal 目标:
A MAN city bus was demonstrated in commercial service in the cities of Munich and Erlangen. Experience for an improvement of the bus system and the refuelling station infrastructure.
MAN 城市公交车在慕尼黑和埃尔兰根市进行了商业运营演示。为改进公交系统和加气站基础设施积累了经验。
Description 描述:
The refueling station was erected at the respective service yards of the transportation utilities.  The station was located in Erlangen from April, 1996 to Febuary, 1997 and in Munich from May, 1997 to August, 1998.  LH2 for buses with restricted access. The filling system consisted of two concentric tubes with vacuum super-insulation, of which the center tube delivered the LH2 and the outer tube extracted the evaporated GH2. The refueling process was a manual one in such a way that the filler coupling (nozzle) was connected to the bus receptacle by hand and then a semi-automatic refueling process was started at the LH2 transfer unit. Certain pre-programmed procedures were performed by a process control system after certain settings were given (levers adjusted, buttons pushed, etc.) by the person refueling the bus. After an introductory training provided to the bus drivers by Linde, every morning the bus drivers could refuel the bus with liquid hydrogen themselves and without any help of a Linde specialist.Transfer times of around 15-20 minutes.   12,000 l LH2  Transfer unit  Cylindrical storage tank (upright)
加油站建在运输公司各自的服务场内。 1996 年 4 月至 1997 年 2 月在埃尔兰根，1997 年 5 月至 1998 年 8 月在慕尼黑。 LH2 用于限制进入的公共汽车。加气系统由两根带有真空超绝缘层的同心管组成，中间的管子输送 LH2，外部的管子抽取蒸发的 GH2。加注过程是手动的，先用手将加注接头（喷嘴）连接到巴士容器上，然后在 LH2 传输装置上启动半自动加注过程。在加气人员进行一定的设置（调整杠杆、按下按钮等）后，由过程控制系统执行某些预先编程的程序。在林德为巴士司机提供入门培训后，巴士司机每天早上都可以自行为巴士加注液氢，无需林德专家的帮助。  12,000升LH2输送装置 圆柱形储罐（直立式）
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
Cylindrical, standing stationary LH2 storage. The cryogenic fuel storage and the refueling equipment were designed and manufactured by Linde AG.
圆柱形固定式 LH2 储藏室。低温燃料储存库和加油设备由林德股份公司设计和制造。
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
A MAN SL 202 city bus with an internal combust engine adapted to hydrogen (LH2) operation and auxiliary gasoline operation
MAN SL 202 城市公交车，配有可用于氢气（LH2）运行和辅助汽油运行的内燃机
Comments 评论:
The refueling station was skid-mounted and transportable. This "filling station" does not require external energy for refueling the bus with LH2 with exemption of the electricity to operated the vacuum pump for helium inertizing. 
加气站采用撬装式，可以运输。这种 "加气站 "不需要外部能源就能为客车加注 LH2，只需用电操作氦气惯性真空泵。

StationName 站名:
Clean Air Now
立即清洁空气
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Goal 目标:
This project demonstrates a practical application of solar generated hydrogen as fuel for utility vehicles at the Xerox facility in El Segundo, CA
该项目展示了太阳能产生的氢气在加利福尼亚州埃尔塞贡多施乐公司设施中作为公用车辆燃料的实际应用。
Description 描述:
Praxair Inc. provided a fueling system consisting of a partial fast-fill system. The Electrolyser Corp. integrated their systems with Praxair. The fueling system was upgraded to a full fast fill system that has the capability of fueling multiple vehicles in succession in under seven (7) minutes each. The resulting facility is serving as a fully operational hydrogen fueling station capable of fueling any additional hydrogen vehicles, operating on or off site. 13,000 scf @ 5,000 psi plus 80,000 scf @ 2,200 psi
普莱克斯公司提供了一个由部分快速加注系统组成的加注系统。Electrolyser 公司与普莱克斯公司整合了他们的系统。加氢系统升级为完全快速加氢系统，能够在 7 分钟内连续为多辆汽车加氢。由此产生的设施可作为一个全面运行的氢气加气站，能够为任何其他在现场或场外运行的氢气车辆提供燃料。13,000 scf @ 5,000 psi 加 80,000 scf @ 2,200 psi

Description 描述:
The station was part of the EU funded Zero regio project.   A 1.7 km transport line was built which connects the station to the hydrogen production plant of Hoechst.  The hydrogen is compressed to almost 900 bar with ionic liquid compression developed by Linde. The station has also solar panels installed on the roof of the multi fuel service station.     22.07.2010 The project is finished. Summary of Results is available. Station will stay in operation.  The station is upgraded to be ready for CEP (CleanEnergyPartnership) patners.  The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa no. The station is accepted by major car companies.   The H2 dispenser is part of a normal refueling station with a shop.
该站是欧盟资助的 "零区域 "项目的一部分。  已建成的 1.7 千米运输线将该站与 Hoechst 的氢气生产厂连接起来。 氢气通过林德公司开发的离子液体压缩技术被压缩至近 900 巴。多燃料服务站的屋顶上还安装了太阳能电池板。    22.07.2010 项目完成。可提供成果摘要。加油站将继续运营。 该加油站已升级，可为 CEP（清洁能源合作伙伴关系）的客户提供服务。 戴姆勒公司建议将该站用于 FC B 级 70 MPa 是，35 MPa 否。该加油站已被各大汽车公司所接受。  H2 加气机是带商店的普通加油站的一部分。

Description 描述:
The bp CUTE installation in Porto was part of a site that is used to park, maintain and refuel the buses operated by STCP working in Porto's metropolitan area. Hydrogen was generated with an on-site steam reformer based on natural gas. The compressor station was designed to produce the high pressure GH2 quantities needed for 3 buses, along with backup high pressure storage, in order not to compromise the filling times specifications, with back-to-back filling operations. Components: Steam reformer, Compressor High pressure storage (backup), Dispenser
bp CUTE 在波尔图的安装是一个站点的一部分，该站点用于停放、维护和为 STCP 在波尔图市区运营的公共汽车加油。氢气由现场的天然气蒸汽转化炉产生。压缩机站的设计是为了生产 3 辆公交车所需的高压 GH2，并配有备用高压储气罐，以避免因背靠背加气操作而影响加气时间规格。组件： 蒸汽转化炉、压缩机 高压储气罐（备用）、加气机

StationName 站名:
EMT CUTE Hydrogen Refueling Station
EMT CUTE 加氢站
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Street1 街道1:
Calle de Mauricio Legendre, 40
Calle de Mauricio Legendre, 40
Street2 街道 2: (Bus depot of EMT)
Goal 目标:
The station supplied fuel cell buses within the EC funded CUTE project and the CITYCELL project.
在欧共体资助的 CUTE 项目和 CITYCELL 项目中，该站为燃料电池巴士提供服务。
Description 描述:
Refueling for the 4 fuel cell busese ( 3 CUTE and 1 CITYCELL) was during the night. At the process of refueling CGH2 gets compressed from 20 MPa to 40 MPa. With a max. temperature of 50°C hydrogen is dispensed to the bus. Filling time is around 15 min. Between each refueling process there has to be an 1 hour stop for hydrogen generation.  4,000 Nm3 @ 20 MPa  Steam reformer  Compressor (max. 2,400 Nm3/h @ 40 MPa)  Tube trailers (Air Liquide)  Hydrogen is produced on-site through a compact methane steam reformer with a rated capacity slightly below the maximum demand. Complementary and back-up supply are provided by trucked hydrogen (CGH2 tube trailers) from a central production plant, mainly as by-product from an industrial process.   	 The city of Madrid operated the three fuel cell buses on different lines in the inner-city area like the other cities. Due to high temperatures in summer and also due to the highly congested traffic, Madrid challenged the technical performance of the fuel cell drive train working under these conditions. Air Liquide is responsible for the filling station including hydrogen storage, compression and vehicle filling dispenser; it will truck complementary hydrogen and back-up supply as well.

Description 描述:
The project aims to have the world ´s largest hydrogen- fuelled public transport operation in a single region before the end of the decade. The five-year project will evaluate public reaction as well as the reliability and economics of using hydrogen to fuel public transport in major urban areas. It will also help to establish technical standards for operating hydrogen fuel outlets.  June 2017: The storage capacity of the station was expanded to use the station within the 3Emotions project.+ extra nozzle Initially no pre-cooling, later pre-cooling to -8°C → improvement of refueling time • Depreciation of the upgrade over just 3,5 year caused high H2 price (€ 15,5/kg) → long contract = better price • Challenges: • Permit • Refeuling speed • Parallel refueling of vehicles not possible June 2020. 4 of 24 new buses for South Holland arrived
该项目的目标是，在本十年结束之前，在一个地区运营世界上最大的氢燃料公共交通。这个为期五年的项目将评估公众的反应，以及在主要城市地区使用氢气作为公共交通燃料的可靠性和经济性。它还将帮助建立氢燃料网点运营的技术标准。 2017 年 6 月： 在 3Emotions 项目中扩大了加氢站的存储容量。+ 额外的喷嘴 最初没有预冷，后来预冷至 -8°C → 加氢时间缩短 - 升级折旧仅 3.5 年，导致氢气价格高昂（15.5 欧元/千克） → 长期合同 = 更好的价格 - 挑战： - 2020 年 6 月。南荷兰 24 辆新公共汽车中的 4 辆已抵达

StationName 站名:
H2 HUB Sydthy
H2 HUB Sydthy
Street2 街道 2: Nordic Folkecenter
Goal 目标:
Hydrogen Link is a Nordic Transportpolitical Network (NTN) project, for the establishment of a Green Nordic Hydrogen Transportation Corridor between Norway, Sweden, Denmark and Germany.
Hydrogen Link 是北欧运输政治网络 (NTN) 的一个项目，旨在建立挪威、瑞典、丹麦和德国之间的绿色北欧氢运输走廊。
Description 描述:
Hydrogen is produced centrally in the city of Holstebro and is distributed by truck to each of the filling stations in the cities. The hydrogen production based on wind power and the production plant is operated by a local energy company. Seven various fuel cell hybrid vehicles will be put in operation in the cities at the various end-users, among these the world’s largest wind turbine manufacturer Vestas Wind Systems A/S. The hydrogen and fuel cell technology in the project is developed and supplied by H2 Logic A/S. The project is financed by all the participating companies and organisations, among these, the Danish Energy Agency, Vestas Wind Systems A/S and H2 Logic A/S.  
氢气在霍尔斯特布罗市集中生产，由卡车配送到各城市的加氢站。氢气生产依靠风力，生产厂由当地一家能源公司运营。七辆不同的燃料电池混合动力车将在各城市的最终用户处投入使用，其中包括世界上最大的风力涡轮机制造商维斯塔斯风力系统公司（Vestas Wind Systems A/S）。该项目的氢和燃料电池技术由 H2 Logic A/S 公司开发和提供。该项目由所有参与公司和组织提供资金，其中包括丹麦能源署、维斯塔斯风力系统公司和 H2 Logic 公司。

Description 描述:
Designed to operate unattended, it was capeable of delivering 40 kg of pure hydrogen fuel to each of the three fuel cell buses on a daily basis. The dispenser modul is activated through a PIN. The amount and pressure of hydrogen fuel which is delivered to the bus's tank is controlled by the dispenser. CGH2: 95kg Hydrogen generation (60 Nm3h or 120kg per day) Compression High-pressure storage Fuel dispenser Cute partners in Stockholm: Busslink AB (bus operator), Fortum AB (energy and gas distributor), Stockholm Environment and Health Protection (project co-ordinater), SL (local transportation company) and WP4 group, Hydrogenics
该装置设计为无人值守运行，每天可向三辆燃料电池巴士各输送 40 千克纯氢燃料。通过 PIN 激活分配器模块。输送到巴士油箱中的氢燃料的数量和压力由分配器控制。CGH2: 95kg 制氢量（每天 60 Nm3h 或 120kg） 压缩 高压储存 燃料分配器 斯德哥尔摩的主要合作伙伴： Busslink AB（巴士运营商）、Fortum AB（能源和天然气分销商）、斯德哥尔摩环境和健康保护局（项目协调人）、SL（当地运输公司）和 WP4 小组、Hydrogenics

Hydrogen Demonstration Park (HYDEPARK)
氢示范园（HYDEPARK）
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Street2 街道 2:
TUBITAK MRC Energy Institute
土耳其科学技术研究理事会 MRC 能源研究所
Goal 目标:
R&D and demonstration project concerning hydrogen production, storage and utilization
有关氢气生产、储存和利用的研发和示范项目
Description 描述:
"Hydrogen Energy Park" is one of the parts of the national State Planning Organization (SPO) project HY-PARK. It will demonstrate the integration of renewable energy and hydrogen production for several applications. The design & installations have already been started in the Research Center. Most of the components have been installed on site.  There are several units in this demo plant such as:  - Small scale wind turbines (each 5 kW)  - PV modules (~ 12 kW) modules  - Electrolyser (PEM type, 1.1 Nm3/h)  - Hydrogen compressor (Diaphram, 1.5 Nm3/h)  - Hydrogen storage (in MCPs and MH tanks)  - PEM fuel cells with control units (for residential and transport applications)  There is also a small scale NG fuel reformer installation for hydrogen production.  
氢能公园 "是国家规划组织（SPO）"氢能公园"（HY-PARK）项目的组成部分之一。它将展示可再生能源与氢气生产在多个应用领域的结合。研究中心已经开始设计和安装。大部分组件已在现场安装完毕。 该示范工厂有几个单元，例如  - 小型风力涡轮机（每台 5 千瓦） - 光伏组件（约 12 千瓦） - 电解器（PEM 型，1.1 Nm3/h） - 氢气压缩机（隔膜式，1.5 Nm3/h） - 氢气存储（MCP 和 MH 储罐） - 带控制单元的 PEM 燃料电池（用于住宅和运输应用）。

Goal 目标:
Fueling four FC buses
为四辆 FC 巴士加油
Description 描述:
Temporary station has been in operation since 2010.   The project is funded by the Global Environment Facility and by the Brazilian Innovation Agency (FINEP). It is carried out by the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP), in partnership with Metropolitan Urban Transport Company of São Paulo (EMTU/SP), Ministry of Mines and Energy of Brazil and Brazilian Cooperation Agency.    The project embraces one hydrogen production and fueling station and four fuel cell buses. Both the buses and the station are provided by private companies.    The station is capable of fueling all the four buses of the project. The first bus was tested from mid-2009 through mid-2011 and is currently under maintenance. The next three buses are planned for the second half of 2014.  The station is located inside an area that belongs to EMTU/SP. Its operator during the project is Petrobras Distribuidora (BRA), and the components (electrolyser, compressor, storage tanks, dispenser etc.) were provided by Hydrogenics (CAN).   Other private companies related to the project are: Ballard Power Systems (CAN), Electric Power Research Institute (USA), AES Eeltropaulo (BRA), Marcopolo (BRA), Nucellsys (GER) and Tuttotrasporti (BRA).  Technical details:   Production rate: 60 Nm³/h  Purity: 99,998%  Efficiency: 5.2 kWh/Nm³  Storage tanks: 72 kg stored at 430 bar  Electrolyzer type: alkalyne – 30% of KOH in water  The Project PNUD BRA/99/G32 ended in March 2016. The three new buses were successfully tested from July 2015 to March 2016. The hydrogen station did work well and was able to supply hydrogen for the buses during that period. 
临时站自 2010 年开始运行。该项目由全球环境基金和巴西创新署（FINEP）资助。该项目由联合国开发计划署（UNDP）与圣保罗大都会城市交通公司（EMTU/SP）、巴西矿产和能源部以及巴西合作署合作实施。该项目包括一个氢气生产和加氢站以及四辆燃料电池公共汽车。巴士和加氢站均由私营公司提供。加氢站能够为该项目的所有四辆巴士提供燃料。第一辆巴士已于 2009 年年中至 2011 年年中进行了测试，目前正在进行维护。接下来的三辆巴士计划于 2014 年下半年投入使用。加油站位于属于 EMTU/SP 的区域内。该项目的运营商是巴西国家石油公司（Petrobras Distribuidora，BRA），组件（电解器、压缩机、储罐、分配器等）由 Hydrogenics 公司（CAN）提供。与该项目有关的其他私营公司有 巴拉德电力系统公司（加拿大）、电力研究所（美国）、AES Eeltropaulo 公司（巴西）、Marcopolo 公司（巴西）、Nucellsys 公司（德国）和 Tuttotrasporti 公司（巴西）。技术细节：   生产率： 60 Nm³/h 60 Nm³/h 纯度：99,998% 效率：5.2 kWh/Nm³ 储罐：72 kg，430 bar 电解槽类型：烷基涟 - 水中 30% 的 KOH PNUD BRA/99/G32 项目于 2016 年 3 月结束。2015 年 7 月至 2016 年 3 月，三辆新巴士成功进行了测试。在此期间，氢气站确实运行良好，能够为巴士供应氢气。

Description 描述:
The Goverment of Western Australia, Department for Planning and Infrastructure, has contracted BOC to operate and maintain the fueling station. The buses will be housed, refuelled and maintained by PATH Transit. The hydrogen for the fuel cell bus trial will be produced by BP as a by-product from their oil refinery in Kwinana and piped to the BOC site next door where it will be purified and pressurised. The compressed hydrogen will then be trucked to the bus depot and off-loaded to the refuelling facility, from which the hydrogen fuel cell buses will be refuelled. Components: Storage vessel, Dispenser

The University of Texas at Austin, Center for Electromechanics (UT-CEM) and GTI plan to install the first permanent hydrogen fueling station packaged by GreenField Compression Inc. of Richardson, Texas and deploy the first zero-emission fuel cell hybrid bus in the State of Texas this summer. StationName 站名:
Northern H - Multi-Fuel Hydrogen Highway
北部 H--多燃料氢气公路
北部 H - 多燃料氢气公路
Goal 目标:
The Upper Midwest Hydrogen Initiative wants to accelerate North America’s shift toward clean, domestic hydrogen production and use through:Pilot demonstrations, Research, Public education, Policy reform
上中西部氢能倡议 "希望通过试点示范、研究、公共教育和政策改革，加快北美向国内清洁氢气生产和使用的转变。
Description 描述:
Northern H Corridors Initiative. A ten-year, coordinated effort to establish a hydrogen-fueling infrastructure along major Upper Midwest interstate transportation corridors, linking Iowa, Minnesota, North and South Dakota, Wisconsin and the Canadian Manitoba. Proposed station locations are: Ames, Des Moines, Alexandria or St. Cloud, Duluth, Minneapolis, Fargo, Grand Forks, Brookings, Sioux Falls, Madison and Winnipeg.  Northern H Energy Stations would offer a unique, multi-fuel network that can support off-road fleet vehicles (like those at airports and distibution centers), take advantage of higher efficiency transportation technologies available today, such as flexible-fuel and hybrid-electric vehicles and support hydrogen fuel cell vehicles when they are ready. The stations may also produce electricity, via fuel cell for on-site use and for sale to the grid via CHP if possible.
北部 H 走廊倡议。这是一项为期十年的协调努力，旨在沿上中西部主要州际交通走廊建立氢燃料基础设施，连接爱荷华州、明尼苏达州、南北达科他州、威斯康星州和加拿大马尼托巴省。建议的加油站地点包括 埃姆斯、得梅因、亚历山大或圣克劳德、德卢斯、明尼阿波利斯、法戈、大福克斯、布鲁金斯、苏福尔斯、麦迪逊和温尼伯。 Northern H Energy 加气站将提供一个独特的多燃料网络，可支持非公路车队车辆（如机场和配送中心的车辆），利用当今更高效的运输技术，如灵活燃料和混合动力电动汽车，并在氢燃料电池汽车准备就绪时为其提供支持。加气站还可以通过燃料电池发电，供现场使用，并在可能的情况下通过热电联产向电网出售。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
each station would likely demonstrate a different renewable or carbon-neutral hydrogen production option
每个氢气站都可能展示不同的可再生或碳中性制氢方案

各种车辆

StationName 站名:
Northern H - Multi-Fuel Hydrogen Highway
北部 H--多燃料氢气公路
北部 H - 多燃料氢气公路
Goal 目标:
The Upper Midwest Hydrogen Initiative wants to accelerate North America’s shift toward clean, domestic hydrogen production and use through:Pilot demonstrations, Research, Public education, Policy reform
上中西部氢能倡议 "希望通过试点示范、研究、公共教育和政策改革，加快北美向国内清洁氢气生产和使用的转变。
Description 描述:
Northern H Corridors Initiative. A ten-year, coordinated effort to establish a hydrogen-fueling infrastructure along major Upper Midwest interstate transportation corridors, linking Iowa, Minnesota, North and South Dakota, Wisconsin and the Canadian Manitoba. Proposed station locations are: Ames, Des Moines, Alexandria or St. Cloud, Duluth, Minneapolis, Fargo, Grand Forks, Brookings, Sioux Falls, Madison and Winnipeg.  Northern H Energy Stations would offer a unique, multi-fuel network that can support off-road fleet vehicles (like those at airports and distibution centers), take advantage of higher efficiency transportation technologies available today, such as flexible-fuel and hybrid-electric vehicles and support hydrogen fuel cell vehicles when they are ready. The stations may also produce electricity, via fuel cell for on-site use and for sale to the grid via CHP if possible.
北部 H 走廊倡议。这是一项为期十年的协调努力，旨在沿上中西部主要州际交通走廊建立氢燃料基础设施，连接爱荷华州、明尼苏达州、南北达科他州、威斯康星州和加拿大马尼托巴省。建议的加油站地点包括 埃姆斯、得梅因、亚历山大或圣克劳德、德卢斯、明尼阿波利斯、法戈、大福克斯、布鲁金斯、苏福尔斯、麦迪逊和温尼伯。 Northern H Energy 加气站将提供一个独特的多燃料网络，可支持非公路车队车辆（如机场和配送中心的车辆），利用当今更高效的运输技术，如灵活燃料和混合动力电动汽车，并在氢燃料电池汽车准备就绪时为其提供支持。加气站还可以通过燃料电池发电，供现场使用，并在可能的情况下通过热电联产向电网出售。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
each station would likely demonstrate a different renewable or carbon-neutral hydrogen production option
每个氢气站都可能展示不同的可再生或碳中性制氢方案
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
different vehicle types
各种车辆
Contact 联系方式:
Rolf Nordstrom, Upper Midwest Hydrogen Initiative, Great Plains Institute, 2801 21st Ave. S., Suite 230, Minneapolis, MN 55407 Rnordstrom@gpisd.net
Rolf Nordstrom，上中西部氢能倡议，大平原研究所，2801 21st Ave. S., Suite 230, Minneapolis, MN 55407 Rnordstrom@gpisd.net

Manitoba Hydrogen Initiative
马尼托巴氢能倡议
Status 状态:
Out of Operation

Goal 目标:
Manitoba has developed a hydrogen vision to position the province for the future, and has begun the process to develop a Hydrogen Economic Development Strategy. 
马尼托巴省制定了氢能愿景，为该省的未来发展定位，并已开始制定氢能经济发展战略。
Description 描述:
The Province of Manitoba has an active program to develop hydrogen opportunities and it strongly supports the Upper Midwest Hydrogen Initiative and the Northern H - the first multi-fuel Hydrogen Highway network in North America. Northern H Corridors Initiative is a  ten-year, coordinated effort to establish a hydrogen-fueling infrastructure along major Upper Midwest interstate transportation corridors, linking Iowa, Minnesota, North and South Dakota, Wisconsin and the Canadian Manitoba.
马尼托巴省制定了一项积极的计划来开发氢能机会，并大力支持 "上中西部氢能倡议"（Upper Midwest Hydrogen Initiative）和 "北部氢走廊"（Northern H）--北美首个多燃料氢能高速公路网。北部氢走廊倡议是一项为期十年的协调努力，旨在沿上中西部主要州际交通走廊建立氢燃料基础设施，将爱荷华州、明尼苏达州、南北达科他州、威斯康星州和加拿大马尼托巴省连接起来。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
for the bus testing in 2005 there was a winterized electrolysis-based station
在 2005 年的巴士测试中，有一个冬季电解站
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
in 2005 a H2 ICE bus was tested, in 2006 a H2 FC bus was tested
2005 年测试了一辆 H2 ICE 公共汽车，2006 年测试了一辆 H2 FC 公共汽车
Contact 联系方式:

Robert Parsons, MBA, P.Eng., Manitoba Energy, Science and Technology Energy Development Initiative, 12th Floor - 155 Carlton Street,Winnipeg, Manitoba R3C 3H, robert.parsons@gov.mb.ca
Comments 评论:
The station is also part of the Northern H, a project of the Upper Midwest Hydrogen Initiative (= an idustry-led, US-Canadian, public-private venture of the non-profit Great Plains Institute www.umhi.org). 
Since 2003 Manitabo has been working in partnership with Iceland´s hydogen initiative and tested a hydrogen ICE bus in 2005. A electrolysis-based hydrogen filling station was tested.

该站也是 "上中西部氢能倡议"（=非营利性大平原研究所 www.umhi.org）项目 "北方氢能"（Northern H）的一部分。"上中西部氢能倡议 "是一个由行业领导的美加公私合营企业。
自 2003 年以来，马尼塔博一直与冰岛氢能计划合作，并于 2005 年测试了一辆氢内燃机公交车。测试了一个基于电解的加氢站。

StationName 站名:
Rockford Airport Hydrogen Fueling Station
罗克福德机场氢气加气站
Street1 街道1:
Rockford's Greater Northwest Chicagoland Regional 
罗克福德的大芝加哥西北地区
Goal 目标:
The goal of this project is to demonstrate the viability of using renewably produced hydrogen in an airport environment.
该项目的目标是证明在机场环境中使用可再生氢气的可行性。
Description 描述:
The hydrogen generated by the solar and wind array will provide stationary heat and power for an airport building and transportation fuel for zero emission airport vehicles. The Illinois Coalition received a grant from the Illinois Clean Energy Community Foundation to develop Illinois' first hydrogen fueling station powered by renewable sources. The grant was matched by in-kind contributions from participant organizations including Illinois Institute of Technology, Aerotecture Inc, Rock Valley College, and global law firm Latham and Watkins. The project, powered primarily by solar and wind energy, will be housed at Rockford's Greater Northwest Chicagoland Regional Airport and represents the Foundation's first investment in fuel cell technology.
太阳能和风能阵列产生的氢气将为机场大楼提供固定热能和电力，并为机场零排放车辆提供运输燃料。伊利诺伊州联盟获得了伊利诺伊州清洁能源社区基金会（Illinois Clean Energy Community Foundation）的一笔赠款，用于开发伊利诺伊州首个以可再生能源为动力的加氢站。伊利诺伊理工学院、Aerotecture Inc、Rock Valley College 和全球律师事务所 Latham and Watkins 等参与机构也提供了相应的实物捐助。该项目主要由太阳能和风能提供动力，将设在罗克福德的大芝加哥西北地区机场，这也是基金会对燃料电池技术的首次投资。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
with solar power and wind power
利用太阳能和风能

StationName 站名:
Chicago Transit Authority Ballard PEMFC Bus Demo
芝加哥交通局 Ballard PEMFC 公交车演示
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Description 描述:
Located at the Palaski Bus Garage in Chicago the fueling station consisted of two major systems: - Hydrogen receiving and long-term storage system: to receive and store LH2, vaporize LH2 to CGH2 and compress and store compressed H2 for fueling operations - Hydrogen transfer system: for fueling the buses for revenue operation LH2: 34,000 l @ 1 Mpa CGH2: 420 Nm3 @ 31 MPa Liquide Hydrogen Tank HP Storage Dispenser Liquid hydrogen from natural gas was supplied by Air Products
该加油站位于芝加哥的帕拉斯基巴士车库，由两大系统组成： - 氢气接收和长期储存系统：接收和储存 LH2，将 LH2 气化为 CGH2，并压缩和储存压缩 H2，用于加气操作 - 氢气输送系统：为营运巴士加气 LH2：34,000 升 @ 1 兆帕 CGH2：420 牛立方米 @ 31 兆帕 液化氢储罐 HP 储存分配器 天然气液态氢由空气产品公司提供。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
H2 from natural gas
来自天然气的 H2
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
CGH2, LH2
CGH2、LH2
VehiclesServed 服务车辆: 3 Ballard PEMFC Buses
Comments 评论:
The refueling station was part of the Xcellsis/ Ballard Phase 3 Program, which took place in two communities, in Chicago, Illinois and British Columbia.The project was successfully concluded on March 23, 2000. The three buses accumulated more than 5,000 hours in revenue service, covered over 30,000 miles, carried more than 100,000 passengers.
DoE and FTA will fund a new FC bus project. Start is planned for the third quarter of 2012. Delay to 2013
该加气站是 Xcellsis/ Ballard 第三阶段计划的一部分，该计划在伊利诺伊州芝加哥市和不列颠哥伦比亚省的两个社区实施。这三辆公共汽车累计运营时间超过 5,000 小时，行驶里程超过 30,000 英里，载客量超过 100,000 人次。
教育部和联邦交通局将资助一个新的 FC 巴士项目。计划于 2012 年第三季度启动。推迟到 2013 年

Recognizing the challenge presented by the intermittency and varying outputs of wind power, an important element of the project is the development of various control schemes by which the electrolyser can interface with the electrical output of wind turbines to optimise fuel production. The station is one of the first United States-based hydrogen filling stations to use electricity from a wind power resource to produce hydrogen from water , in this case using electricity generated by wind resources either owned or contracted by Basin Electric.

Description 描述:
The DTE Energy Hydrogen Technology Park is a hydrogen energy demonstration project designed to provide critical insight into the role of hydrogen in our nation's energy system. From the generation of hydrogen to storage, distribution and conversion to energy, this working prototype will: * produce hydrogen gas from tap water using a mix of solar power, biomass power and power from the electric grid * compress and store the hydrogen on site * deliver enough electricity to power a small office complex, or approximately 20 homes, and produce enough compressed hydrogen gas to power about three fuel cell vehicles per day Q4/ 2008 upgrade to 70 MPa

Out of Operation
停止运行
Goal 目标:
Evaluate the safety and reliability of operating internal combustion engine (ICE) vehicles on hydrogen and blended HCNG fuels; Develop a working model of a refueling system for ICE and fuel cell vehicles
评估内燃机 (ICE) 汽车使用氢气和混合 HCNG 燃料的安全性和可靠性；开发内燃机汽车和燃料电池汽车加气系统的工作模型
Description 描述:
The plant's hydrogen system consits of production, compression, storage and dispensing. It distinctly separates the hydrogen ystem from the natural gas system, but can blend the two fuels at the stationary filling system. Components: Hydrogen Generator – PEM fuel cell, 57 kW, 300 scfh hydrogen output (Hogan 300) Hydrogen Compressor – Oil free, three stage, diaphragm compressor, 99.9997% purity Hydrogen Dispenser – Dispenses hydrogen up to 5,000 psi HCNG and CNG Dispenser – Dispenses HCNG and CNG up to 3,600 psi CNG Boot Compressor – 300 scfm @ 60 psi CNG Main Compressor – 350 scfm @ 4500 psi CNG Storage – 50,000 scf up to 5,000 psi Fuel Dispenser – Pure hydrogen or CNG and HCNG blended fuels, with metering and electronic billing interface
工厂的氢气系统包括生产、压缩、储存和分配。它将氢气系统与天然气系统截然分开，但可以在固定充气系统中混合两种燃料。组件： 氢气发生器 - PEM 燃料电池，57 千瓦，300 scfh 氢气输出（Hogan 300） 氢气压缩机 - 无油三级隔膜压缩机，99. 氢气分配器 - 可分配高达 5,000 psi 的氢气 HCNG 和 CNG 分配器 - 可分配高达 3,600 psi 的 HCNG 和 CNG CNG 靴式压缩机 - 300 scfm @ 60 psi CNG 主压缩机 - 350 scfm @ 4500 psi CNG 存储器 - 50,000 scf 高达 5,000 psi 燃料分配器 - 纯氢或 CNG 和 HCNG 混合燃料，带计量和电子计费界面

StationName 站名:
California Fuel Cell Partnership (CaFCP)
加州燃料电池合作组织 (CaFCP)
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Street1 街道1:

Street2 街道 2:
Suite 1000

西萨克拉门托
Description 描述:
The station is used to fill vehicles with gaseous hydrogen. The hydrogen is stored cryogenically at a temperature of -423° degrees F (-253° C). Fueling the fuel cell vehicle is a very quick and automated process, allowing a safe fill of the vehicle tank in just 4 minutes or less-- comparable to existing car fill up times. Very simply, the fuel cell vehicle driver will connect the communication cable to the vehicle to confirm that the safety and vehicle systems are established and functioning properly. The information transferred to the computer includes details of the vehicle fuel tank, the vehicle manufacturer and specific conditions set by the manufacturer that must be met to begin fueling. Following that, the driver connects the fill nozzle and fills the vehicle.    Dispenser: Dispensing pressure @ 25 MPa and 35 Mpa  - One 4,500 gallon liquid hydrogen storage tank  - A 'vaporizer' that warms the liquid hydrogen to gaseous hydrogen  - A compressor to raise the gas pressure to 6,250 psig  - 3 gaseous hydrogen storage tubes  - Two gaseous dispensers, one at 3,600 psig the other at 5,000 psig, and one liquid hydrogen dispenser  - One dispenser system delivers liquid hydrogen    Upgrades in 2009 and 2010 to 70 MPa and state-of-the-art technology. Equipment will be probably moved to a retail station.
该加氢站用于为汽车加注气态氢。氢气以低温储存，温度为华氏零下 423 度（摄氏零下 253 度）。为燃料电池汽车加油是一个非常快速和自动化的过程，只需 4 分钟或更短的时间就能安全地为汽车油箱加满氢气，与现有的汽车加油时间相当。非常简单，燃料电池汽车驾驶员将通信电缆连接到汽车上，确认安全和汽车系统已经建立并正常运行。传输到计算机的信息包括车辆燃料箱的详细信息、车辆制造商以及制造商设定的开始加注必须满足的特定条件。随后，驾驶员连接加油枪，为车辆加油。   加油机： 分配压力为 25 兆帕和 35 兆帕 - 一个 4,500 加仑的液态氢储罐 - 一个将液态氢加热为气态氢的 "蒸发器" - 一个将气体压力提高到 6,250 psig 的压缩机 - 3 个气态氢储存管 - 两个气态分配器，一个为 3,600 psig，另一个为 5,000 psig，还有一个液态氢分配器 - 一个分配器系统提供液态氢 2009 年和 2010 年升级为 70 兆帕，并采用了最先进的技术。设备可能会转移到零售站。

Goal 目标:
Develop retail compatible hydrogen refueling systems. Evaluate emerging hydrogen technologies that have the ability to meet DOE cost and performance targets

Description 描述:
The Controlled Hydrogen Fleet and Infrastructure Demonstration and Validation Project will be the first effort of its kind to bring together, at a national level, nearly every major automobile and energy company in a hydrogen fuel and vehicle demonstration project. The project will be a learning demonstration that will help DOE focus its research and development efforts, provide insight into vehicle and infrastructure interface issues, and help address codes, standards and safety issues. The project will develop complete system solutions to address hydrogen infrastructure and vehicle development in parallel to validate that a commercialization decision by 2015 is on schedule. 
受控氢车队和基础设施示范与验证项目将是首次在全国范围内将几乎所有主要汽车和能源公司聚集到氢燃料和车辆示范项目中的同类项目。该项目将是一个学习示范项目，有助于能源部集中精力开展研发工作，深入了解车辆和基础设施的接口问题，并帮助解决法规、标准和安全问题。该项目将开发完整的系统解决方案，以同时解决氢基础设施和车辆开发问题，从而验证在 2015 年之前如期做出商业化决定。

Description 描述:
The station, installed by Air Products and Chemicals, Inc., is located at the Unitrans Maintenance Yard on Garrod Drive in Davis. It provids both hydrogen enriched natural gas (Hythan) and pure hydrogen. Both fuels are delivered to vehicles in gaseous form. To fuel the hydrogen enriched natural gas buses, CGH2 is mixed with CNG in a blend unit and then dispensed into the buses at 3,200 to 3,600 psi. The blend fuel contains 30% hydrogen by volumen.

Goal 目标:
Alternative energy as a key to reducing dependence on foreign oil.
替代能源是减少对外国石油依赖的关键。
Description 描述:
Linde is using technology known as ionic compression, which uses less electricity than other hydrogen fueling stations and requires less maintenance.   It is a fast-fill dispensing system. The IC-50 ionic bus fueling system can fill a bus with 30 kg of hydrogen in six minutes. The MF-90 car fueling system can fill an automobile in three minutes for 300-400 miles of operation. A -40° C chiller is used to enable fast filling to 700 bar.    Linde's refueling station  will use liquid hydrogen produced off-site and gaseous hydrogen produced from water by a state-of-the-art electrolyzer, which will be powered by renewable energy credits generated by AC Transit's new 575- Kilowatt solar installation at its central maintenance facility. The electrolyzer is made by Proton Energy Systems.  The Linde system supports both 350 bar and 700 bar fuel systems.    There are two stations: a bus station and a passenger car station. Two 35 MPa dispenser. And since 2012 a 35 MPa and 70 MPa dispenser street side publicly accessible.  Hydrogen supply: electrolysis on-site with 575 kW renewable energy (solar power plant) capacity 60 kg/ day; combined with weekly delivered LH2 capacity up to 600kg/day; upgraded station 350 kg/day, 33 % renewable H2   Hydrogen storage: 2400 kg LH2, 360kg CGH2 at 40 MPa, 28 kg CGH2 at 90 MPa   May 2012: the station was ouf of operation after an incident with a valve. Started again in May 2013.   2017: station should be upgraded to retail station   20.11.2018 retail station opens; 100% renewable hydrogen by electrolysis on-site 2020: bus refueling: operator Linde, not public ; retail station: operator Messer, H2 source = electrolysis on-site 33% renewable 2021: Bus station operator Messer H2 source NG steam reforming
林德使用的是离子压缩技术，这种技术比其他加氢站耗电更少，维护要求也更低。这是一种快速加注系统。IC-50 离子巴士加氢系统可在 6 分钟内为一辆巴士加注 30 千克氢气。MF-90 汽车加氢系统可在三分钟内为一辆汽车加满氢气，行驶 300-400 英里。零下 40 摄氏度的冷却器可使加氢速度达到 700 巴。林德的加气站将使用场外生产的液态氢和由最先进的电解槽从水中产生的气态氢，电解槽将由 AC Transit 在其中央维护设施新建的 575 千瓦太阳能装置产生的可再生能源积分供电。电解槽由质子能源系统公司制造。林德系统支持 350 巴和 700 巴燃料系统。有两个站：一个公共汽车站和一个轿车站。两个 35 兆帕加气机。自 2012 年起，还可在街道旁向公众提供 35 兆帕和 70 兆帕加气机。氢气供应：利用 575 千瓦可再生能源（太阳能发电厂）在现场进行电解，日产量为 60 千克；结合每周输送的 LH2，日产量可达 600 千克；升级后的加氢站日产量为 350 千克，33% 为可再生 H2 氢气储存：2400 千克 LH2、360 千克 CGH2（40 兆帕）、28 千克 CGH2（90 兆帕） 2012 年 5 月：因阀门事故，加氢站停止运行。2013 年 5 月重新启动。2017 年：该站应升级为零售站 20。11. 
林德采用的技术2018 年零售站开放；现场电解 100% 可再生氢气 2020 年：巴士加气：运营商林德，不对外开放；零售站：运营商梅塞尔，氢气来源 = 现场电解 33% 可再生 2021 年：巴士加气：运营商林德，不对外开放；零售站：运营商梅塞尔，氢气来源 = 现场电解 33% 可再生： 公交车站运营商梅塞尔，氢气来源 NG 蒸汽重整。

氢气将为 AC Transit 的 40 英尺 Van Hool/UTC/ISE 燃料电池巴士车队和未来的轻型车辆（轿车、SUV 和小型卡车）车队提供燃料，以支持州长阿诺德-施瓦辛格在加利福尼亚州建立氢气高速公路网络的愿景。
Description 描述:
Former station (started March 2006):  Hydrogen filling station providing CGH2 for three fuel cell buses.  Hydrogen was derived via a small-scale, on-site natural gas steam reformer. The station dispensed up to 150 kg hydrogen per day. The station was also able to fuel H2-powered light duty vehicles.   Two dispensers (35 MPa, expected refuelling time less than 15 minutes) + mobile fueler with a maximum capacity of two bus fillings/day.     ACT took over the station in fall 2010 (before Chevron);  From the first half of 2011 on, new filling technology was installed by Linde like in Emergyville, but without car filling, only buses. The new station is able to fuel up to 12 buses consecutively (each with 30 kg within 5 minutes) and is fully integrated in a existing diesel fueling station. A third of the fuel supply will be derived from the electrolysis of water using a PEM electrolyzer powered by renewable electricity generated from biogas-fed, stationary 400kW solid oxide fuel cells.    Photovoltaic system was installed to produce electricity for the electrolyser.   The new station went in operation in January 2016. July 2019: H2 source unclear: only on-site natural gas steam reforming? April 22:CEC:  Proposed resolution approving Agreement ZVI-21-018 with Alameda-Contra Costa Transit District for a $4,565,975 grant to upgrade the existing hydrogen refueling station  OCTA installed precooling in their dispenser. Station upgrade was confirmed to be capable of fueling up to 130 buses, back to back in 10 hour window
前站（2006 年 3 月启动）：  加氢站为三辆燃料电池巴士提供 CGH2。氢气通过一个小型现场天然气蒸汽转化器提取。加氢站每天最多可提供 150 公斤氢气。该加氢站还能为以氢气为动力的轻型车辆提供燃料。两台加气机（35 兆帕，预计加气时间不超过 15 分钟）+ 移动加气机，每天最多可为两辆公共汽车加气。ACT 于 2010 年秋季接管该加气站（在雪佛龙之前）；从 2011 年上半年开始，林德公司安装了新的加气技术，就像在埃默吉维尔一样，但不为汽车加气，只为巴士加气。新加油站可连续为 12 辆巴士加油（每辆巴士可在 5 分钟内加油 30 公斤），并与现有的柴油加油站完全整合。三分之一的燃料供应将来自使用 PEM 电解槽电解水，该电解槽由沼气驱动的固定式 400 千瓦固体氧化物燃料电池产生的可再生能源供电。安装的光伏系统为电解槽发电。新电站于 2016 年 1 月投入运行。2019 年 7 月：H2 来源不明确：只有现场天然气蒸汽重整？4 月 22 日：CEC：建议通过决议，批准与阿拉米达-康特拉科斯塔运输区签订的 ZVI-21-018 号协议，以获得 456.5975 万美元的补助金，用于升级现有加氢站 OCTA 在其加气机中安装了预冷装置。经确认，升级后的加油站可在 10 小时内为多达 130 辆巴士背靠背加油。

Description 描述:
Santa Clara Valley Transportation Authority (VTA) adopted a Clean Fuels Strategy in December 2000. The Zero-Emission Bus Demonstration Program is a joint effort between VTA and the San Mateo County Transit District (SamTrans). The program consists of using Zero Emission Bus technology in transit revenue service, facility modifications, the installation of a hydrogen fueling station at VTA's Cerone division, and training for VTA and SamTrans personnel on the new technology. VTA, SamTrans, the Federal Transit Administration (FTA) and the U.S. Department of Energy will evaluate bus performance and fuel cell technology.
圣克拉拉河谷交通管理局（VTA）于 2000 年 12 月通过了一项清洁燃料战略。零排放巴士示范计划是圣塔克拉拉谷交通局和圣马刁县交通局（SamTrans）的一项联合行动。该计划包括在公交营运服务中使用零排放巴士技术、设施改造、在 VTA Cerone 分部安装氢燃料加注站，以及对 VTA 和 SamTrans 人员进行新技术培训。VTA、SamTrans、联邦运输管理局 (FTA) 和美国能源部将对公共汽车的性能和燃料电池技术进行评估。

Goal 目标:
To build confidence in hydrogen systems and facilitate the transition of hydrogen technologies into the market place.
建立对氢气系统的信心，促进氢气技术向市场过渡。
Description 描述:
On-site hydrogen production began in Novenber 2000 using two electrolyzers and a Hydrogen Burner Technology (HBT) natural gas reformer.The Teledyne Brown electrolyzer has not only the task of producing 40 scf/ hour. It is also testing the viability of using solar power. Generation from wind power is planned. The second electrolyzer is a self-contained Phase 3 (P3) Stuart Energy (now Hydrogenics) unit that produces and compresses 1, 400 scf per hour. In addition to the two electrolyzers, steam reforming. The HBT can produce 4,200 scf/ hour, 180 kg/day.   Since August 2006 on-site hydrogen production by using a HyRadix Adéo reformer (after a successful two-year test of a prototype system)    2012: production by HyRadix natural gas reformer typically with 4.5kg/h, 9kg/h possible; unclear whether electrolyser is further in operation    SunLine produces H2 by steam reforming of biogas (bioCNG from landfill). 180 kg/day. 5 FC buses. Average cost (under best condition) are estimated to be around $8/kg 10.4.19 upgrade with NEL Hydrogen electrolysis technology is planned to start 1.9.2019 January 2020: electrolyser by NEL, capacity of the station is upgraded to 900 kg/day with two 35 MPa bus dispensers, 17 FC buses June 2020: further 8 buses are planned and a solar project with 4 MW; 35 MPa for public; plans to upgrade public to 70 MPa for light and heavy duty vehicles May 2021: plans to expand the existing heavy-duty hydrogen fueling infrastructure to include a new stand-alone liquid hydrogen station to support current and future transit fueling needs Oct 2021: 5 additional H2 New Flyer buses; now 21 buses Jan 2022 additional mobile station in Indio: installation of a new Liquid Hydrogen Pump in Indio that will allow the Agency to fuel its fuel cell bus fleet with hydrogen through this new mobile solution
2000 年 11 月，开始使用两台电解槽和一台氢燃烧器技术（HBT）天然气转化炉进行现场制氢。Teledyne Brown 电解槽的任务不仅是每小时生产 40 立方英尺的氢气。它还在测试使用太阳能发电的可行性。计划利用风能发电。第二个电解槽是一个独立的第三阶段（P3）Stuart Energy（现为 Hydrogenics）装置，每小时生产和压缩 1,400 scf。除两个电解槽外，还有蒸汽重整装置。HBT 每小时可生产 4,200 scf，每天可生产 180 公斤。自 2006 年 8 月起，使用 HyRadix Adéo 重整器现场生产氢气（在对原型系统进行了为期两年的成功测试之后） 2012 年：使用 HyRadix 天然气重整器生产氢气，通常为 4.5 千克/小时，也可能为 9 千克/小时；尚不清楚电解器是否在进一步运行 SunLine 通过对沼气（来自垃圾填埋场的生物压缩天然气）进行蒸汽重整生产氢气。每天 180 千克。5 辆 FC 巴士。平均成本（最佳条件下）估计约为 8 美元/千克 10. 4. 19 台采用 NEL 电解氢技术的升级设备计划于 1. 9. 2019 年 2020 年 1 月：由 NEL 提供电解槽，加氢站容量升级至 900 公斤/天，配备两台 35 兆帕巴士加注机，17 辆 FC 巴士 2020 年 6 月：计划增加 8 辆巴士和一个 4 兆瓦的太阳能项目；35 兆帕供公众使用； 计划将轻型和重型车辆的公众使用升级至 70 兆帕 2021 年 5 月： 2021 年 10 月：新增 5 辆 H2 New Flyer 公交车；现有 21 辆公交车 2022 年 1 月：在 Indio 增设移动站：在 Indio 安装新的液氢泵，使该机构能够通过这一新的移动解决方案为其燃料电池公交车队提供氢燃料。

Description 描述:
The goal of this project is to provide wind-generated hydrogen to fuel vehicles from the California Fuel Cell Partnership and SunLine Transit Agency. This will be the first hydrogen fuel facility powered by wind energy. Only hydrogen produced from renewable energy sources, such as wind or solar, provides the opportunity for zero emissions from "well to wheels".
该项目的目标是为加州燃料电池合作公司和 SunLine Transit Agency 的车辆提供风力产生的氢气燃料。这将是首个以风能为动力的氢燃料设施。只有风能或太阳能等可再生能源产生的氢才能实现从 "井到车轮 "的零排放。

with wind power: 3 Nordtank 65kW wind turbines, 3 kg/hr. Can produce up to 9000 kg H2/yr.

StationName 站名:
Torrance  - W. 190th St. (Upgrade)
托伦斯 - W. 190th St.
Street1 街道1:
W. 190th Street 
W. 第 190 街
Description 描述:
The old fueling station was capable of providing hydrogen based upon demand. As the demand increases, the pipeline is capable of supplying the fuel to meet those needs. Hydrogen costs $4.5 to $5.5 per kg    There are two pumps and  four dispensers. Simultaneously filling of four vehicles is possibel. Despensing according to SAE TIR-J2601.    When starting with full storage, six cars can be filled in succession.   H2 pipeline 6MPa  hydrogen purification technology for production of ultra-pure hydrogen   PDC Machines diaphragma compressor  50 kg/day to 45 MPa  Hydropac hydraulic booster compressor  to 100 MPa  opened 2011:   Two dispenser, each with 2 nozzles  mechanical chiller for precooling to -20°C   The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class: 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa yes.  Average utilisation 368 fills/month 1000 kg H2/month  Oct 2014: Upgrade is planned for middle of 2015.   June 2015: upgrade is delayed, estimated for Q1 2016   Aug 2016  upgrade is postponed to 2017   march 2017 temporary fueler is available with limited fueling until upgrade to retail station is ready  August 2017 upgraded retail station open March 2021: further upgrade is under pre-permitting Oct 2022: upgrade is planned for early 2023 Dec 2022: upgrade is planned to start mid 2023
旧的加氢站能够根据需求提供氢气。随着需求的增加，管道能够提供燃料来满足这些需求。氢气的成本为每公斤 4.5 美元至 5.5 美元。可同时为四辆汽车加氢。按照 SAE TIR-J2601 标准卸载。   如果开始时储存的氢气已满，则可同时为六辆汽车充气。  用于生产超纯氢气的 6MPa 氢气纯化技术 PDC 机器隔膜压缩机 50 公斤/天至 45 MPa Hydropac 液压增压压缩机至 100 MPa 2011 年启用：   两个分配器，每个分配器有 2 个喷嘴 机械冷却器，用于预冷至 -20°C 该加氢站是戴姆勒公司推荐的 FC B 级加氢站： 70 兆帕 是，35 兆帕 是。 平均利用率 368 次/月 1000 千克 H2/月 2014 年 10 月： 计划于 2015 年年中进行升级。  2015 年 6 月：升级被推迟，预计在 2016 年第一季度进行 2016 年 8 月：升级被推迟到 2017 年 2017 年 3 月：在零售站升级准备就绪之前，临时加油机可提供有限的加油服务 2017 年 8 月：升级后的零售站开放 2021 年 3 月：进一步升级正在进行前期许可 2022 年 10 月：升级计划在 2023 年初进行 2022 年 12 月：升级计划在 2023 年年中启动
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
hydrogen feed from existing AP pipeline; 4 kg/hr compressor skid; capacity 60 kg/day; 100% renewable hydrogen
从现有 AP 管道输送氢气；4 千克/小时压缩机撬装；产能 60 千克/天；100% 可再生氢气

Description 描述:
Old station opened 2007: Air Products designed, engineered and installed the station with funding from the U.S. Department of Energy and California’s South Coast Air Quality Management District. The National Fuel Cell Research Center at UC Irvine operates the station, which was open to authorized users. The station is maintained by Air Products.   21.04.2011 expand capacity; CEC co-funding awarded   The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class: 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa no.   Feb 2014: the station is public; upgrade is planned   Technical details: first compressor up to 50 MPa, second compressor reciprocating piston booster compressor up to 70 MPa, mechanical chiller for precooling to -20°C    Avarage utilization: 669 kg/month   average refueling time 2.2 min/kg   November 2015 opening as retail station with expanded capacity.  UC Irvine is the owner of the station property, NFCRC manages the site and leases the equipment from Air Products who is the owner, operator of the total equipment.  Spring 2016  retail commissioning is complete Nov 2018: one of the bussiest stations in South California, plans to upgrade capacity to 800 kg/day
旧车站于 2007 年启用： 在美国能源部和加州南海岸空气质量管理区的资助下，空气产品公司设计、建造并安装了该站。加州大学欧文分校的国家燃料电池研究中心负责运营该站，并向授权用户开放。该站由空气产品公司负责维护。  21.04.2011 扩大容量；获得 CEC 联合资助 该加气站由戴姆勒公司推荐为 FC B 级： 70 兆帕 是，35 兆帕 否。  技术细节：第一台压缩机最大压力为 50 兆帕，第二台压缩机为往复活塞式增压压缩机，最大压力为 70 兆帕，机械冷却器用于预冷至 -20°C 平均利用率： 669 公斤/月 平均加油时间 2.2 分钟/公斤 2015 年 11 月作为零售站开业，并扩大了容量。 加州大学欧文分校是加油站物业的所有者，NFCRC 负责场地管理，并从空气产品公司租赁设备，后者是整个设备的所有者和运营商。 2016 年春季零售调试完成 2018 年 11 月：南加州最繁忙的站点之一，计划将容量升级至 800 公斤/天

StationName 站名:
Honda Refueling Station
本田加油站
Street2 街道 2:
Honda's research and development center
本田的研发中心
Goal 目标:
The station is being used to: - conduct studies on hydrogen production, storage and fueling using renewable energy sources, - support the company's ongoing fuel cell powered vehicle development
该站的用途是 - 利用可再生能源对氢气的生产、储存和燃料添加进行研究， - 支持公司正在进行的燃料电池动力汽车的开发工作
Description 描述:
There were two stations: one with H2 production via electrolysis (Solar station) and a second with production via steam reforming (Home Energy station) which hasn´t existed anylonger since some time..    Honda R&D Co., Ltd., Honda's subsidiary responsible for research and development activities has established an experimental Home Energy Station (HES) that generates hydrogen from natural gas for use in fuel cell vehicles while supplying electricity and hot water to the home. Cars can be fueled at the rate of 20 liters per minute. Hydrogen is despensed to the vehicle using a unique fast-fill and multi-bank cascade system. Only Honda staff that have undergone special training and have been given a password are allowedd to perform fueling of vehicles and operation of the hydrogen dispenser.   The station has two filling modes:  - ""Fast Fill"" mode: FCV's are fueled directly from the high-pressure hydrogen tank in a short period  - ""Slow Fill"" mode: FCV's are fueled by hydrogen compressor in a comparatively long period.   The station uses an arry of photovoltaic (PV) cells to extract hydrogen from water via electrolysis. When power is unavailable or insufficient, electricity from the grid is used for the electrolysis process. The system, when running exiclusively on solar energy, can produce about 5,700 liters (@ 35 MPa) of gaseous hydrogen per year. By using both solar power and electricity from the grid, the station's capability is 26,000 liters per year.   There is also a Home Energy Station IV installed there. without compressor and with best system efficiency.  The station was installed 2001, with improvments 2003 and 2008.    29.01.2010 a new single-unit station begins operation with a new high differential pressure electrolyser.     2014 March: Air Products installed at the Honda´s R&D Headquarter a new station of the type  "SmartFuel" within 7 months from contract signing to final commissioning with 70 MPa and SAE J2601 standard.
有两个站：一个是通过电解生产 H2 的站（太阳能站），另一个是通过蒸汽重整生产 H2 的站（家庭能源站）。本田研发有限公司 有限公司 本田公司负责研发活动的子公司本田研究开发有限公司建立了一个试验性家庭能源站 (HES)，该能源站利用天然气生产氢气，供燃料电池汽车使用，同时为家庭提供电力和热水。汽车可以每分钟 20 升的速度加氢。氢气通过独特的快速加注和多罐级联系统输送到汽车中。只有经过特殊培训并获得密码的本田员工才能为汽车加氢和操作氢气分配器。加氢站有两种加氢模式： - "快速加氢 "模式： FCV 可在短时间内直接从高压氢气罐中获得燃料： FCV 由氢气压缩机在相对较长的时间内提供燃料。氢气站使用一组光伏 (PV) 电池，通过电解从水中提取氢气。当电力不可用或不足时，电解过程使用电网提供的电力。该系统完全依靠太阳能运行时，每年可生产约 5,700 升（@ 35 兆帕）气态氢。如果同时使用太阳能和电网提供的电力，则每年可生产 26,000 升氢气。共有两个氢气站： 这里还安装了家庭能源站 IV，不带压缩机，系统效率最高。该站于 2001 年安装，2003 年和 2008 年进行了改进。29. 2010 年 1 月：一个新的单体电站开始运行，配备了一个新的高压差电解槽。2014 年 3 月： 空气产品公司在本田研发总部安装了一座 "SmartFuel "型新电解槽，从签订合同到最终投入使用仅用了7个月时间，压力为70兆帕，符合SAE J2601标准。

StationName 站名:
Cal State LA
加州州立大学洛杉矶分校
Street1 街道1:
State University Drive
州立大学路
Street2 街道 2:
on the east side of the campus
校园东侧
Description 描述:
The station, which will cost $4.5 million, is the first piece of infrastructure in the development of a sustainable energy engineering academic program. It will operate as both a teaching and research resource for the campus, allowing for the study of sustainably produced hydrogen and its commercial viability. The facility will also serve as a public station, open to those driving hydrogen fuel cell vehicles and buses in the Los Angeles area.    The compressors and storage arrived in November 2010. The electrolyzer and other units were moved onsite on their foundations in January 2011.    First and second stage compressors ( PDC diaphragma 25 Nm³/h, 2 Hydro-Pac Intensifiers) for fast filling at 70 MPa  electrolyser by Hydrogenics HySTAT-30  30 Nm³/h 60kg/day   pre- cooling system -20°C by Quantum  grid-tied and powered by 100% renewable  60 kg high pressure storage  dispenser by Quantum  The station has passed H2 purity testing and has had the first fueling at 350 bar. CSULA will continue to test fueling protocols to verify the station readiness before opening to the public.   Test operation since 2013. Officially open since May 2014.   2015 certified to sell fuel to the public Jan 2020 CaFCP commissioning completed: This is a legacy retail station with limited performance, capacity, and operating hours. This station generates hydrogen using an on-site electrolyzer, with an available capacity of about 50 kg. The station may be able to fill up to 16 cars per day with an average fill time ranging from 10 to 15 minutes. Once the hydrogen supply is fully depleted, the station will take about 2-hours to refresh for the next vehicle and may take more than one day to replenish to full capacity. Dec 2022: unavailabel because of problems with the electrolyser
该氢气站耗资 450 万美元，是发展可持续能源工程学术项目的第一个基础设施。它将作为校园的教学和研究资源，研究可持续生产的氢气及其商业可行性。该设施还将作为一个公共站，向洛杉矶地区的氢燃料电池汽车和公共汽车驾驶员开放。压缩机和存储设备已于 2010 年 11 月运抵。2011 年 1 月，电解槽和其他设备被搬到现场的地基上。第一级和第二级压缩机（PDC diaphragma 25 Nm³/h，2 Hydro-Pac Intensifiers）用于在 70 MPa 压力下快速充气，电解器由 Hydrogenics 生产 HySTAT-30 30 Nm³/h 60kg/day 预冷系统-20°C，由 Quantum 生产 并网，由 100% 可再生能源供电，60 kg 高压存储分配器由 Quantum 生产 该站已通过 H2 纯度测试，并在 350 bar 压力下进行了首次充气。CSULA 将继续测试加油协议，以便在向公众开放之前验证加油站是否准备就绪。自 2013 年起试运行。自 2014 年 5 月起正式开放。2015 年获得向公众出售燃料的认证 2020 年 1 月完成 CaFCP 调试： 这是一个传统的零售站，性能、容量和运营时间有限。该站使用现场电解槽产生氢气，可用容量约为 50 千克。该加油站每天最多可为 16 辆汽车加油，平均加油时间为 10 至 15 分钟。一旦氢气供应完全耗尽，加氢站将需要约 2 个小时为下一辆车重新加氢，并可能需要一天以上的时间才能将氢气补充到满负荷。2022 年 12 月：因电解槽问题无法使用。

Description 描述:
First designed and built by BP and Air Products.  Now Hydrogen Frontier maintains the station with steam reforming on-site.  Oct. 2014: An upgrade is under development.  The station has a natural gas reformer system H2GEN HGM2000 (capacity 108 kg/day). Two  2 kg/h PDC machines with diaphragm compressors to store the H2 at 43,5 MPa. 35 MPa refueling from high-pressure storage or 70MPa refueling using a hydraulic booster compressor (Air Products S700, capacity 50kg/h, 0.8kg/min). Pre-cooling system to -20°C. Fillrate 1.75 kg/min with chiller, 0.25  kg/min without cooling. One dispenser with two nozzles.  In 2012 41 FC vehicles were filled per month in average, 120 kg H2 /month; peak month had 76 fillls with 220 kg H2.   March 2017: NEL Hydrogen Solution will deliver a new equipment. 2020 July: upgrade with NEL technology is still under commissioning 2020 September: probably out of operation

Description 描述:
First Air Liquide provided a mobile station (CGH2) to support pre-production bus. Now a permanent station with a 10 years contract with probable extension.   Specification:  99% availability  45 kg H2 filling in 10 minutes  no significant dead times between fills  recover heat losses  avg. consumption 460kg/day   LH2 tanker delivery capacity 3.8 t   Liquefaction at Becancour Qc     20.09.2012: fuel cell bus fleet exceeds 1,5 million miles in service; project runs through 2014
液化空气公司首先提供了一个流动站（CGH2），为试生产总线提供支持。现在，该流动站已成为一个永久性站点，合同期为 10 年，并有可能延期。  规格： 99% 可用性 10 分钟内加注 45 千克 H2，加注之间无明显死锁时间 回收热损失 平均消耗量 460 千克/天 LH2 罐车交付能力 3.8 吨 在贝康库尔（Becancour Qc）液化 2012 年 9 月 20 日： 燃料电池公交车行驶里程超过 150 万英里；项目持续到 2014 年

Comments 评论:
The BC Hydrogen Highway is a coordinated, large-scale demonstration and deployment program intended to accelerate the commercialization of hydrogen and fuel-cell technologies. Project duration 5 years.
Targeted for full implementation by the 2010 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games in Vancouver and Whistler (extended to Victoria), the project will be a showcase of sustainable transportation, creating a hydrogen highway that will allow visitors to travel between the Vancouver Airport and Whistler for the 2010 Olympics.
The first bus was delivered on November 10, 2009. Until December all 20 buses were in operation.
Up to April 2010 1385 fills with 33207 kg of H2 and 275652 km of bus operation.
The project was evaluated by US NREL (see DoE annual progress report 2014. 
The project will not continue after March 2014 because of high costs.
不列颠哥伦比亚省氢能高速公路是一项协调的大规模示范和部署计划，旨在加快氢能和燃料电池技术的商业化进程。项目为期 5 年。
该项目计划在 2010 年温哥华和惠斯勒（延伸至维多利亚）冬季奥运会和残奥会之前全面实施，它将成为可持续交通的一个展示窗口，创建一条氢气高速公路，使游客能够在 2010 年奥运会期间往返于温哥华机场和惠斯勒之间。
第一辆巴士于 2009 年 11 月 10 日交付。直到 12 月，所有 20 辆巴士都已投入运营。
截至 2010 年 4 月，1385 辆巴士加注了 33207 千克 H2，巴士运行里程达 275652 千米。
美国 NREL 对该项目进行了评估（见能源部 2014 年年度进展报告）。
由于成本过高，该项目在 2014 年 3 月之后将不再继续。

Description 描述:
The fuelling station was designed to be modular, open and accessible to researchers. The system currently uses hydrogen gas delivered by BOC Canada in a conventional tube trailer, and is ready to accommodate gas that may be generated on-site in the future. The system has two stages of hydrogen gas compression in a unique design by BOC Canada, plus storage and dispensing through a system supplied by General Hydrogen. System design and integration was performed by BOC, with facilities integration, data management and operation by NRC. Description 描述:
This fuelling station is operated by Powertech Labs Inc. and opened in March 2002. In November 2002, the station was upgraded to deliver fuel to vehicles requiring higher pressure hydrogen gas, becoming the first in the world to fuel at 70 Mega Pascals.   In March 2004, the station was upgraded with a more efficient electrolyser with funding support from Natural Resources Canada’s Canadian Transportation Fuel Cell Alliance.  The station started providing hydrogen fuel for the Vancouver Fuel Cell Vehicle Program in 2005.  2017  Upgraded to 70 MPa SAE J2601 standrard with pre-cooling and publicly accessible. 2020: temporarily unavailable 2022: status unclear, probably closed

BCHH Heavy-Duty Fuelling Station Transit - Ballard PEM Bus Demo

Description 描述:
The first station was part of the Ballard Fuel Cell Demo Project: Three buses could be filled within a 12-hour period. Components: Electrolyser by Stuart Energy (now Hydrogenics), Storage System, Dispenser Hydrogen was generated on-site from electricity in an electrolyzer and filled into the buses over night in a slow fill setting. This station was in operation between 1998 and 2000. Partners: Ballard, Xellsis, Hydrogenics.   The new station ist part of the BCHH and provides a blend of H2 and natural gas which is used in four demonstration buses of TransLink.   Hydrogen is captured from a hydrogen waste stream in North Vancouver, processed, then transported to Port Coquitlam (by Clean Energy). The Port Coquitlam facilities will be designed to be fast-filling, and provide HCNG with a mixture of 20% hydrogen by volume.    TransLink is testing and evaluating a variety of innovative and alternative fuelling options for its buses.
第一个站点是巴拉德燃料电池示范项目的一部分： 可在 12 小时内为三辆公共汽车加满燃料。组件 斯图尔特能源公司（现为 Hydrogenics 公司）的电解槽、存储系统、分配器 氢气通过电解槽在现场发电，并在夜间以缓慢填充的方式注入巴士。该站于 1998 年至 2000 年间投入使用。合作伙伴： 巴拉德（Ballard）、Xellsis、Hydrogenics。  新加氢站是 BCHH 的一部分，提供混合氢气和天然气，用于 TransLink 的四辆示范巴士。  氢气从北温哥华的氢气废物流中提取，经过处理后运往高贵林港（由清洁能源公司负责）。高贵林港的设施将设计为快速充气，并提供氢气含量为 20% 的氢气混合物。   TransLink 正在为其公共汽车测试和评估各种创新的替代燃料方案。

Description 描述:
The BC Hydrogen Highway is a coordinated, large-scale demonstration and deployment program intended to accelerate the commercialization of hydrogen and fuel-cell technologies. Targeted for full implementation by the 2010 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games in Vancouver and Whistler, the project will be a showcase of sustainable transportation, creating a hydrogen highway that will allow visitors to travel between the Vancouver Airport and Whistler for the 2010 Olympics. Victoria station is the first of the Highway.  January 2008 new contracts with Air Liquide and Hydrogenics. The new parts, supplied, operate and maintained by Air Liquide will be completed by mid 2008.
不列颠哥伦比亚省氢能高速公路是一项协调的大规模示范和部署计划，旨在加快氢能和燃料电池技术的商业化进程。该项目计划在 2010 年温哥华和惠斯勒冬季奥运会和残奥会之前全面实施，它将成为可持续交通的一个展示窗口，创建一条氢气高速公路，让游客可以在 2010 年奥运会期间往返于温哥华机场和惠斯勒之间。维多利亚站是该高速公路的第一个站点。 2008 年 1 月 与液化空气公司和 Hydrogenics 签订新合同。由液化空气公司提供、运营和维护的新部件将于 2008 年年中完工。

Faridabad Hydrogen-CNG Dispensing Station
法里达巴德氢气-压缩天然气加注站
Street1 街道1:

Goal 目标:
Station for research and development purposes
用于研究和开发目的的站点
Description 描述:
The equipment consists of a HCNG mixing unit, and dual dispensing unit which has the ability to fuel vehicles with either a HCNG blend or with pure hydrogen. The commissioning of the pilot dispensing station will provide the hydrogen implementation team at Indian Oil‘s R&D Centre a hands-on experience with onsite hydrogen production, storage, distribution and supply. The team will study the performance and emission characteristics of the vehicles operating from 5% - 30% hydrogen blended with CNG and stored onboard at 200 bar.   Electrolyser : Hydrogenics PEM 30 Nm³/h  Compressor : Howden S150  Four type 1 storage tank  Dispense:  Air Products   Dispenser has dual nozzle for HCNG dispensing and H2 Dispensing.  H2 dispensing to be commissioned by mid March of 2015  Will be used for Bus refuelling 
该设备包括 HCNG 混合装置和双分配装置，能够为车辆提供 HCNG 混合燃料或纯氢燃料。试点分配站的投入使用将为印度石油公司研发中心的氢气实施团队提供现场氢气生产、储存、分配和供应的实践经验。该团队将研究使用 5%-30%氢气与压缩天然气混合并在 200 巴压力下储存在车内的车辆的性能和排放特性。  电解器：Hydrogenics PEM 30 Nm³/h 压缩机：Howden S150 四个 1 型储气罐 调配：  空气产品公司的分配器有双喷嘴，可分配 HCNG 和 H2。 H2 加注将于 2015 年 3 月中旬投入使用。

Beijing Sinohytec station
北京中技站
Street1 街道1:
Haidian Yongfeng Hi-tech Industrial Base
海淀永丰高新技术产业基地
Goal 目标:
The goal of the project is to reduce GHG emissions and air pollution through widespread commercial introduction of FCBs in urban areas of China. 
该项目的目标是通过在中国城市地区广泛商业化引进 FCB，减少温室气体排放和空气污染。
Description 描述:
The Beijing Hydrogen Park is China’s first demonstration project for new energy vehicles. Beijing Hydrogen Refueling Station is co-built by Beijing Sinohytec Co Ltd, BP company and Air Products company.    Operator until January 2009 AirProducts; since 2009 Sinohytec.   Initially, hydrogen was  trucked-in supplied from AP plant, then one 50NM3/h small SMR was on stream onsite in 2008, and  50NM3/h small water electrolyser was established in 2010 onsite. This skid device was developed by the 718th Institute of Handan.    One dispenser with three nozzles for different type of vehicles.  April 2017: more then 2000 times refueling with nearly 20000 kg H2 from 2006 to 2010
北京氢能园是中国首个新能源汽车示范项目。北京加氢站由北京中海技术有限公司、BP 公司和空气产品公司共同建设。   2009 年 1 月之前的运营方为空气化工产品公司；2009 年之后的运营方为中国石化。  最初，氢气由卡车从 AP 工厂运入，然后于 2008 年在现场安装了一个 50NM3/h 的小型 SMR，并于 2010 年在现场安装了 50NM3/h 的小型水电解槽。该撬装装置由邯郸第 718 研究所研制。   一台加气机有三个喷嘴，可用于不同类型的车辆。 2017 年 4 月：从 2006 年到 2010 年，加注近 20000 公斤 H2 超过 2000 次
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site, 50 Nm³/h  by electrolysis, 50 Nm³/ by SMR; new info 2018: 200 kg/day, 2020: 500 kg
现场，电解法 50 牛立方米/小时，SMR 法 50 牛立方米/小时；新信息 2018 年：200 千克/天，2020 年：500 千克
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
7,000 Nm³ CGH2; new info 2018:165 kg at 45 MPa
7,000 牛米³ CGH2；2018 年新信息：45 兆帕时 165 千克
VehiclesServed 服务车辆: 3 FCBs by Daimler since Nov, 2005(UNDP/GEF project), 5-10 FCBs R&D by Tsinghua University(Most 863 project), and 20 FC cars by Shanghai VW for the Beijing Olympic Games demonstration project
Contact 联系方式:
Beijing Sinohytec Co., Ltd.  Suit 4500 Yejing Building, Tsinghua University, Beijing, 100084. Tel:010-62796419
北京中海达科技股份有限公司  北京清华大学业精楼 4500 室，邮编 100084。电话：010-62796419
Comments 评论:
The station is funded by the Chinese Ministry of Science and Technology within the 863 program.
This is a cooperation project of UNDP/GEF and China Most.
The filling station is part of a eight-year, 2-phased project funded by the UN. Phase I (started in  2004) launched three  fuel cell buses and a filling station in Beijing. 
Phase II (starts in late 2006) will launch three additional fuel cell buses and a filling station in Shanghai.
See also www.chinafcb.org www.gefonline.org www.undp.org
该站由中国科技部 863 计划资助。

StationName 站名:
Anting Hydrogen Refueling Station
安亭加氢站
Street1 街道1:

City 城市:

Description 描述:
Anting Hydrogen Refueling Station is co-built by Tongji University, Shanghai Aerospace Energy Co. and Shanghai Sunwise Energy Systems Co. Shell Hydrogen cooperates with Tongji University as technical consultant and funds part of the station demonstration. Linde and Shanghai Gas Engineering Design Instiute provides engineering services for the construction of the station. After trucked into the station by tube trailer, H2 is then compressed into the storage cylinders. H2 can be refueled to the vehicle from the tube trailer, storage cylinder or from the compressor directly.   The hydrogen is supplied by a hydrogen purification device in Shanghai Coking Company. This device was developed by Tongji and other companies in 2005, which is also one part of the 863 government project.   A Visitor Center, located within the station, is subsidized by Shell Hydrogen.   In 2013 the station was visited by WHTC conference study tour.  2016: H2 supply from Linde´s SMR plant in Shanghai. Linde diaphragm compression.   April 2017: over 6000 times refueling with more then 10 000 kg H2
安亭加氢站由同济大学、上海航天能源有限公司和上海新智能源系统有限公司共同建设。壳牌氢能源作为技术顾问与同济大学合作，并为加氢站的部分示范工程提供资金。林德和上海燃气工程设计研究院为加气站的建设提供工程服务。氢气通过管式拖车运入加氢站后，被压缩到储气罐中。氢气可从管式拖车、储气罐或压缩机直接加注到车辆上。  氢气由上海焦化公司的氢气净化装置提供。该装置由同济等公司于 2005 年开发，也是政府 863 项目的一部分。  站内设有游客中心，由壳牌氢气提供补贴。  2013 年，世界氢能大会考察团参观了该站。 2016: 林德上海 SMR 工厂供应 H2。林德隔膜压缩。  2017 年 4 月：加氢超过 6000 次，加氢量超过 10 000 千克 H2
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:

Description 描述:
China’s first Hydrogen Filling Station had the mission to provide the three vehicles taking part in den 2004 Michelin Bibendum challenge with hydrogen. The Bibendum Challenge is a competition for ultra-low emission vehicles and took place at Shanghai’s new Formula One circuit. The entire system (a mobile station) is comprised of a hydrogen dispenser, sequencing panel, high pressure storage (provided by Dynetek), a gas booster and hydraulic air compressor. The Mobile Station also boasts on-board controls and an autonomous power supply. FTI fast-fill hydrogen dispenser
中国第一个加氢站的任务是为参加 2004 年米其林必比登挑战赛的三辆汽车提供氢气。必比登挑战赛是在上海新一级方程式赛车场举行的超低排放车辆比赛。整个系统（移动站）由氢气分配器、排序面板、高压储存器（由 Dynetek 提供）、气体增压器和液压空气压缩机组成。移动站还拥有车载控制装置和自主电源。FTI 快速填充氢气分配器

Description 描述:
The Expo 2005 Aichi Japan, Seto-Minami Hydrogen Station produces hydrogen on-site by reforming city gas; using this as the base load, byproduct hydrogen attained off-site is combined and utilized, making this the first domestic hybrid type hydrogen station. With a two-tier hydrogen supply source, a high level of supply reliability has been secured, and the auxiliary use of off-site hydrogen has made possible the highly efficient operation of the on-site city gas reforming hydrogen production facility.
2005 年日本爱知世博会濑户南氢气站通过城市煤气重整在现场生产氢气，并以此为基本负荷，合并和利用场外获得的副产品氢气，使其成为国内首个混合型氢气站。通过两级氢气供应源，确保了高水平的供应可靠性，而辅助使用场外氢气则使现场城市煤气重整制氢设施的高效运行成为可能。

Description 描述:
This was  first a station for experimental study. Upgrade to 70 MPa in September 2008: Now renewed for commercial use.   Steam reformer + PSA 75 Nm³/h, Compressor 110 Nm³/h, Storage cylinders , Dispenser refueling pressure 82 MPa, Pre-cooling system -40°C; Hydrogen Quality over 99.97% (ISO14687-2); hydrogen shipping facility to supply other stations. 2023: Anion Exchange Membrane (AEM) water electrolyzer started H2 production, 100% renewable electricity (with non-fossil certificate). The AEM water electrolyzer, manufactured by Enapter, consists of 30 modules and has a hydrogen production capacity of 15 Nm3/h. The modules can be operated individually, offering redundancy that allows continuous operation of the entire facility in the event of a single failure.Hydrogen will be produced even at night and stored at less than 1 MPa in an introduced hydrogen tank

Description 描述:
The Ome Hydrogen Station includes facilities for producing hydrogen by reforming natural gas (city gas). This station can be moved to any place for supplying hadrogen because ist hzydrogen production device and fueling device are vehicle-mounted. This station is highly available and the cost for hydrogen generation is low because the infrastructure for natural gas reforming is already well organized.
奥姆氢气站包括通过重整天然气（城市煤气）生产氢气的设施。由于氢气生产装置和加氢装置都是车载式的，因此该氢气站可以移动到任何地方供应氢气。该氢气站的可用性很高，制氢成本也很低，因为天然气转化的基础设施已经非常完善。

Description 描述:
The hydrogen station is located at the yard of Tsurumi Soda Co., Ltd. in Tsurumi-Ku, Yokohama city. Bi-product hydrogen gas of 97~98% purity, produced from salt electrolysis in Tsurumi Soda Co., Ltd, is utilized and refined to purity of 99.99% removing imurities and then pressurized up to 19.6 MPa and filled up on tank lorry to transport from head office to the station.
氢气站位于横滨市鹤见区的鹤见纯碱株式会社院内。利用鹤见纯碱株式会社盐电解产生的纯度为 97% 至 98% 的副产品氢气，除去杂质后提纯至纯度为 99.99%，然后加压至 19.6 兆帕，装入罐车，从总公司运往氢气站。

StationName 站名:
ITM Power - Rotherham Station
ITM 电力公司 - 罗瑟勒姆站
Street1 街道1:
Morse Way, off Brunel Way, Catcliffe
莫尔斯路，卡特克利夫布鲁内尔路附近
Street2 街道 2:
Advanced Manufacturing Park (AMP)
先进制造园 (AMP)
Description 描述:
H2 will be generated onsite by electrolysis. Electricity from wind power turbine 225 kW. Air Products S100 hydrogen fuelling system and green H2 store for Hydrogen Mini Grid.   First hydrogen was produced in January 2009.  Further operation status unclear   July 2013 ITM will become operator of the facility - obviously new partner consortium.  New station September 2015:  The site consists of a 225kW wind turbine coupled directly to an electrolyser, 200kg of hydrogen storage, a hydrogen dispensing unit and a 30kW fuel cell system capable of providing backup power generation for nearby buildings. The facility is a showcase for ITM Power’s world-class hydrogen generation equipment and is used to provide retail hydrogen fuel services. The M1 motorway was highlighted as a key route for the early deployment of hydrogen refuelling in the UK in the published UK H2Mobility Phase 1 Report. The facility develops ITM Power’s modular commercial platform for hydrogen generation systems, Power-to-Gas and refuelling solutions. The system is designed so that energy from the wind turbine is used to provide power for some of the buildings on the Advanced Manufacturing Park, with excess energy being used by the electrolyser to generate hydrogen gas. The gas is then compressed and stored ready for dispensing into hydrogen fuel cell vehicles.  Further project partner is Fuel Cell Systems. Sep 2022: pressue level 35 MPa unclear
H2 将在现场通过电解产生。电力来自 225 千瓦的风力涡轮机。空气产品公司的 S100 加氢系统和小型氢气网的绿色氢气储存库。  2009 年 1 月生产出第一批氢气。 2013 年 7 月，ITM 将成为该设施的运营商，显然是新的合作伙伴财团。 2015 年 9 月新建加氢站：  该站点由一台 225 千瓦的风力涡轮机直接连接到一个电解槽、200 千克的储氢装置、一个氢气分配装置和一个 30 千瓦的燃料电池系统组成，能够为附近的建筑物提供备用电源。该设施是 ITM Power 世界级制氢设备的展示窗口，用于提供氢燃料零售服务。在已发布的《英国 H2Mobility 第一阶段报告》中，M1 高速公路被强调为英国早期部署氢燃料加注的关键路线。该设施开发了 ITM Power 的模块化商业平台，用于氢气发电系统、Power-to-Gas 和加氢解决方案。该系统的设计是利用风力涡轮机的能量为先进制造园的一些建筑提供电力，多余的能量则由电解槽生成氢气。氢气随后被压缩和储存，以备注入氢燃料电池汽车。 其他项目合作伙伴为燃料电池系统公司。2022 年 9 月：压力

Goal 目标:
Demonstration and verification of hydrogen production, storage, safety regulation, and fuel cell applications
氢气生产、储存、安全监管和燃料电池应用的示范与验证
Description 描述:
We are currently working on membrane enhanced reformation for hydrogen production to improve the efficiency. We are also building a prototype device using waste heat to compress hydrogen for refuelling service. Fuel cell applications can use the above infrastructure for standardized testing, technology validation and demonstration as well. 
我们目前正在研究膜强化重整制氢技术，以提高效率。我们还在建造一个利用余热压缩氢气的原型装置，用于加气服务。燃料电池应用也可以利用上述基础设施进行标准化测试、技术验证和示范。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site, from natural gas, capacity of 5 Nm³/h
现场使用天然气，流量为 5 Nm³/h
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
216 Nm3 /Steel cylinder/ Compressed/ 5Nm3/h

StationName 站名:
Total Holzmarktstraße (new)
Holzmarktstraße 总计（新）
Description 描述:
Old station 2010 - 2013:    Project started January 2009, construction start was April 2009, anticipated start of operation September 2009 (LH2), CGH2 up from May 2010   Concept:  Integration of hydrogen into an existing TOTAL station in central Berlin with 35 and 70 MPa pressure level.  CGH2:  Pressure electrolysis plant by Hydrogen Technologies (a Statoil subsidiary now NEL Hydrogen )  - Dry-running piston compressor (500 bar) by Andreas HOFER  Hochdrucktechnik in cooperation with Statoil  - Booster compressor (1000 bar) by Andreas HOFER Hochdrucktechnik in cooperation with Statoil  - Underground cascade storage system of composite cylinders, developed by Statoil  LH2:  Linde supplies LH2 from the liquefication plant in Leuna. From autumn 2010 up a part of the LH2 will be produced from a waste product in the Biodiesel production.  - Usage of LH2 tank and pump from previous station Berlin, Messedamm  - Boil-off management by means of Mini-BHKW  - Usage of´all tail gases with the help of new boil-off installation  - fully automated automotive coupling with a mechanical handling aid  storage: under ground storage of CGH2 (100 MPa), new 2 step compressor technology and LH2 tank   In addition, the filling station is equipped with two stationary hydrogen fuel cells ( Axane Fuel Cell Systems, Electro Power Systems) using the boil-off from stored liquide hydrogen to generate warmth respectively electricity. The electricity is fed into the local grid, whereas the warmth is used to support the heating system of the station. There is also a Photovoltaik system.  Since spring 2012 "Wind H2" delivery from Prenzlau   The station was recommended by Daimler for FC B-class 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa no.The station was accepted by major car companies.    The station was closed at the end of 2013 (equipment to KIT). New station was reopend with new technology in spring 2015. Now only 70 MPa and only LH2  delivery (from Leuna) by Linde. Linde cryo compressor.
现有的 TOTAL 站中，压力水平为 35 和 70 兆帕。CGH2：氢技术公司（挪威国家石油公司的子公司，现为 NEL Hydrogen）的压力电解装置 - Andreas HOFER Hochdrucktechnik 公司与挪威国家石油公司合作的干式活塞压缩机（500 巴） - Andreas HOFER Hochdrucktechnik 公司与挪威国家石油公司合作的增压压缩机（1000 巴） - 挪威国家石油公司开发的复合气瓶地下级联存储系统 LH2：林德从位于 Leuna 的液化厂供应 LH2。从 2010 年秋季开始，部分 LH2 将从生物柴油生产过程中产生的废料中提取。- 使用柏林梅塞达姆加气站的 LH2 储罐和泵 - 通过 Mini-BHKW 进行沸腾管理 - 在新沸腾装置的帮助下使用所有尾气 - 带有机械处理辅助装置的全自动汽车联轴器 存储：地下存储 CGH2 (100MPa)、新型 2 级压缩机技术和 LH2 储罐 此外，加气站还配备了两个固定式氢燃料电池（Axane 燃料电池系统，Electro Power Systems），利用存储的液化氢沸腾产生的热量分别发电。电力被输送到当地电网，而暖气则用于支持电站的供暖系统。此外，还有一个光伏发电系统。自 2012 年春季起，"Wind H2 "将从普伦茨劳发货。戴姆勒公司推荐该加油站为 FC B 级加油站，压力为 70 兆帕，35 兆帕。主要汽车公司都接受了该电站。加气站于 2013 年底关闭（设备移交给 KIT）。2015 年春，采用新技术的新站重新开放。现在只有 70 兆帕，林德只提供 LH2（来自 Leuna）。林德低温压缩机。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
"renewable" H2 from Linde production plant in Leuna (by-product Bio- diesel production),  compressor capacity 100 kg/h, capacity 200 kg/d
"可再生 "H2，来自林德位于Leuna的生产厂（副产品生物柴油生产），压缩机容量100公斤/小时，容量200公斤/天
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
LH2 in a super-insulated tank without after-cooling, 400 kg
 不带后冷却装置的超级隔热罐中的 LH2，400 千克

StationName 站名:
HafenCity
哈芬城
Street2 街道 2:
Hafencity
哈芬城
Goal 目标:
to realize pure hydrogen station within city centre, to gain experience with truck delivery 
在市中心建立纯氢站，积累卡车运输经验
Description 描述:
• Hardware by Linde  • Two story building  • 2 electrolysers ( Hydrogenics HySAT-60 electrolyzer for 260 kg H2 /day  120 Nm³/h), optional 3  for 20 busses and some passenger cars per day ( 750 kg/d)   • purification: Donaldson Ultrafilter  • 2  Ionic compressors Linde  • Middle & high pressure tanks (2 at 45 bar with 2x 215 kg  (Vako),   120 high pressure bottles at 830 bar with approx. 250 kg, 6000l) (Faber)  • 350 bar for cars and buses  • 700 bar technology, SAE J2601  • 50% of dispensed hydrogen will be from electrolysis on-site  • Electrolysis uses certificates to ensure renewable hydrogen  • Other 50% of hydrogen are trucked in at night  • Buses in daily haul  • Bus refuelings during day  • No service or snack-shop  • Only 688 m² footprint  • Partly danger of flooding  • Rural mixed area (offices)  • Surrounded by water  • Bridges at each end of the property  • Traffic (cars, bikes, pedestrians, ships)  • Permit following BImSch  SAEJ 2601  Delivery of CGH2 isn´t necessary. Capacity of the electrolysis is sufficient also with consideration of fleet forecast.   The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa  no.   The station is accepted by major car companies.   Vattenfall used to be involved, but now H2 Mobility is the operator. Februar 2019: 4 old buses went out of operation, but will again be replaced by FC buses Station is meanwhile mostly supplied by delivery because of economical reasons (high taxes on electricity)
- 林德硬件 - 两层建筑 - 2 个电解槽（Hydrogenics HySAT-60 电解槽，260 千克 H2/天，120 Nm³/h），可选 3 个电解槽，20 辆公共汽车和一些客车/天（750 千克/天） - 净化： 唐纳森超滤器 - 2 台离子压缩机 林德 - 中压和高压罐（2 个，压力 45 巴，容量 2x 215 千克（Vako），120 个高压瓶，压力 830 巴，容量约 250 千克，6000 升）。汽车和公交车用 350 巴 - 700 巴技术，SAE J2601 - 50%的氢气来自现场电解 - 电解使用证书以确保氢气的可再生性 - 另外 50%的氢气在夜间用卡车运入 - 每天有公交车运输 - 白天有公交车加气 - 没有服务或小卖部 - 占地面积仅 688 平方米 - 有部分洪水危险 - 农村混合区（办公楼） - 四周环水 - 两端有桥 - 交通（汽车、自行车、行人、船只） - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 - 有水 交通（汽车、自行车、行人、轮船） - 不需要 BImSch SAEJ 2601 许可即可交付 CGH2。考虑到车队的预测，电解能力也足够。  戴姆勒公司推荐该电解站为 FC B 级电解站，压力为 70 兆帕，35 兆帕。  主要汽车公司都认可该电站。  Vattenfall 曾经参与其中，但现在 H2 Mobility 是运营商。2019 年 2 月：4 辆旧公交车停运，但将再次由 FC 公交车取代 由于经济原因（电费税率高），车站目前主要由交付方式提供服务
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site with electricity produced by renewable energy ( with certified `green` energy); 780kg/day; until 2013: 20 buses or 200 passenger cars /day

VehiclesServed 服务车辆: 6 busses of Hamburger Hochbahn and passenger cars; Feb 2019: 4 old bues went out of operation, but will be replaced
