Description 描述:
Air Products designed and incorporated the safety systems to allow it to be used more broadly for hydrogen vehicles, 24 hours a day with self-service. It is a turn-key system with modular single parts of the model series 100.   The hydrogen is a byproduct of the near by chemical industry.   13.05.2011: 2 H2-Hybrid buses are in operation now   The station is accepted by major car companies.  It has a high level of availability (>95%).  2017: After CHIC project end: plans to expand the FC bus fleet 2019: upgrade to refuel more buses March 2022: first 5 Solaris buses start operation Sept 2022: 10 buses in operation of RVK
空气产品公司设计并集成了安全系统，使其能够更广泛地用于氢能汽车，每天 24 小时提供自助服务。这是一个交钥匙系统，采用 100 型系列的模块化单一部件。  氢气是附近化学工业的副产品。  13.05.2011: 2 辆 H2-Hybrid 公交车已投入运营。 可用率很高（>95%）。 2017: CHIC 项目结束后：计划扩大 FC 巴士车队 2019 年：升级为更多巴士加油 2022 年 3 月：首批 5 辆 Solaris 巴士投入运营 2022 年 9 月：10 辆 RVK 巴士投入运营

Description 描述:
Until 2010 a temporary station was in Lise-Meitner-Str. 14.  Hydrogenics provided a HySTAT 30 hydrogen generation unit and a HyPM 50 kW fuel cell power system to Herten. In 2013 the electrolyser started the operation to use surplus wind electricity to produce H2 and to use this H2 in a CHP in the hydrogen center (nearby the filling station).   Possible plans to install a new station at the H2 center to use the H2 for refueling. Plans depend on the possibility to get FC vehicles.   July 2013: electrolyser started to work in nearby H2 center 
直到 2010 年，在 Lise-Meitner-Str. 14.  Hydrogenics 为赫腾提供了 HySTAT 30 制氢装置和 HyPM 50 kW 燃料电池发电系统。2013 年，电解槽开始运行，利用剩余的风能生产氢气，并在氢气中心（加气站附近）的热电联产中使用这些氢气。  可能计划在氢气中心安装一个新的加气站，利用氢气进行加气。计划取决于获得 FC 汽车的可能性。  2013 年 7 月：附近制氢中心的电解槽开始工作

Three stations were planned for 2009/2010 and 2x5 H2 buses were already ordered and the three HRS were also already contracted, up to 60 light vehicles to be acquired; public budget £ 25 million. But this plans were cancelled.   March 2010:   The new plans are a pilot fleet of about 150 hydrogen cars in the run-up to the 2012 London Olympics, together with five buses (H2 ICE) and 20 black taxis and 6 hydrogen refueling stations around London.     11.07.2012 Hyundai ix35 used as first passenger car the station in May 2012 and H2 buses reach 1000 fuelling    February 2014: Accessibility will be increased to help to create a hydrogen refueling station network.

Description 描述:
The gas station design has basically not changed since before the Great Depression of the 1930‘s. Today's gas station in America, which is a convenience store with its pumps placed on islands set in grey fields of concrete or asphalt under bright energy wasting lights, is virtually the same as those that were built in the 1920's. The fuel was, and still is, stored in leaky, environmentally damaging underground tanks and is the same oil based dinosaur then as it is now. M Squared is determined to change the way you look at this architectural eye sore. The stations will either have a futuristic look or have a retro yet futuristic appearance. 
自 20 世纪 30 年代经济大萧条之前，加油站的设计基本上就没有改变过。今天美国的加油站是一家便利店，其加油机被放置在灰色的混凝土或沥青地面上，灯光明亮，浪费能源，与 20 世纪 20 年代建造的加油站几乎没有什么区别。燃料过去和现在都储存在渗漏的、破坏环境的地下油罐中，而且当时和现在都是以石油为基础的恐龙。M Squared 决心改变人们对这一建筑疮疤的看法。这些加油站要么具有未来主义的外观，要么具有复古但未来感十足的外观。

Goal 目标:
Implementation of the hydrogen technology in South Tyrol; Further H2 stations along the motorway Bolzano -Modena are planned to supply the hole motorway with hydrogen until 2013.
在南蒂罗尔州实施氢气技术；计划在 2013 年之前，在博尔扎诺-摩德纳高速公路沿线建立更多的氢气站，为这条高速公路提供氢气。
Description 描述:
The  plant combines the distribution of traditional fuel, natural gas, bio-methane and mixtures of self-produced hydrogen within a service area with:  Co-generation plant H2-CNG/O2,   H2 production site,   Multienergy filling station for H2CNG vehicles,   H2 filling station for H2 buses and cars.    Hydrogen is produced from hydropower via electrolysis at max. 500 kg/day (5.700 Nm³). The capacity could be doubled in the future. The HRS dispenses pure hydrogen as well as natural gas/hydrogen mixtures (HCNG) with a content of up to max. 30% H2 in CH4. The CNG buses in Bolzano then can be refuelled with HCNG.    The station is located at the Autobahn exit Bolzano South and thus well situated for the highway users as well as for the local residents/ customers.    September 21, 2009 groundbreaking of the center  September 25, 2010: a new FC citybus was presented (Hydrogenics, 200km, 44 passengers)  May 2011: H2/CNG Iveco bus presentation  Nov 2012:  Station 1 was in operation for a short period to evaluate some experimental projects with H2-CNG bus operation. It was supplied with H2 delivery. Station 2 (CHIC station) will get an electrolyser, which will be delivered at the end of 2013. Refueling for Buses (35 MPa) and cars (70MPa) will be possible then.  June 2013: Hydrogenics will provide 3 HySTAT(R)60 electrolyser  August 2013: first buses was delivered, which will be refueled at a temporary station at H2 center operated by IIT. Further 4 buses will be delivered end of September  September 2013: buses were delivered, refueled at a  temporary filling station  Dec 2016: no changes after project end of CHIC 2019 January: FC passengers cars can be rent 2019 June: 12 FC buses from Solaris are ordered 2021 May: the first two Solaris buses arrived
    H2 公共汽车和汽车的氢气加气站。通过电解从水力发电中生产氢气，最大生产量为每天 500 千克（5. 500 公斤/天（5. 700 Nm³）。未来产能可翻倍。HRS 提供纯氢以及天然气/氢气混合物 (HCNG)，氢气在 CH4 中的含量最高可达 30%。在 CH4 中的氢含量最高可达 30%。这样，博尔扎诺的 CNG 公共汽车就可以加注 HCNG。该加气站位于博尔扎诺南部高速公路出口处，对高速公路使用者和当地居民/客户来说都是绝佳的位置。2009 年 9 月 21 日：该中心破土动工 2010 年 9 月 25 日：一辆新的 FC 城市客车亮相（Hydrogenics，200 公里，44 名乘客） 2011 年 5 月： H2/CNG 依维柯巴士亮相 2012 年 11 月：  1 号站投入短期运营，对一些 H2-CNG 公共汽车运营实验项目进行评估。该站已交付 H2。2 号站（CHIC 站）将配备一个电解槽，将于 2013 年底交付。届时将可为巴士（35 兆帕）和轿车（70 兆帕）加气。2013 年 6 月： 2013 年 8 月：第一辆公共汽车交付，将在印度理工学院运营的 H2 中心的临时加气站加气。另外 4 辆公交车将于 9 月底交付 2013 年 9 月：公交车交付，在临时加气站加气 2016 年 12 月：CHIC 项目结束后无变化 2019 年 1 月： FC 客车可以租用 2019 年 6 月： 2021 年 5 月：首批两辆 Solaris 巴士抵达。

Further H2 stations along the motorway Bolzano -Modena are planned to supply the hole motorway with hydrogen until 2013. The goal is a hydrogen highway between Munich and Modena.
Further stations are planned for Brenner, Nogaredo, Verona, Modena.

An extension northward via Innsbruck (North Tyrol, Austria) to Munich is presently under discussion.

Bolzano is also CHIC project partner and within this project it  operates 5 buses in the area Seiser Alm.

The responsibility for the introduction of hydrogen in South Tyrol lies in the hands of the non-profit and  partly government owned Institute for Innovative Technologies (IIT) in Bolzano, Italy.

Hydrogen Centre Baglan
巴格兰氢气中心

Hydrogen Centre, Baglan Energy Park
巴格兰能源园氢气中心
Goal 目标:
Research and demonstration
研究与示范
Description 描述:
The station is part of the University of Glamorgan’s Renewable Hydrogen Research and Demonstration Centre. There are a H2 refueler and a HCNG Refueler.  The equipment:  A 20kW capacity photovoltaic array is installed on the roof of the Hydrogen Centre.  Electricity from the PV and emulated wind power output are fed to the Hydrogenics alkaline electrolyser, installed by Air Liquide.  This separates deionised water into oxygen and hydrogen at a maximum rate of 10Nm3/hr.  Initially this is compressed to 200bar and then 350bar storage. It is intended to trial a range of hydrogen production and storage mechanisms at the Hydrogen Centre.  Some of the compressed hydrogen will be used as a vehicle fuel. A hydrogen fuel dispenser installed by Air Liquide will enable a range of hydrogen vehicles to refuel with renewable hydrogen from the Hydrogen Centre.   A CNG fuel dispenser and electric vehicle recharging point will allow further alternative fuelled vehicles to operate from the site.  April 2015: upgrade by UK funding    January 2017: Pure Energy Centre (PEC) has been awarded the contract for the supply of a 700 bar hydrogen refueling station. It will consist of a 900 bar hydrogen compressor, high pressure storage system and a 700 hydrogen fuel dispenser. Jan 2019: 70 MPa is still planned as additional HRS Feb 2023: station is not operable, uncertain when it will be restart, out of operation; up-grade is planned, but time schedule uncertain June 2023: bus trial Caetano Bus H2 City Gold; HyQube(mobile)  refueller from Fuel Cell Systems; H2 from the Hyrogen Centre new electrolyser (100 kW) from Protium (40 kg/day)
该站是格拉摩根大学可再生氢研究和示范中心的一部分。这里有一台 H2 加气机和一台 HCNG 加气机。设备：  氢能中心的屋顶上安装了一个 20 千瓦容量的光伏阵列。光伏发电和模拟风力发电输出的电力被输送到液化空气公司安装的 Hydrogenics 碱性电解槽。该装置以每小时 10Nm3 的最大速率将去离子水分离成氧气和氢气。氢气最初被压缩到 200bar 的压力，然后被储存到 350bar 的压力。计划在氢气中心试用一系列氢气生产和储存机制。部分压缩氢将用作汽车燃料。液化空气公司（Air Liquide）安装的氢燃料分配器将使一系列氢能汽车能够从氢能中心获得可再生氢燃料。CNG 燃料加注机和电动汽车充电点将使更多的替代燃料车辆能够在氢能中心运行。2015 年 4 月：由英国资助升级 2017 年 1 月： 纯能源中心（PEC）获得了供应 700 巴加氢站的合同。该加氢站将由一个 900 巴氢压缩机、高压存储系统和一个 700 氢燃料分配器组成。2019 年 1 月：仍计划将 70 兆帕作为额外的 HRS 2023 年 2 月：该站无法运行，不确定何时重新启动，已停止运行；计划进行升级，但时间安排不确定 2023 年 6 月：进行 Caetano Bus H2 City Gold 公交车试验；使用燃料电池系统公司的 HyQube（移动）加注机；使用 Hyrogen 中心的 H2，使用 Protium 公司的新电解槽（100 千瓦）（40 千克/天）。

Description 描述:
March 2008 David E. Langdon, chairman of the Albany County Airport announced the launch of the Airport’s portion of HyIMPACT, a joint hydrogen vehicle test program which will be undertaken by the Albany International Airport and the Capital DistrictTransportation Authority. The demonstration project is funded by the New York State Energy Research and Development Authority (NYSERDA) as part of its Hydrogen Roadmap Program. The Airport will add two hydrogen-powered pickup trucks to its growing fleet of “green” vehicles which currently features compressed natural gas (CNG) powered shuttle buses and pick-up trucks. The project will also include the construction of a hydrogen fueling station that will serve the two Airport vehicles as well as two vehicles being placed into service by the Capital District Transportation Authority. The hydrogen fueling station was installed at the Airport by Air Liquide. No further information is available.   The status of the station is unclear.

Description 描述:
The station includes a Linde MaxFuler 90 dispensing system for fast filling Linde also will supply hydrogen for the adjacent Hythane station.   Linde developed a modular concept for hydrogen fueling that places hydrogen production equipment at a central filling facility instead of at each fueling station, reducing the footprint and cost of individual stations. The hydrogen fuel is liquefied at the central station, then delivered to the retail dispensers and vaporized on demand.   22.11.2011:in development, commission planned for Q1/2012   11.07.2012 SFO will likely stop plans because of liability problems, but is included in the California RoadMap
加氢站包括一套林德 MaxFuler 90 加氢系统，用于快速加氢 林德还将为邻近的 Hythane 加氢站提供氢气。  林德开发了一种模块化氢气加注概念，将氢气生产设备置于中央加注设施，而不是每个加注站，从而减少了单个加注站的占地面积和成本。氢燃料在中央加氢站液化，然后输送到零售加氢站并按需汽化。  22.11.2011:in development, commission planned for Q1/2012 11.07.2012 由于责任问题，SFO 可能会停止该计划，但该计划已被纳入加州路线图。

Description 描述:
old station: GM was the owner and operator of the old station opened in 2008  GM Driveaway project). Air Liquide designed and built the old station.     GM installed the 700bar, fast-fill technology to support on-going needs of the Project Driveway fleet.  The hydrogen station is co-located at a Clean Energy natural gas refuelling station in a retail environment.  The station took approximately six months to design, permit, and construct.   The hydrogen station can fill three vehicles back to back in less than 5 minutes each and can support up to 30 kg/d.     H2 is delivered in tube trailer by Praxair  3 Maximator DLE 75-2 pneumatic booster compressors   pre-cooling to -35°C   Air Liquide dispenser   IrDA TK-17 WEH nozzle   fill rate with chiller 0.75 to 0.9 kg /min    Users have access to the equipment 24/7.  new station:   An upgrade was planned for the middle of 2015.  Commssioning of re-tail station is planned for Q2 2016.   Postponed to Q2 2017, then to late 2018   Air Liquide celebrates completion of the new station in October 2018. CaFCP under commssioning.
老车站 通用汽车公司是 2008 年启用的老加油站（GM Driveaway 项目）的所有者和运营商。液化空气公司设计并建造了旧加气站。    通用汽车安装了700bar的快速充气技术，以满足 "Project Driveaway "车队的持续需求。 氢气加气站与清洁能源公司的天然气加气站设在同一地点。 该加氢站的设计、许可和建造耗时约六个月。  加氢站可在 5 分钟内为 3 辆车进行背靠背加氢，加氢量最高可达 30 公斤/天。    氢气由普莱克斯（Praxair）公司的 3 台 Maximator DLE 75-2 气动增压压缩机在管式拖车中输送，预冷至 -35°C 液化空气公司的加气机 IrDA TK-17 WEH 喷嘴（带冷却器）的填充率为 0.75 至 0.9 公斤/分钟，用户可全天候使用设备：   计划于 2015 年年中进行升级。 计划于 2016 年第二季度投入使用。  后推迟至2017年第二季度，再推迟至2018年底。液化空气公司庆祝新站于2018年10月竣工。CaFCP正在筹备中。

Description 描述:
A hydrogen energy station (HES) that uses a high temperature fuel cell to co-produce electricity and hydrogen will be evaluated and demostrated in a four phase project. First the system will be installed at FuelCell energy ´s facility in Danbury, CT. Then it will be moved to Orange County Sanitation District´s (OCSD´s) sewagetreatment plant in Fountain Valley, CA.   The system will be operated for a minimum of 6 month.  The renewable hydrogen product will be made available to fuel hydrogen vehicles.  For more details see DoE annual progress reports 2007 to 2012  Average usage in April 2013 was about 1.5 vehicles /day    H2 production 100kg/day via high-temperature molten carbonate fuel cell (by FuelCell Energy) from digester gas, compression to 45.5 MPa, pipeline, additional compression with diaphragma compressor to 54 MPa, booster compressor to 80MPa,mechanical chiller for precooling to -40°C, one dispenser with two nozzles 35 and 70 MPa, SAE TIR-J2601 standard    16.01.2013 DoE project ended, operation will continue until May 31, 2014 >br/> open to the public since July 2015  new supply:  CGH2 delivery with 33,% H2 from renewable sources
氢能源站（HES）使用高温燃料电池共同产生电力和氢气，将在一个四期项目中进行评估和演示。首先，该系统将安装在 FuelCell Energy 位于康涅狄格州丹伯里的工厂。然后，该系统将被转移到位于加利福尼亚州喷泉谷的橘郡环卫区（OCSD）污水处理厂。  该系统将运行至少 6 个月。 可再生氢产品将用于氢燃料汽车。 更多详情，请参见能源部 2007 年至 2012 年年度进展报告 2013 年 4 月的平均使用量约为 1.5 辆车/天 通过高温熔融碳酸盐燃料电池（由 FuelCell Energy 生产）从消化器气体中生产 100 公斤/天的氢气，压缩至 45. 5 兆帕，管道，隔膜压缩机额外压缩至 54 兆帕，增压压缩机至 80 兆帕，机械冷却器预冷至 -40°C，一个分配器带两个喷嘴 35 和 70 兆帕，SAE TIR-J2601 标准 2013 年 1 月 16 日 DoE 项目结束，运营将持续至 2014 年 5 月 31 日 >br/> 自 2015 年 7 月起向公众开放新供应：  提供 CGH2，其中 33.% 的 H2 来自可再生能源

It is planned to install a wind turbine in order to produce hydrogen by means of electrolysis  - Hydrogen will either be distributed to vehicles or will be induced into the electrical grid by means of fuel cells or BHKW.    Vattenfall oder Boreal are possible partners to invest in and to operate the wind turbine, the electrical units, and partly the reelectrification system  Air Liquide or Heliocentris are possible partners for the electrolyser   Compressor system to support 700bar  Booster or cascade refuelling    Time frame:   Beginning 2009: Clarifying partners, and project, then planning and integration   2009 – 2010: Installation of wind turbine, completion of construction and start of operation End of 2010
计划安装一台风力涡轮机，以便通过电解产生氢气--氢气将分配给车辆或通过燃料电池或 BHKW 进入电网。   Vattenfall 公司或 Boreal 公司可能是投资和运营风力涡轮机、电力装置以及部分再电气化系统的合作伙伴。 液化空气公司或 Heliocentris 公司可能是电解槽的合作伙伴。 压缩机系统支持 700bar 增压或级联加气：   2009 年初： 明确合作伙伴和项目，然后进行规划和整合 2009 - 2010 年： 安装风力涡轮机，完成施工，开始运行 2010 年底

Description 描述:
The Amsterdam station is located at a bus station in the north of the city owned by the local transport company, Gemeentelijk Vervoer Bedrijf (GVB) and only for CUTE-buses of GVB. No public access possible.   Technology by Linde   Hydrogen is produced at the station by electrolysis (Hydrogenics) using water and ‘green’ electricity produced from renewable energy sources. Each refuelling will dispense approximately 40 kilogrammes of hydrogen in a process taking about 10 minutes. HySTAT-A 120 kg/day 60 Nm³/h   The station worked extremely well,  proved high reliablility and will be deconstructed now. 
阿姆斯特丹站位于城市北部的一个公共汽车站，由当地运输公司 Gemeentelijk Vervoer Bedrijf（GVB）所有，只供 GVB 的 CUTE 公共汽车使用。公众无法进入。  林德技术 利用水和可再生能源产生的 "绿色 "电力，在加氢站通过电解法（氢气技术）生产氢气。每次加氢约需 10 分钟，可提供约 40 公斤氢气。HySTAT-A 120 千克/天 60 牛米³/小时 该加氢站运行非常良好，可靠性很高，现在即将拆除。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:

VehiclesServed 服务车辆: 2 Phileas buses (same as in Cologne)

The station was in operation between December 2003 and January 2008 within the EC project CUTE and HyFLEET:CUTE. Since that time it was in a standby modus (see ID 034). Now it is reopened for the new project.

Description 描述:
The Wind2H2 project uses two wind turbine technologies: a Northern Power Systems 100-kW wind turbine and a Bergey 10-kW wind turbine.   The energy from the 10-kW wind turbine is converted from its wild AC form to direct current (DC) and then used by two HOGEN 40RE polymer electrolyte membrane electrolyzers from Proton OnSite (Connecticut) and one Teledyne HMXT-100 alkaline electrolyzer to produce hydrogen and oxygen from water. After compressing the hydrogen, it is stored for later use where it is used to generate electricity and fed into the utility grid during peak demand hours.
Wind2H2 项目采用两种风力涡轮机技术：Northern Power Systems 公司的 100 千瓦风力涡轮机和 Bergey 公司的 10 千瓦风力涡轮机。  来自 10 千瓦风力涡轮机的能量从野生交流电形式转换为直流电 (DC)，然后由 Proton OnSite（康涅狄格州）公司的两台 HOGEN 40RE 聚合物电解质膜电解槽和 Teledyne HMXT-100 碱性电解槽利用水产生氢气和氧气。压缩后的氢气被储存起来，以便日后用于发电，并在用电高峰时段输入公用电网。

Description 描述:
At the station four H2 FC vehicles can be fueled simutaneously.  Two Gilbarco (PowerTech Labs)dispenser with 2 nozzles each  chiller for precooling to -20°C  Refuelling time less than 8 min.  Two hydraulic compressors (one booster).  Average 150 fills/month, 342 kg/month  The station was built by PowerTech Labs and is maintained by Hydrogenics.   The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class: 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa yes.   The station is a CaFCP non-retail station.  April 2017: upgrade planned for 2018  May 2018: upgraded to a retail station.Now a second 70 MPa dispenser, instead of 35 MPa; 33 % renewable H2, status on-site steam reforming unclear since Feb 2019: station temporarily not available Dec 2020:  out of operation, upgrade is in planning status Sept 2021: restart is planned for Mid 2022
该站可同时为四辆氢燃料电池汽车提供燃料。 两台 Gilbarco（PowerTech Labs）加气机，每台加气机有两个喷嘴，用于预冷至 -20°C 加气时间小于 8 分钟。 两台液压压缩机（一台增压器）。 平均每月加注 150 次，每月加注 342 公斤 该加气站由 PowerTech Labs 公司建造，由 Hydrogenics 公司负责维护。  该加气站由戴姆勒推荐用于 FC B 级： 70 兆帕 是，35 兆帕 是。  该站是 CaFCP 非零售站。 2017 年 4 月：计划于 2018 年升级 2018 年 5 月：升级为零售站。现在有第二个 70 兆帕加气机，而不是 35 兆帕；33 % 的可再生 H2，自 2019 年 2 月起，现场蒸汽重整状况不明 2019 年 2 月：该站暂时不可用 2020 年 12 月：停止运行，升级处于规划状态 2021 年 9 月：计划于 2022 年年中重启

Description 描述:
The station will be CO2 neutral. The stations energy demand will be provided by `green`energy (wind power and solar power). Also other alternative fuels will be offered: biofueles and electricity.    AEL Electrolyser by McPhy 500kW with capacity of 200kg H2/day operated by Enertrag  Ionic compression, storage at various pressure levels and trailer filling plant to take off excess hydrogen are built and operated by Linde  A part of the hydrogen will be filled in trailers to supply other hydrogen refuelling stations in Berlin.   Additional combined heat and power unit built by 2G with ability to run on pure hydrogen, upstream hydrogen buffer storage (metal hydride by McPhy)  The station is ready since 2014 and officially inaugurated, but not in operation, because the airport is not in operation. Meanwhile used for tests. Mid June 2022: the station is in operation with final ajustment and available for public

Description 描述:
The hydrogen station will base its hydrogen production on local, renewable energy. The station will feature on-site production of hydrogen via photovoltaic panels connected to an alkaline electrolyser and a newly developed reformer technology which will make hydrogen out of land fill gas. The station will also feature metal hydride compression, which will draw the compression energy from low-temperature waste heat. Tests of other hydrogen production technologies such as PEM electrolysis are possible in the future. IFE is the project leader. Installation of a A‐70MPa H2Station® from H2Logic A/S. SAE J2601 standard A-Level. June 2013: opening of the innovation zone The Innovation Zone is a part of the station where innovative new hydrogen technologies will be tested and demonstrated, in conjunction with the operation of the station. 2014 new owner and operator (Hyop instead of StatoilHydro).
The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class: 70 MPa yes. Goal 目标:
Provide real hydrogen infrastructure to research and technology community 
为研究和技术界提供真正的氢基础设施
Description 描述:
The Foundation for the Development of New Hydrogen Technologies in Aragon has designed this hydrogen filling station and it is the owner. The Government of Aragon has contribute to the financing.  Basic data:  25 kg/day served, 25 kg/day produced by electrolysis, two pressure levels (350 and 200 bar).  Hydrogen is produced by water electrolysis in an alkaline electrolyzer (Lurgi-IHT technology). The electrolyzer has a discharge pressure of 32 bar which involves an important energy saving in the next stage of hydrogen compression.  The electric consumption is close to 70 kW with a discharge flow of 10 Nm3/h and 99,7% (vol) of purity.  In order to use the hydrogen in a fuel cell, the hydrogen purity is increased in the purification unit (99,999% vol), meanwhile the oxygen is vented to the atmosphere.  The hydrogen store is composed of high pressure stain steel cylinders in a steel bank. In the first stage of operation, the high pressure hydrogen storage will be close to 25 Kg. The cascade is formed by 18 cylinders with 6 bottles for each stage.    Dispenser: The FTI International dispenser is able to fill buses and cars at 350 or 200 bar with a touch screen interface to select the fill pressure and visualize operation parameters.     There is one dispenser which is provided with two WEH TK 16 y TK 25 nozzles.  There is NO precooling NEITHER communications interface with the vehicle.  The filling rate depends highly on the ambient temperature. Hereby, if the ambient temperature is higher than 30ºC, the dispenser supplies hydrogen with a low filling rate in order to keep the temperature inside the vehicle tank below 85ºC. This filling rate could vary between 0.2 and 0.6 Kg/min.    The station is controlled by a master PLC which oversees the installation for a safe operation and will be also used to record and send all the important operation parameters such as pressures, temperatures, flows, time of fillings or electric consumptions so that these results can be analyzed in order to optimize the installation and to improve future designs of hydrogen stations.  Jan 2022: plans for upgrade to 70 MPa
阿拉贡氢能新技术开发基金会设计了这座加氢站，它也是这座加氢站的所有者。阿拉贡政府提供了资金。基本数据  日供氢量 25 千克，日电解氢量 25 千克，两级压力（350 巴和 200 巴）。氢气通过碱性电解槽（Lurgi-IHT 技术）中的水电解产生。电解槽的放电压力为 32 巴，这为下一阶段的氢气压缩节省了大量能源。耗电量接近 70 千瓦，排出流量为 10 Nm3/h，纯度为 99.7%。为了在燃料电池中使用氢气，氢气纯度在净化装置中得到提高（99.999% vol），同时氧气被排放到大气中。氢气储存器由钢组中的高压不锈钢气瓶组成。在运行的第一阶段，高压储氢接近 25 公斤。级联由 18 个钢瓶组成，每级 6 瓶。加气机：快三计划国际加气机可在 350 或 200 巴的压力下为巴士和汽车加气，并配有触摸屏界面，用于选择加气压力和可视化操作参数。一台加气机配有两个 WEH TK 16 y TK 25 喷嘴。没有预冷装置，也没有与车辆的通信接口。加注速度在很大程度上取决于环境温度。因此，如果环境温度高于 30ºC，氢气加注器就会以较低的加注速度供应氢气，以便将车辆油箱内的温度控制在 85ºC 以下。加氢速度在 0.2 至 0.6 公斤/分钟之间。该加氢站由一个主 PLC 控制，该 PLC 负责监督加氢站的安全运行，并记录和发送所有重要的运行参数，如压力、温度、流量、加氢时间或耗电量，以便对这些结果进行分析，从而优化加氢站的安装，并改进未来加氢站的设计。2022 年 1 月：计划升级至 70 兆帕。

Hydrogen Plant with  option on a hydrogen filling station
氢气厂，可选择加氢站
Goal 目标:
to gain experiences with production, distribution and use of hydrogen as energy carrier for increasing the renewable energy share in the energy production from Nukissiorfiit.
获得生产、分配和使用氢气作为能源载体的经验，以提高可再生能源在努基西奥菲特能源生产中的比例。
Description 描述:
H2 Logic A/S from Denmark has developed and delivered the hydrogen plant which is owned and operated by the national energy company Nukissiorfiit. The test plant produces hydrogen by electrolysis. The hydrogen is stored for later conversion into electricity and heat in a fuel cell. The excess heat from the hydrogen production and the fuel cell can be used for heating, while the electricity can be supplied to grid. The plant also includes a compression and distribution system that enables storing of the hydrogen under pressure in distributable bulks. The plant is also prepared for a future upgrade with a hydrogen refueling station.
丹麦的 H2 Logic A/S 公司开发并交付了这套制氢装置，该装置由国家能源公司 Nukissiorfiit 拥有和运营。试验工厂通过电解产生氢气。氢气被储存起来，随后在燃料电池中转化为电能和热能。制氢和燃料电池产生的多余热量可用于供暖，而电力则可供应电网。该工厂还包括一个压缩和分配系统，可将氢气在压力下储存成可分配的散装氢气。该工厂还为将来升级加氢站做好了准备。

Description 描述:
Fast fill CGH 700 bar according to SAE J2601,   Slow fill CGH 350 bar according to California Fuel-Cell Partnership protocol 30 bar pressure electrolyser (Hogen by Proton Energy Systems), mechanical compressor, puffer storage with two pressure levels    This filling station demonstrates the full hydrogen energy chain consisting of electricity generation (photovoltaics), hydrogen production by PEM-electrolysis (30 bar), compression, storage and fuelling. v   Access:   700 bar fueling is accessed with the Clean Energy Partnership (CEP-)Card. For 350 bar fueling please contact station operator in advance.  The station is recommended by Daimler for FC B-class 70 MPa yes, 35 MPa yes. The station is accepted by major car companies.
快速充气 CGH 700 巴，符合 SAE J2601 标准；慢速充气 CGH 350 巴，符合加利福尼亚燃料电池合作协议 30 巴压力电解槽（质子能源系统公司的 Hogen）、机械压缩机、具有两个压力等级的膨化器存储装置 该加气站展示了由发电（光伏）、PEM 电解制氢（30 巴）、压缩、存储和加气组成的完整氢能源链：   使用清洁能源合作卡 (CEP-)700 bar 加氢。如需加注 350 巴燃料，请提前联系加油站运营商。 该加油站是戴姆勒推荐的 FC B 级加油站，压力为 70 兆帕，35 兆帕。主要汽车公司均可使用该加油站。

Description 描述:
old station in the backyard nearby: December 2012: A consortium of the project "Don Quichote" will develop a new H2 prodution system which will enlarge the H2 production capacity to demonstrate an integrated hydrogen storage system of renewable energy linked to an hydrogen refueling station.   Don Quichote = Demonstration of new qualitative innovative concept of hydrogen out of wind turbine electricity.   The station is built for forklifts and is in operation for forklifts 24h/7 days.   Hydrogenics HySTAT 30 Nm³/h electrolyser, capable to produce up to 65 kg H2 per day, compressor, high pressure cascade storage,-20° chiller   SAEJ 2601    WaterstofNet is the owner and operator of the station. Colruyt is the land owner.  The station corresponds to der ISO 14687-2:2012 Norm and is accepted by Daimler.  November 2015: The station is expanded with a PEM electrolyser (30 Nm³/h) additionally to the existing alkaline electrolyser.  Up to now the existing station has technical availability of more than 95%.  March 2016: Inauguration of the new electrolyser, a 100 kW fuel cell and storage system.  2017 Several changes have been made: Colruyt is the new operator, because of the high number of forklifts and the availability conditions. Upgrade with an additional compressor (60 Nm³). The old electrolysis is upgraded in capacity (60 Nm³/h). Two additional  indoor dispensers for 75 forklifts. Some hundred meters away a new outdoor dispenser with public access for 70 MPa (to start in May 2018)   is installed in the DATS 24 station nearby.  Hydrogen from electrolysis is delivered with a short pipeline to this new station. One the map the flag is located for the new public station with 70 MPa. The old private station is some hundred meters in the backyard of the Colruyt distribution center. The 35 MPa dispenser will be tested for a heavy duty truck in 2019.   June 2018: 70 MPa public dispenser is in test operation   08.10.2018 opening of the 70 MPa public dispenser.
附近后院的旧车站： 2012 年 12 月： Don Quichote "项目的一个联合体将开发一个新的氢气生产系统，该系统将扩大氢气生产能力，以展示与加氢站相连的可再生能源综合储氢系统。Don Quichote = 演示利用风力涡轮机发电制氢的新质创新概念。加氢站专为叉车而建，全天候为叉车提供服务。Hydrogenics HySTAT 30 Nm³/h 电解槽，每天可生产高达 65 公斤的氢气，压缩机，高压级联存储，-20° 冷却器 SAEJ 2601 WaterstofNet 是该站的所有者和运营商。Colruyt 是土地所有者。该站符合 der ISO 14687-2:2012 标准，并获得了戴姆勒公司的认可。2015 年 11 月： 在现有碱性电解槽的基础上，又增加了一个 PEM 电解槽（30 Nm³/h）。截至目前，现有电解槽的技术可用率超过 95%。2016 年 3 月： 新电解槽（100 千瓦燃料电池和存储系统）投入使用。2017 年 发生了一些变化： 由于叉车数量多和可用性条件，Colruyt 成为新的运营商。升级增加了一台压缩机（60 Nm³）。旧电解能力升级（60 Nm³/h）。为 75 辆叉车增加两台室内加油机。约 100 米外，附近的 DATS 24 站安装了一个新的室外配药机，可向公众提供 70 兆帕的配药服务（将于 2018 年 5 月启动）。电解产生的氢气通过一条短管道输送到这个新的加氢站。在地图上，新的 70 兆帕公共加氢站的旗帜就插在这里。旧的私人站位于 Colruyt 配送中心后院约 100 米处。35 兆帕加气机将于 2019 年进行重型卡车测试。2018 年 6 月：70 兆帕公共加油机投入试运行 08. 10. 2018 年启用 70 兆帕公共加油机。

Support hydrogen vehicle R&D and initial S Wales H2 refuelling infrastructure
支持氢能汽车研发和威尔士 H2 加气基础设施的初期建设
Description 描述:
AP  Series 100 equipment.   It is the second station of the University Glamorgan. Hydrogen is taken from the hydrogen facility in Port Talbot.   A 350bar compressed hydrogen refuelling station to support the university’s R&D and deployment goals for hydrogen vehicles and to encourage uptake of hydrogen vehicles. The University’s second hydrogen refueller to complement the facility at Baglan (40km  away).   Feb 2016: currently out of operation, awaiting maintenance and recertification
AP 系列 100 设备。  这是格拉摩根大学的第二个氢气站。氢气取自塔尔博特港的氢气设施。  这是一个 350bar 的压缩氢加气站，用于支持大学氢能汽车的研发和部署目标，并鼓励氢能汽车的使用。大学的第二台氢气加注机，以补充巴格兰（40 公里外）的设施。  2016 年 2 月：目前停止运行，等待维护和重新认证
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
produced by electrolysis with solar power at the station in Port Talbot University’s Hydrogen Centre at Baglan
在位于巴格兰的塔尔博特港大学氢气中心的电解站利用太阳能生产氢气
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
Initially the University’s own vehicles, but aiming to support development of vehicles for and by a range of organisations
最初是大学自己的车辆，但目的是支持为各种组织开发车辆和由各种组织开发车辆

Comments 评论:
The project has been part-funded by the University, the Department for Transport Alternative Fuels Infrastructure Grant (AFIGP) Programme and the European Regional Development Fund through the Welsh Assembly Government (ERDF funded CymruH2Wales project).
The station is part of the ongoing hydrogen and fuel cell R&D at the University of Glamorgan and part of the Welsh Government’s Low Carbon Economic Area initiative, focused on hydrogen energy development.
该项目由格拉摩根大学、交通部替代燃料基础设施补助金计划 (AFIGP) 和欧洲区域发展基金（通过威尔士议会政府由欧洲区域发展基金资助的 CymruH2Wales 项目）提供部分资金。
该站是格拉摩根大学正在进行的氢能和燃料电池研发工作的一部分，也是威尔士政府低碳经济区倡议的一部分，重点关注氢能开发。

Description 描述:
Honda teamed up with ANA (All Nippon Airways) at the request of HySUT (The Research Association of Hydrogen Supply/Utilization Technology) to offer the FCX Clarity fuel cell vehicle as a limo service to passengers on international flights at Tokyo’s Narita International Airport from 5 September 2011.  The old station for experimental research provided refueling at 35 MPa and started operation in 2011. Went out of operation in September 2015.  The new public and commercial station provides refueling at 70 MPa for the initial sale price of 1,100 yen/kg (not including consumption tax).  Station with pre-cooling equipment
应 HySUT（氢供应/利用技术研究协会）的要求，本田与全日空（ANA）合作，自 2011 年 9 月 5 日起在东京成田国际机场为国际航班乘客提供 FCX Clarity 燃料电池汽车的豪华轿车服务。 旧的实验研究站提供 35 兆帕的加氢，于 2011 年开始运行。2015 年 9 月停止运营。 新的公共和商业加油站以 70 兆帕的压力加油，初始售价为 1,100 日元/公斤（不含消费税）。 配备预冷设备的加油站

Goal 目标:
Reduce the cost of hydrogen supply by making use of existing hydrogen production and distribution mechanisms and eventually Scotland’s extensive wind energy resources
利用现有的氢气生产和分配机制，最终利用苏格兰丰富的风能资源，降低氢气供应成本
Description 描述:
Aberdeen city councillors have agreed to support the European project. 11.04.2012: the EU FCH Bus fleet project was launched on Marche 24 Government funds the demonstration of a whole renewable hydrogen system, connecting a 1 MW electrolyser to the grid , in conjunction with a wind farm located in Aberdeen Shire, to explore the grid impacts and energy storage potential of hydrogen production and to provide the "green" hydrogen to the planned fleet of H2 FC buses. 10 hydrogen fc buses will be ordered. Bus and station operation should start by early 2014. 10.10.2012 BOC Linde wil provide the refueling technology and own and operate the station. Linde´s IC-90 ionic compressor. Dec. 2013: 2 x Tokheim fast flow dispensers (120 gms/sec) Facility is currently designed to service ten fuel cell buses only, but compressors are rated to 900b for the potential filling of 700b passenger cars in the future. Additional investment will be required however in a 700b dispenser, 700b storage tubes and payment architecture before being made available to the general public. Goal: - To validate the techno-economic case for fuel cell buses in inter-city duty cycles - To better understand the operational costs associated with an integrated production and refuelling facility of this type - To understand the role electrolysers can play in supporting a high daily demand of hydrogen and as an energy storage and grid balancing medium Feb 2014: Hydrogenics will provide 3 HySTAT 60 electrolyser for the production up to 400 H2 kg/day March 2014: the first four buses were delivered Dec 2014: Hydrogenics will supply the 700 bar hydrogen station
April 2016: After one year of operation the station´s availability is 99,99%. technical specifications: electrolyser: 3 HySTAT 60 with max. 5.1 kg/h each compressor: 2 IC 90 max pressure rate 30 kg/hr each Linde (or IC 60 ?) buffer storage 374 kg at max 50 MPa card reader: TokheimSlimDiaLOG RFID Dispenser: Tokheim fast flow, nozzle WEH TK 16 fast flow 2017: Aberdeen City Council wants to expand its fleet with 10 additional buses Nov 2018: opening of the upgrade to public station, now refueling of buses, vans and trucks is possible with 35 MPa and 70 MPa for cars Feb 2022: UK’s first hydrogen fuel cell waste truck will start in Aberdeen in March March 2022: Aberdeen City Council and bp have signed an agreement to form a joint venture partnership that will deliver a scalable green hydrogen production, storage and distribution facility in the city powered by renewable energy. March 2023: Aberdeen Hydrogen Hub reaches planning milestone. The current project ambition is to have the facility producing hydrogen by the end of 2024. 阿伯丁市议员已同意支持该欧洲项目。11. 2012 年 4 月：欧盟氢燃料电池公交车队项目于马尔凯 24 日启动，政府资助了整个可再生氢气系统的示范项目，将 1 兆瓦的电解槽与位于阿伯丁郡的风力发电厂连接到电网，以探索氢气生产对电网的影响和储能潜力，并为计划中的氢燃料电池公交车队提供 "绿色 "氢气。将订购 10 辆氢 FC 巴士。巴士和车站将于 2014 年初开始运行。10. 10. 2012 中银林德将提供加氢技术，并拥有和运营加氢站。林德的 IC-90 离子压缩机。2013 年 12 月：2 台托克海姆快速加气机（120 克/秒） 设施目前的设计仅能为 10 辆燃料电池巴士提供服务，但压缩机的额定能 力为 900b ，未来可能为 700b 的乘用车加气。不过，在向公众开放之前，还需要在 700b 加注机、700b 储存管和支付结构方面进行额外投资。Goal: - To validate the techno-economic case for fuel cell buses in inter-city duty cycles - To better understand the operational costs associated with an integrated production and refuelling facility of this type - To understand the role electrolysers can play in supporting a high daily demand of hydrogen and as an energy storage and grid balancing medium Feb 2014: Hydrogenics will provide 3 HySTAT 60 electrolyser for the production up to 400 H2 kg/day March 2014: the first four buses were delivered Dec 2014: Hydrogenics will supply the 700 bar hydrogen station
April 2016: After one year of operation the station´s availability is 99,99%. technical specifications: electrolyser: 3 HySTAT 60 with max. 5. 1 kg/h each compressor: 2 IC 90 max pressure rate 30 kg/hr each Linde (or IC 60 ?) buffer storage 374 kg at max 50 MPa card reader: TokheimSlimDiaLOG RFID Dispenser: Tokheim fast flow, nozzle WEH TK 16 fast flow 2017: Aberdeen City Council wants to expand its fleet with 10 additional buses Nov 2018: opening of the upgrade to public station, now refueling of buses, vans and trucks is possible with 35 MPa and 70 MPa for cars Feb 2022: UK’s first hydrogen fuel cell waste truck will start in Aberdeen in March March 2022: Aberdeen City Council and bp have signed an agreement to form a joint venture partnership that will deliver a scalable green hydrogen production, storage and distribution facility in the city powered by renewable energy. 2023 年 3 月 阿伯丁氢气枢纽达到规划里程碑。目前该项目的目标是在 2024 年底之前让该设施生产出氢气。

Comments 评论:
Part of the European hydrogen project Hyer High V.LO City which joins the three regions Flanders V, Liguria L, Scotland O  and of HyTransit and HyTrEC.
The HyTransit Aberdeen Bus Project will be Europe’s largest demonstration of electrolytic hydrogen production and fuel cell bus operation. It is hoped that this project will be the catalyst for a roll out of this technology to other regions across Scotland and beyond.
Further refueling stations are proposed to be built across the city as the project develops further.
阿伯丁是欧洲氢能项目 Hyer High V.LO City 的一部分，该项目由佛兰德斯 V、利古里亚 L、苏格兰 O 三个地区以及 HyTransit 和 HyTrEC 组成。
HyTransit 阿伯丁巴士项目将是欧洲最大的电解制氢和燃料电池巴士运营示范项目。希望该项目能成为向苏格兰及其他地区推广该技术的催化剂。
随着项目的进一步发展，建议在全市范围内建设更多的加气站。

Description 描述:
The ferry will carry up to 12 passengers per journey. It is being built by Bristol Hydrogen Boats - a consortium formed between No 7 Boat Trips, the Bristol Packet, and Auriga Energy Ltd. Air Products will provide the hydrogen fuel and the refuelling infrastructure to the demonstration project. The council is supporting its development with an investment of £225,000. The ferry "Hydrogenesis" was tested in August 2012, public service started in February 2013 and will continue until end of August 2013. Then the filling station will be decommissioned.
渡轮每次最多可搭载 12 名乘客。它由布里斯托尔氢能船公司建造，该公司是由 No 7 Boat Trips、布里斯托尔包船公司和 Auriga Energy Ltd.组成的联合体。空气产品公司将为该示范项目提供氢燃料和加气基础设施。议会将投资 22.5 万英镑支持该项目的开发。渡轮 "Hydrogenesis "于 2012 年 8 月进行测试，2013 年 2 月开始提供公共服务，并将持续到 2013 年 8 月底。之后，加气站将退役。

StationName 站名:
High VLO City station at Solvay 
位于索尔维的 VLO 城市站
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Street1 街道1:
BLD J501 HAVEN 725 -SCHELDELAAN 600
BLD J501 HAVEN 725 -SCHELDELAAN 600
Street2 街道 2:
at Solvay Chimie NV  c/o BASF Antwerpen
在 Solvay Chimie NV c/o BASF Antwerpen
Goal 目标:
Reduce the cost of hydrogen supply by using by-product hydrogen from industry
利用工业副产品氢气，降低氢气供应成本
Description 描述:
Dec. 2015 plans to remove the station from Solvay towards the depot of DeLijn.   1.1.2017 PitPoint takes over the station.  The hydrogen is delivered by Air Liquide via pipeline  100 bar.The hydrogen is an by-product from chlorine production (electrolysis). 1 compressor (400 kg/day), 1 fast flow dispenser  Jan 2018: Plans to move the station from the port of Antwerp to De Lijins´s bus depot still exist for 2018 to make the fleet more efficient. Dec 2019 project ended Dec 2019, station remains -for the moment - in operation July 2020: stations and buses are probably out of operation During the project it became more and more clear that the location of the HRS, not being on the  depot(>20kms),  became  a  bottleneck  for  a  good  service  and  operation  of  the  different  lines,  operated  with  the  5  FCBs.  This  non-bus  related  issues  as  well  as  the  structural  shortage  of qualified drivers were affecting the ambitions and goals of the site. Affecting the daily mileage and even the buses going into service in the morning, showing lower percentages of usage.  Nevertheless  DeLijn  operated  the  buses  on  a  regular  basis  resulting  in  almost  300.000kms driven in service.  The  relocation  of  the  HRS  will  take place after the projects’ closure.  Operation of the buses and the station  unfortunately  suffered  from  this.   Although  it  also  has  to  be  said,  that the station performed well and  showed  also  a  very  high  availability and reliability for fueling the buses. 
2015 年 12 月 计划将车站从索尔维迁往 DeLijn 车库。2017 年 1 月 1 日，PitPoint 接管了该站。氢气由液化空气公司通过 100 巴管道输送。氢气是氯生产（电解）的副产品。1 台压缩机（400 公斤/天），1 台快速流量分配器 2018 年 1 月： 2018 年仍计划将该站从安特卫普港移至 De Lijins 的公交车站，以提高车队效率。2019 年 12 月 项目结束，车站暂时仍在运营 2020 年 7 月：车站和公交车可能停止运营 在项目实施期间，越来越明显的是，HRS 的位置不在公交车站（>20 公里），这成为了由 5 辆 FCB 运营的不同线路的良好服务和运营的瓶颈。这些与公共汽车无关的问题以及合格司机的结构性短缺影响了该站点的雄心和目标。这影响了每天的行驶里程，甚至影响了早上投入运营的公交车的使用率。尽管如此，DeLijn 仍定期运营巴士，使巴士行驶了近 300. 000公里。HRS 将在项目结束后搬迁。遗憾的是，巴士和车站的运营因此受到影响。尽管如此，该加油站还是表现出色，为公共汽车加油的可用性和可靠性也非常高。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:

工业副产品氢气；200 千克/天

Comments 评论:
The station is part of the EU funded project High V.LO City which joins the regions Flandern, Liguria (Imperia) and Scotland (Aberdeen).
The High V.LO City project, coordinated by the bus manufacturer Van Hool, started in 2012 and will run until the 
end of 2019. 
 The station will likely be  used for the 3Emotion project, too (www.3emotion.eu).
该车站是欧盟资助的 "High V.LO City "项目的一部分，该项目联合了弗兰德恩（Flandern）、利古里亚（Imperia）和苏格兰（阿伯丁）地区。
High V.LO City 项目由巴士制造商 Van Hool 负责协调，于 2012 年启动，将持续到 2019 年底。
2019年底。
 该站还将用于 3Emotion 项目 (www.3emotion.eu)。

StationName 站名:
WaterstofNet Station Helmond
赫尔蒙德水网站
Status 状态:
Out of Operation
停止运行
Street2 街道 2:
Automotiv Campus Helmond
赫尔蒙德自动化校园
Description 描述:
Hydrogenics HySTAT 30 Nm³/h electrolyser, capable to produce up to 65 kg H2 per day, compressor (Idro Mechanicca), high pressure cascade storage, -40° chiller  SAEJ 2601, SAEJ2799  The station corresponds to der ISO 14687-2:2012 Norm and is accepted by Daimler.   January 2016: Two Toyoto Mirai of the Ministry will be refueled at this station.  October 2016: The storage system for 35 MPa was extended from 100kg to 250 kg H2 to enable refuellling of two editional busses. Busses and passenger cars 35 MPa are refueled at the same nozzle ("normal flow"). There are two dispenders (35 and 70 MPa) now.  January 2017: Plans to upgrade the electrolyserto 60 Nm²/h and the storage for 70MPa refueling in Q3/4 2017  February 2019: upgrade and expansion are nearly finalised. More capacity is necessary because of the increasing demand.  April 2019: garbage trucks were officially inaugurated October 2021: closed, will be relocated  n Veldhoven
Hydrogenics HySTAT 30 Nm³/h 电解槽，每天最多可生产 65 千克 H2，压缩机（Idro Mechanicca），高压级联存储，-40° 冷却器 SAEJ 2601, SAEJ2799 该电站符合 der ISO 14687-2:2012 标准，并被戴姆勒认可。  2016 年 1 月： 国防部的两辆丰田 Mirai 将在该加油站加油。 2016 年 10 月： 35 MPa 的储存系统从 100 千克 H2 扩展到 250 千克 H2，以便为两辆普通客车加气。巴士和 35 兆帕客车在同一个喷嘴（"正常流量"）加气。现在有两台加气机（35 兆帕和 70 兆帕）。 2017 年 1 月： 计划在 2017 年第 3/4 季度升级 60 Nm²/h 的电解槽和 70MPa 加气的储气罐 2019 年 2 月：升级和扩建工作已接近尾声。由于需求不断增长，必须增加容量。 2019 年 4 月：垃圾车正式投入使用 2021 年 10 月：关闭，将搬迁至费尔德霍芬

StationName 站名:
Honda Solar Hydrogen Station
本田太阳能氢气站
Street2 街道 2:
at Honda R&D Center Wako
本田和光研发中心
State 州/省:
Saitama prefecture, Kanto Area
埼玉县，关东地区
Description 描述:
This is the first installation in Japan of a total system to produce, store and dispense hydrogen with ZERO CO2 emissions. A high pressure water electrolysis system, uniquely developed by Honda, produces hydrogen.  With no mechanical compressor, the system is nearly silent and highly energy efficient. Using Solar and grid power, the system is capable of producing 1.5kg of hydrogen within 24 hours which enables an FCX Clarity to run approximately 150km or 90 miles. Honda aims to further develop the system to offer clean energy sources for the home in the future. Honda Solar Hydrogen Station SHS has been developed since 2001. First demonstration in Los Angeles USA in 2010. Further development with demonstration testing 2012 Saitama Prefectural Office grounds, 2014 with Iwantani at Saitama City and Kitakyushu City. Currently (2016) at Honda´s Wako headquarter.
这是日本首次安装二氧化碳零排放的氢气生产、储存和分配全套系统。本田公司独特开发的高压水电解系统生产氢气。 由于没有机械压缩机，该系统几乎没有噪音，而且非常节能。利用太阳能和电网供电，该系统能够在 24 小时内产生 1.5 千克氢气，使 FCX Clarity 能够行驶约 150 公里或 90 英里。本田的目标是进一步开发该系统，将来为家庭提供清洁能源。本田太阳能氢气站 SHS 自 2001 年开始研发。2010 年在美国洛杉矶进行了首次示范。进一步发展，2012 年在埼玉县办公室场地进行了示范测试，2014 年与岩谷公司在埼玉市和北九州市进行了示范测试。目前（2016 年）在本田和光总部进行。

Goal 目标:
To fuel 5 FC Buses/day at 350 bar@15°C, each with 40 kg Hydrogen
每天为 5 辆 FC 巴士提供 350 bar@15°C 的燃料，每辆巴士 40 千克氢气
Description 描述:
Riviera Trasporti is expected to substitute already Zero emission vehicles (trolleybus) with potentially more effective zero emission vehicles (FCB), due to the old infrastructures of the trolleybus and the high costs of its maintenance.   First project plan: The hydrogen is produced on site by electrolyses (Hydrogenics). The minor required part of hydrogen is delivered by tube trailers (40%), both managed by Air Liquide Italia.   One dispenser only is planed provided by Hydrogenics.The HRS manufacturer is Air Liquide Italia.    December 2013: 5 buses have arrived. They will start testing phase in  February 2014. A mobile refueling station displayed in the bus depot will be used until the station will be ready.  Nov. 2015: Because of problems with co-funding there will be only 3 buses in operation and station construction is delayed. Two busses will go to a forth HighVLO City project station (Groningen). Start of operation is planned for the middle of 2016.  May 2017: Buses are not in operation but to start running in the second half of 2017. Station is under construction. To start in some weeks. January 2018: station should start in the first weeks of 2018, regular service of the 3 buses will start in spring 2018 after test phase. Jan 2020: Project High V-#.L.O. ended, station and buses remain in operation June 2021: final report: The Site Acceptance Test was finished in 25-10-2018 and the station went in operation in the first  days  of  December  of  2018.  Initially,  it  was  initially  also  designed  with  its  own  on-site production of hydrogen by electrolyses, producing and storing the hydrogen. For economical reason, the project was reduced and the electrolyser was cancelled.  - Trucked-in  hydrogen  via  tube-trailer  (200bar)  - 2x Hofer membrane compressor  (220kgs/day to 450 bar)  - 160 kg onsite storage @400 bar  - 1 fast flow dispenser  Total  amount  of refuellings 141 Total  amount  of hydrogen refuelled 5596 kg Average refuelled quantity 39.68 kg Overall availability 92%
由于无轨电车基础设施陈旧，维护费用高昂，预计 Riviera Trasporti 公司将用可能更有效的零排放车辆（FCB）取代已经是零排放的车辆（无轨电车）。第一个项目计划： 通过电解（Hydrogenics）在现场生产氢气。所需氢气的一小部分由管式拖车运送（40%），均由液化空气意大利公司管理。计划由 Hydrogenics 提供一台分配器。HRS 生产商为液化空气意大利公司。2013 年 12 月： 5 辆巴士已抵达。它们将于 2014 年 2 月开始测试阶段。在加气站准备就绪之前，将使用展示在公交车站内的移动加气站。2015 年 11 月： 由于共同筹资问题，只有 3 辆巴士投入运营，车站建设也被推迟。两辆公交车将开往第四个 HighVLO 城市项目站点（格罗宁根）。计划于 2016 年年中开始运营。2017 年 5 月： 公交车尚未投入运营，但将于 2017 年下半年开始运行。车站正在建设中。几周后开工。2018 年 1 月：车站应在 2018 年的前几周启动，3 辆公交车的常规服务将在测试阶段后于 2018 年春季开始。2020 年 1 月： High V-#. 2021 年 6 月：最终报告： 现场验收测试于 2018 年 10 月 25 日完成，车站于 2018 年 12 月初投入运营。最初的设计还包括现场电解制氢、生产和储存氢气。由于经济原因，项目被缩减，电解槽被取消。- 通过管式拖车运入氢气（200 巴） - 2x Hofer 膜压缩机（220 千克/天，450 巴） - 160 千克现场储存（400 巴） - 1 台快速加气机 加气总量 141 加氢总量 5596 千克 平均加气量 39. 68 kg 整体可用率 92%。

Description 描述:
Refueling of 5 kg H2 in 3 minutes is possible.   The Kaminokura facility creates hydrogen using LP gas as the fuel, and with a five stage reciprocal compressor (100 Nm3 an hour) increases the pressure to 82MPa and then fills a new type CFRP accumulator employing new standards. It fills the FCV with hydrogen by means of the difference in pressure.   The station is also a pertol station without boundaries between the hydrogen and gasoline equipment.
可在 3 分钟内补充 5 千克 H2。  上仓设施使用液化石油气作为燃料制造氢气，并使用五级往复式压缩机（每小时 100 Nm3）将压力提高到 82MPa，然后填充采用新标准的新型 CFRP 蓄能器。它利用压力差向 FCV 注入氢气。  该加氢站也是一个氢气和汽油设备之间没有界限的加氢站。

Description 描述:
The station is constructed for bus refueling: 30kg/ 15 min, two buses back-to-back refueling is possible.   From September 2013 onwards 70 MPa refueling will be possibel, but without pre-cooling (no SAE standard).  But upgrade to SAE standard is planned for the end of 2015.   The station is located at Büchenauer street, but the entrance of the campus is at Helmholtz Platz 1. The campus is private area, but public access is possible after appointment. Access with Cleanenergy partnership CEP refueling card will be easier soon.   Refueling of Daimler FC vehicles is possible.
该加油站专为巴士加油而建： 30 公斤/15 分钟，可为两辆巴士背靠背加油。  从 2013 年 9 月起，可进行 70 兆帕的加油，但不带预冷装置（不符合 SAE 标准）。 但计划在 2015 年底升级到 SAE 标准。  加油站位于 Büchenauer 大街，但园区入口位于 Helmholtz Platz 1。 园区为私人区域，但公众可在预约后进入。不久后，使用清洁能源合作伙伴 CEP 加油卡将更加方便。  可为戴姆勒 FC 车辆加油。

Description 描述:
The hydrogen filling station is supplied by green electricity, through PV panels on the roof of Belenos Clean Power Holding.  Although there is no public access, refueling is possible upon request: please contact the station operator.   The filling station is operated by Swiss Hydrogen Power. It was supplied as an integrated system by Diamond Lite.  On-site PEM electrolyser from Proton-on-Site (Hogen S producing 1 Nm3/h H2 at 14 bar and 0.5 Nm3/h O2 at ambient pressure).   Dispensers: Stäubli quick-connect fittings (O2), Weh TK16 (H2)   The station is Swiss TS reviewed, CE conform/CE marked.
加氢站由贝莱诺斯清洁能源控股公司屋顶的光伏板提供绿色电力。 虽然加氢站不对公众开放，但可以根据要求进行加氢：请联系加氢站运营商。  加气站由瑞士氢能源公司运营。它是由 Diamond Lite 公司提供的集成系统。 现场 PEM 电解槽由 Proton-Site 提供（Hogen S 在 14 巴压力下每小时产生 1 Nm3 H2，在环境压力下每小时产生 0.5 Nm3 O2）。  分配器： 该站通过了瑞士 TS 审查，符合 CE 标准/CE 标志。

StationName 站名:
Costa Rica Hydrogen Transportation Ecosystem
哥斯达黎加氢能运输生态系统
Street1 街道1: 10 km Wesr, Burger KIng Finca La Flor
Goal 目标:
Used for experimental purposes only. The goal is to initiate hydrogen technology development in Costa Rica and the region
仅用于实验目的。目标是在哥斯达黎加和该地区启动氢能技术开发
Description 描述:
This plant is the result of an ongoing partnership between private aerospace company, Ad Astra Rocket and the state-owned oil refinery RECOPE with the purpose of reducing the dependency on imported fossil fuels for transportation in Costa Rica. The production and high pressure storage facility was commissioned in December 2013, and the plan for expansion including an H2 dispenser and a hybrid BEV/FCEV mobile application are under way for completion in early 2015.   Jan 2017: Currently the dispenser is on-site and undergoing integration with the hydrogen production and storage facilities. The integration should be complete by the end of March this year and should begin operations immediately on April.The bus is scheduled to arrive late February. 2021 July: 70 MPa refuelling is possible 2022 June: public access is possible now The Costa Rica Hydrogen Transportation Ecosystem is Latin America's first 100% carbon-free electric transportation pilot project based on green hydrogen, led by Ad Astra Rocket Company and an alliance of public- and private-sector entities. It has both H35 and H70 dispensing capabilities, and currently serves a fleet of 1 FCEB and 4 FCEV's operating within the local tourism industry. A major upgrade is planned for early 2024 for the project's green hydrogen production capability, including an expansion of the current fleet of hydrogen vehicles.
该工厂是私营航空航天公司 Ad Astra Rocket 与国有炼油厂 RECOPE 持续合作的成果，旨在减少哥斯达黎加交通对进口化石燃料的依赖。生产和高压储存设施已于 2013 年 12 月投入使用，包括 H2 加注机和混合动力 BEV/FCEV 移动应用在内的扩建计划正在进行中，预计将于 2015 年初完成。  2017 年 1 月： 目前，加注机正在现场与氢气生产和储存设施进行整合。整合工作应于今年 3 月底完成，并应立即于 4 月开始运行。巴士计划于 2 月下旬抵达。2021 年 7 月： 哥斯达黎加氢能交通生态系统是拉丁美洲首个基于绿色氢能的 100% 无碳电动交通试点项目，由 Ad Astra 火箭公司和公共及私营部门实体联盟领导。该系统具有 H35 和 H70 配氢能力，目前为当地旅游业的 1 辆 FCEB 和 4 辆 FCEV 提供服务。计划在 2024 年初对该项目的绿色氢气生产能力进行重大升级，包括扩大现有的氢气车队。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site with renewable energy (solar power and wind power)
现场使用可再生能源（太阳能和风能）
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
buffer tank: 4 m³ 1, MPa, high pressure vessels: 5 units, 1 kg at 70MPa
缓冲罐： 4 立方米，1 兆帕；高压容器：5 个，1 千克，70 兆帕
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
FC bus delivered in August 2017, 4 Toyota Mirai (operating within the local tourism industry)
FC 巴士于 2017 年 8 月交付，4 辆丰田 Mirai（在当地旅游业内运营）
Contact 联系方式:
for further inforamtion Juan Ignacio Del Valle Gamboa:  juan@adastrarocket.com phone +506 2666 9272
欲了解更多信息，请访问 Juan Ignacio Del Valle Gamboa：juan@adastrarocket.com 电话 +506 2666 9272

Comments 评论:
The station will be part of the announced "50 hydrogen refuelling stations until 2015 project" funded within the German National Hydrogen and Fuel Cell Technology Innovation Programme (NIP) and of the Daimler-Linde infrastructure programme.
The station has a footprint of about 7mx7m. This HRS was developed explicitly for congested locations  by Linde together with  station operators. The LH2 tank could also be increased a bit with the same footprint (probably a bit higher designed).
The stations with LBST-Id 610, 711, 552 and 709 are built in the same way..
该加氢站将成为已宣布的 "2015 年前 50 个加氢站项目 "的一部分，该项目由德国国家氢能和燃料电池技术创新计划（NIP）和戴姆勒-林德基础设施计划资助。
加氢站占地面积约为 7 米 x 7 米。这种 HRS 是林德与加氢站运营商共同开发的，专门用于交通拥堵的地点。在占地面积不变的情况下，LH2 储气罐也可以增加一些（可能设计得更高一些）。
带有 LBST-Id 610、711、552 和 709 的加油站也是这样建造的。

Description 描述:
ENGIE GNVert is the operator of this HRS located in the Edouard Herriot port in Lyon (CNR) and  McPhy is the supplier of the HRS   1st stage: 200 bar H2 buffers  2nd stage: on site electrolyzer, producing « clean » hydrogen, using electricity from renewable energy (CNR)  April 2018: a second station is planned with capacity of 80 kg/day (probably at the same place) also built by McPhy in  the framework of the Eu funded project H2ME.

Goal 目标:
Start conversations with businesses, Local, State and Federal Governments to encourage infrastructure investment and infrastructure roll out in Australia, New Zealand and Pacific regions.
开始与企业、地方、州和联邦政府对话，鼓励在澳大利亚、新西兰和太平洋地区进行基础设施投资和基础设施建设。
Description 描述:
It is planned to install an electrolyser  (by Sefca) and a solar power plant to produce H2 on-site.  2014: Air Procducts installed the station Series 100 at 35 MPa. Coregas will deliver the hydrogen (produced by steam reforming of natural gas).  The operator is Hyundai Motor Company Australia working with Australian State and Federal Government Departments, Macquarie University, University of Western Sydney, Coregas, SEFCA, Air Products, Energy Australia and H2H Energy   Hydrogen delivered by Coregas Australia. Steam reformed Natural Gas from Port Kembla NSW. Solar and Electrolyser will be installed in late 2015. Dec 2020: delivery of H2 produced with renewable energy (PtG plant of Jemena) will start mid 2021 JAn 2022: station will replaced by a new one with electrolysis on-site. The state-of-the-art station will produce up to 20kg of hydrogen per day via an integrated electrolyser, as well as providing 700bar refuelling capability. Hyundai has selected US-based PDC Machines and IVYS Energy Solutions to supply the hydrogen refuelling station, known as the SimpleFuelFast, with ENGV responsible for local integration, installation and ongoing operational services.
计划安装一个电解槽（由 Sefca 制造）和一个太阳能发电站，在现场生产 H2。 2014: Air Procducts 公司安装了 35 兆帕的 100 系列加氢站。Coregas 将提供氢气（由天然气蒸汽转化产生）。 运营商为现代汽车澳大利亚公司，合作方包括澳大利亚州政府和联邦政府部门、麦考瑞大学、西悉尼大学、Coregas、SEFCA、Air Products、澳大利亚能源公司以及由 Coregas 澳大利亚公司提供氢气的 H2H Energy Hydrogen。来自新南威尔士州肯布拉港的蒸汽转化天然气。太阳能和电解槽将于 2015 年底安装。2020 年 12 月：2021 年年中开始交付利用可再生能源（杰梅纳的 PtG 工厂）生产的氢气 2022 年 1 月：氢气站将被新的现场电解氢气站取代。这个最先进的加氢站将通过一个集成电解槽每天生产多达 20 公斤的氢气，并提供 700bar 的加氢能力。现代汽车公司已选择美国的 PDC Machines 和 IVYS Energy Solutions 供应氢气加气站（称为 SimpleFuelFast），ENGV 负责本地集成、安装和持续运营服务。

Goal 目标:
The goal of the ESH2 2.0 Project is to develop a hydrogen filling station based on high efficient PEM electrolysis.
ESH2 2.0 项目的目标是开发基于高效 PEM 电解技术的加氢站。
Description 描述:
This hydrogen refueling station is part of the ESH2 2.0 project, and Andalusian initiative coordinated by Abengoa Hidrógeno, partially funded by Innovation and Development Agency of Andalusia (IDEA). The ESH2 2.0 project, finalized in March 2015, has involved four partners: Abengoa Hidrógeno, MC2, Soinan and ECA Bureau Veritas Group.  The objectives of this project were to develop and construct a complete hydrogen refueling station, using pure hydrogen produced on site by PEM electrolysis. The PEM electrolyzer system has been also developed, constructed and tested during this project by Abengoa Hidrógeno. The electrolyzer produces 30 Nm3/h of pure hydrogen (99.9995% of purity, fulfilling the standard SAE J2719), at 40 bara. Hydrogen is then compressed and stored on site at 450 bara. Hydrogen is finally cooled down 20 ºC (below ambient temperature), to avoid issues at the dispenser. The refueling station is designed to supply hydrogen at 350 bara, being also feasible supplying hydrogen to 700 bar tanks (limiting vehicle range).   Development project started in October 2013  Hydrogen station construction ended in March 2015  Station in full operation can be considered as from December 2015 
该加氢站是 ESH2 2.0 项目的一部分，该项目是由 Abengoa Hidrógeno 协调的安达卢西亚倡议，由安达卢西亚创新与发展署 (IDEA) 提供部分资金。ESH2 2.0 项目于 2015 年 3 月完成，有四个合作伙伴参与： Abengoa Hidrógeno、MC2、Soinan 和 ECA 必维国际检验集团参与了该项目。 该项目的目标是开发和建造一个完整的加氢站，使用现场通过 PEM 电解产生的纯氢。在该项目中，Abengoa Hidrógeno 公司还开发、建造并测试了 PEM 电解槽系统。该电解槽在 40 bara 的条件下每小时可产生 30 Nm3 的纯氢（纯度为 99.9995%，符合 SAE J2719 标准）。然后在现场以 450 bara 的压力压缩和储存氢气。最后将氢气冷却到 20 ºC（低于环境温度），以避免加气机出现问题。加氢站的设计可供应 350 bara 的氢气，也可向 700 bar 的氢气罐供应氢气（限制车辆续航里程）。  开发项目于 2013 年 10 月开始，加氢站建设于 2015 年 3 月结束，加氢站可于 2015 年 12 月开始全面运行

The project will include creation of a fleet of minibuses and a fuel cell powered educational trailer and associated new hydrogen production and refuelling facilities at the Hydrogen Office and at Fife Council’s vehicle depot.  Two 35MPa refuellers, technology provided by Logan Energy Limited H2 produced by on site electrolysis from renewable electricity from wind and solar PV.  The two refuellers are identical, apart from one uses a PEM electrolyser and the other an Alkaline electrolyser, and are co-located on the same Methil site. 
该项目将包括在氢能办公室和法夫议会的车辆仓库建立一支小巴车队和一辆燃料电池驱动的教育拖车，以及相关的新氢气生产和加氢设施。 两台 35MPa 加气机由 Logan Energy Limited 提供技术，利用风能和太阳能光伏发电产生的可再生能源在现场电解生产氢气。 除了一个使用 PEM 电解器，另一个使用碱性电解器之外，这两个加氢器完全相同，并且位于同一个梅希尔地点。

StationName 站名:
Coop hydrogen station
合作氢气站
Goal 目标:
The vision of COOP is to have a CO2 free vehicle fleet until 2013.
COOP 的愿景是在 2013 年之前实现车队无二氧化碳排放。
Description 描述:
H2 is produced at the hydro power plant in Aarau (capacity H2 for 170 vehicles/a) and compressed to 20 MPa (metal membran compressor by sera ComPress GmbH).The H2 purity produced by electrolysis in Aarau corresponds to SAE J2719. Electrolyser by Proton OnSite C30. Trailer by Messer Schweiz AG. H2 Energy and IBAarau are responsible for the H2 production and delivery to the refueling station. Coop Mineraloel AG is the owner and operator of the refueling station.  Storage with 50 MPa pressure level. High pressure storage at 95 MPa. Compressor by Linde Ionic IC 90. Trucks and passenger cars can be refueled simultaneously.Precooling to -40 °C for 70 MPa refueling. Medium pressure storage tank 310 kg under ground. High pressure storage 18 bottles 70 MPa, 39 bottles 35 MPa. capacity.  max. 388 kg H2 at the station,  numbers of refuellings  cars 12 x 3 kg in 2’ back-to-back, PKW 6 x 6 kg in 3’ Standzeit ca. 10’  trucks 4 x 15 kg in 4’ back-to-back 2 x 30 kg in 7’ Standzeit ca. 12’ time to refill all storages 2 h
阿劳水力发电厂生产的 H2（H2 容量为 170 辆车/年），压缩后的压力为 20 兆帕（由 sera ComPress GmbH 生产的金属膜压缩机）。阿劳电解生产的 H2 纯度符合 SAE J2719 标准。电解槽由 Proton OnSite C30 制造。拖车由梅塞尔股份公司制造。H2 Energy 和 IBAarau 负责生产 H2 并将其运送到加气站。Coop Mineraloel AG 是加气站的所有者和运营商。 存储压力为 50 兆帕。95 兆帕高压储气罐。林德 Ionic IC 90 压缩机。可同时为卡车和客车加油。预冷至 -40 °C，用于 70 兆帕的加油。地下中压储气罐 310 千克。高压储气罐 18 瓶 70 兆帕，39 瓶 35 兆帕。加气站内 388 千克 H2，加气次数 汽车 12 x 3 千克，2' 背靠背，PKW 6 x 6 千克，3' Standzeit ca. 10' 卡车 4 x 15 千克，4'背靠背 2 x 30 千克，7'站立时间约为 10'。12'装满所有储藏室所需时间 2 小时
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
production by electrolysis with renewable energy (by hydro power at the hydro power station in Aarau) 200 kW; capacity 170 vehicles/day max 388 kg H2
利用可再生能源（阿劳水电站的水力发电）电解生产 200 千瓦；产能 170 辆/天，最大 388 千克 H2
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
max 388 kg; Medium pressure storage tank 310 kg under ground. High pressure storage 18 bottles 70 MPa, 39 bottles 35 MPa
最大 388 千克；地下中压储气罐 310 千克。高压储罐 18 瓶 70 兆帕，39 瓶 35 兆帕
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
prototype 34t FC ESORO truck (35 MPa) for the COOP logistc, 12 FC vehicles

Description 描述:
Biomaa-based hydrogen demonstration project   Air Products SmartFuel® hydrogen fueling technology.  The Shikaoi Hydrogen Farm utilizes agricultural wastes which are anaerobically digested to create a supply of raw biogas. This biogas is upgraded to a purified supply of biomethane using Air Products’ PRISM® PB Membrane separators. The biomethane is then used as a feedstock to manufacture renewable hydrogen on-site, which generates heat, power and vehicle fuel.

Description 描述:
Linde IC 90 compressor, footprint 7m x 7m   In operation since August 2017, inauguration on October 18, 2017.
林德 IC 90 压缩机，占地面积 7m x 7m 2017 年 8 月开始运行，2017 年 10 月 18 日启用。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
capacity 6 - 7 cars / h, approximate 200 kg/day
产能 6 - 7 辆/小时，约 200 公斤/天
HydrogenStorage 氢储存: 400 kg LH2
Comments 评论:
Funded by German NIP with 400,000€. Investcost apporxomately 1 - 1.3 Mio €.
The station has a footprint of about 7mx7m. This HRS was developed explicitly for congested locations  by Linde together with  station operators. The LH2 tank could also be increased a bit with the same footprint (probably a bit higher designed).
The stations with LBST-Id 610, 711, 552 and 709 are built in the same way.
由德国 NIP 资助 400 000 欧元。投资成本约为 100-130 万欧元。
加油站占地面积约为 7mx7m。该 HRS 是林德公司与加气站运营商共同开发的，专门用于加气站拥挤的地方。在占地面积不变的情况下，LH2 储气罐也可以增加一些（可能设计得更高一些）。
LBST-Id为610、711、552和709的加油站也是这样建造的。

Description 描述:
orl: The station is part of the Renewable Transport Fuels Test Berth. Neoen, Megawatt Capital, SIemens and Hyundai will establish a 1.25 MW H2 electrolyser that will produce the hydrogen with electricity from a big wind farm. ENGV, IVYS, Nel and PDC Machines contributed to the design and construction of the station. The HRS incorporates a Nel C10 PEM electrolyser and PDC Machines & Ivys compression and refuelling solution. The station is designed to refuel up to 20 hydrogen fuel cell electric vehicles (FCEV) initially, with future expansion capabilities built in as the hydrogen transport market develops. Owned by ActewAGL and supplied by renewable hydrogen produced on-site, this first Australia hydrogen retail station was specially tailored for this application. PDC-IVYS designed the equipment to provide the fleet up to 140 kg/week initially but engineered it to be easily expandable. The station can increase capacity three-fold by adding a second compressor in the existing enclosure and additional storage tubes on the pad, with no increase in station footprint. Future-proofing these installations makes scaling adoption of green vehicles like the Hyundai Nexo even more viable and appealing to governments and entities looking to make the investment into clean transportation. 2021 September: project description new:  The hydrogen refuelling station pilot will use renewable electricity sourced from the grid (which is 100% renewable in the ACT) to produce hydrogen on-site with an electrolyser. The electrolyser is a Nel Hydrogen Proton Exchange Membrane (PEM) electrolyser (0.075 MW size) and can produce 21 kg of hydrogen per day. The produced hydrogen is compressed and stored in three tanks (all held at different pressures) which together can hold 44 kg of hydrogen (and from which the hydrogen is drawn during fuelling). Limited additional access to the refuelling station will also be available for privately-owned hydrogen vehicles by arrangement with ActewAGL, with the first private vehicle to be welcomed in August 2021. Consideration will also be given to installing solar panels at the station to provide a direct source of renewable energy. This project will allow Canberra-based industry and researchers to gain valuable firsthand knowledge of hydrogen refuelling operating models, transport supply chains, and consumer refuelling patterns. Feb 2022: now certified that it is powered by 100 per cent renewable energy
或者 该站是可再生运输燃料试验泊位的一部分。Neoen、Megawatt Capital、SIemens 和 Hyundai 将建立一个 1.25 兆瓦的氢电解槽，利用大型风力发电场的电力生产氢气。ENGV、IVYS、Nel 和 PDC Machines 参与了试验站的设计和建设。HRS 采用了 Nel C10 PEM 电解槽和 PDC Machines & Ivys 压缩与加氢解决方案。该加氢站最初可为多达 20 辆氢燃料电池电动汽车 (FCEV) 加氢，随着氢运输市场的发展，未来还将扩展加氢能力。该加氢站由 ActewAGL 所有，由现场生产的可再生氢气供应，是澳大利亚首个专门为该应用量身定制的加氢站。PDC-IVYS 设计的设备最初可为车队提供 140 千克/周的氢气，但设计时考虑到了设备的可扩展性。通过在现有机柜中增加第二台压缩机和在垫板上增加存储管，该加气站的产能可以提高三倍，而不会增加加气站的占地面积。这些装置面向未来，使现代 Nexo 等绿色车辆的推广应用更加可行，对希望投资清洁交通的政府和实体更具吸引力。2021 年 9 月：项目说明新内容：加氢站试点将使用来自电网的可再生能源电力（澳大利亚首都地区 100% 可再生能源电力），在现场用电解槽生产氢气。该电解槽为 Nel Hydrogen 质子交换膜 (PEM) 电解槽（0.075 兆瓦），每天可生产 21 千克氢气。产生的氢气被压缩并储存在三个储氢罐中（压力各不相同），三个储氢罐共可容纳 44 千克氢气（加气时从三个储氢罐中提取氢气）。根据 ActewAGL 公司的安排，加氢站还将为私人拥有的氢能汽车提供有限的额外通道，第一辆私人汽车将于 2021 年 8 月投入使用。此外，还将考虑在加氢站安装太阳能电池板，直接提供可再生能源。该项目将使堪培拉的行业和研究人员获得有关加氢运营模式、运输供应链和消费者加氢模式的第一手宝贵知识。2022 年 2 月：现已通过认证，100% 使用可再生能源。

StationName 站名:
Hynion Høvik
Hynion Høvik
Description 描述:
The station is relocated from Oslo Bjerke HYOP Økern station. Two dispensers with 70 MPa. September 2018: Hyop has to close the station because of econimical reasons March 2019: new company Hydrogenisk plans to reopen the station Nov, 21 2019 reopen by Hynion; The station will be expanded with a new supply line in collaboration with Hyundai and Toyota, which will improve capacity and security of supply when it is ready by the end of April 2020. December 2020: station is now upgraded so that it can meet expected demand. It is now a fully redundant station with two compressor lines and two dispensers.    The station is very busy: an average of 13 cars per day 7 days per week.  The current record is 22 cars refilled in one day. Hynion is operator and owner of the station. Sept 2022: plans for on-site electrolysis;  Hynion significantly improved the fuelling station's capacity by installing a new and powerful compressor. 
该站由奥斯陆比约克 HYOP Økern 站迁址而来。两个分配器的压力为 70 兆帕。2018 年 9 月： 2019 年 3 月：新公司 Hydrogenisk 计划重新开放加气站 2019 年 11 月 21 日，Hynion 重新开放加气站；加气站将与现代和丰田合作扩建一条新的供应线，2020 年 4 月底完工后将提高加气站的产能和供应安全性。2020 年 12 月：加油站现已升级，可以满足预期需求。它现在是一个完全冗余的加油站，拥有两条压缩机生产线和两台加气机。   加油站非常繁忙：每周 7 天，平均每天 13 辆车。 目前的记录是一天加注 22 辆汽车。Hynion 是该加气站的运营商和所有者。2022 年 9 月：计划进行现场电解；Hynion 通过安装新的大功率压缩机大大提高了加气站的能力。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
surplus H2 from chemical industry in Porsgrunn Rafnes; Sept 2022 plans for on-site electrolysis

StationName 站名:
Sandviken hydrogen station
桑德维肯氢气站
Description 描述:
Built and operated by Linde  Feb 2022: Hynion has taken over the station as operator Oct 2022: The station is serving 700 bar cars, and has installed a 350 bar line.  This had not been taken into use by Linde, but Hynion is now working to get this going.  Test refuelled the two Solaris buses, but  some rebuilding is necessary before it is all operational. to be operational end of 2022.  Also plans to install an electrolyser
2022 年 2 月：Hynion 接管该站并担任运营商 2022 年 10 月：该站为 700 巴的车辆提供服务，并安装了一条 350 巴的线路。 林德公司尚未投入使用，但 Hynion 正在努力使其投入使用。 对两辆 Solaris 公共汽车进行了加油测试，但在全部投入使用之前还需要进行一些重建工作。 还计划安装一个电解槽
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
Existing pipeline between AGA/Linde production facility and Sandvik industrial area, hydrogen from renewable energy (wind power), 2022: plans for on-site electrolysis

HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
1000 L High pressure, 27 m3 buffer tank @ approx. 12 bar.
1000 升高压、27 立方米缓冲罐 @ 约 12 巴。
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
cars, minivans, buses, already test refueling of 2 Solaris Urbino, (12 buses should started in autumn 2021)

Description 描述:
Bus manufacturer Van Hool (BE) supplies the buses. ITM Power will build the production (1 PEM electrolyser) and 8 distribution units for green hydrogen by electrolysis. 2 compressors IC 90 (Linde?), ENGIE and its subsidiary GNVert will contribute their know-how to the operation of the station. Jan 2019: construction started June 2019 Van Hool presented the bus at the headquarter in Koningshooikt September 2019: offical inauguration June 2020: The ITM Power 0.5MW electrolyser central to the Pau bus refueler project have produced since Dec 2019 over nine tonnes of hydrogen which have been used by the buses in seven days per week refuelling. July 2021: 4 additional buses are ordered (Van-Hool) overnight refuelling with 8 dispensers 1 kg/min
巴士制造商 Van Hool (BE) 提供巴士。ITM Power 公司将负责生产（1 个 PEM 电解槽）和 8 个电解绿色氢气的分配装置。2 台压缩机 IC 90 (林德？)、ENGIE 及其子公司 GNVert 将为加氢站的运营提供专业技术。2019 年 1 月：开工 2019 年 6 月：Van Hool 在 Koningshooikt 总部展示巴士 2019 年 9 月：正式落成 2020 年 6 月： 自 2019 年 12 月以来，Pau 公交车加气站项目的核心设备 ITM Power 0.5MW 电解槽已生产出超过 9 吨氢气，供公交车每周七天加气使用。2021 年 7 月：又订购了 4 辆公共汽车（Van-Hool），使用 8 台加注机，每分钟加注 1 公斤氢气。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site with renewable energy PEM EL 700kW, capacity 268 kg/day; 1 kg/min; back up H2 delivery with tube trailers
现场使用可再生能源 PEM EL 700 千瓦，日产量 268 千克；1 千克/分钟；用管式拖车运送后备 H2
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
< 1000 kg at 60 MPa
< 1000 千克，60 兆帕
VehiclesServed 服务车辆: 8 Van Hool Exqui City's (tram bus Febus) (3 within 3Emotion, 5 within JIVE project), delivery of the first bus is scheduled for September 2019; status 2021: 8 buses, 4 additional are ordered (to be delivered July 2022)
Comments 评论:
The station and buses are part of the EU FCH-JU funded projects 3Emotions ( 3 buses) and Jive 2 (5 buses). The bus project benefits from a grant from the ERDF (European Regional Development Fund) for 1.45 million euros. It has been certified by the France Ministry of the Environment as part of the "Territories Hydrogen". part of FEBUS, too.
车站和公交车是欧盟 FCH-JU 资助项目 3Emotions （3 辆公交车）和 Jive 2（5 辆公交车）的一部分。公交车项目获得了欧洲区域发展基金（ERDF）145 万欧元的资助。该项目已获得法国环境部的认证，成为 "氢地区 "的一部分。

StationName 站名:
PitPoint Arnhem
阿纳姆 PitPoint
Description 描述:
The H2 will be produced by SMR (HyGear technology). Pitpoint is owner of the production unit but its places op de premises of HyGear (neighbour) and HyGear will operate the production unit. Delivery is compressed hydrogen gas.  1 dispenser ( 1 hose) of 70 MPa for cars, and 1 separate dispenser (1 hose) of 35 MPa for buses and trucks Dec 2019 test operation starts October 2020: compressor has to be changed, until end of month refuelling with full pressure up to 100% will be possible; new compressor from Haskel April 2021: successful development, installation and deployment of new hydrogen refuelling compressor equipment (Haskel’s hydraulic-drive gas booster, H-Drive)
H2 将由 SMR（HyGear 技术）生产。Pitpoint 公司是生产装置的所有者，但其生产场所是 HyGear 公司（邻居）的，HyGear 公司将负责生产装置的运营。提供压缩氢气。 2019 年 12 月开始试运行 2020 年 10 月：必须更换压缩机，直到月底才能实现 100%全压加氢；新压缩机来自 Haskel 2021 年 4 月：成功开发、安装和部署新的加氢压缩机设备（Haskel 的液压驱动气体增压器 H-Drive）。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
about 100 m pipeline from production unit at HyGear with on-site production by steam reforming of  biogas, capacity 200 kg/day
距离 HyGear 生产装置约 100 米的管道，通过沼气蒸汽转化进行现场生产，产能为 200 公斤/天
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
passenger cars, bus, refuse collection vehicle (garbage truck)
客车、公交车、垃圾收集车（垃圾车）
Comments 评论:
Funded by the European Union  (H2Nodes project) and the Dutch Government (DKTI scheme).
由欧盟（H2Nodes 项目）和荷兰政府（DKTI 计划）资助。

TotalEnergies

埃尔兰根
Street2 街道 2:
at the Siemens AG campus
在西门子股份公司园区
Description 描述:
Siemens will operate an electrolyser powered by a PV system, for generating hydrogen from renewables. Hydrogenious LOHC Technologies supplies the filling station with green hydrogen, bound in liquid organic carrier material (LOHC), which is stored at the station in conventional underground tanks. The Hydrogenious release system installed at the station handles the recovery and feeding-in of the LOHC-bound hydrogen. Hydrogenious Technologies will demonstrate the recovery and supply of hydrogen from delivered LOHC using a ‘release box’.  The station allows for 700-bar refuelling of cars and light commercial vehicles, as well as 350-bar refuelling for vehicles like buses. The deployment of LOHC at the Erlangen hydrogen filling station is part of Hydrogenious’ broader H2Sektor pilot project, which has received subsidies from the Bavarian State Ministry for Economic Affairs and Energy due to its innovativeness and relevance (duration 2020 – 2022): H2Sector involves the development and research of a complete LOHC-based chain from green hydrogen production to transport and precisely to the use of hydrogen for mobility. The starting points are the generation of solar power via a PV system and its conversion into green hydrogen via a PEM electrolyzer at Hydrogenious’ headquarters in Erlangen. This is followed directly by hydrogen storage in the LOHC. A conventional tanker then transports the LOHC to the new Erlangen hydrogen filling station, where it is stored in underground tanks (30 m³ each), enabling hydrogen to be stocked in quantities of 1,500 kilograms. Such large hydrogen volumes in storage are not yet common at pressurized hydrogen refueling stations. Via its release system, which is connected to the underground tanks, Hydrogenious then ultimately provides green hydrogen with the highest degree of purity (according to the DIN EN 17124 or ISO 14687 standard) as a vehicle fuel. The liquid organic material benzyltoluene utilized by Hydrogenious LOHC Technologies – well-established in industry as a heat transfer medium – brings with it ideal properties for use as a hydrogen carrier: The potential hazard is very low, as it is flame retardant and non-explosive. It has a high volumetric energy density and can be handled like a fossil liquid fuel in existing infrastructure at ambient pressure and temperature. After dehydrogenation, it can be reused many hundreds of times to bind hydrogen. In test operation since May 2022 official inauguration on July 2nd 2022 commissioning in Feb 2023
西门子将运行一个由光伏系统供电的电解槽，利用可再生能源生产氢气。Hydrogenious LOHC 技术公司为加氢站提供以液态有机载体材料 (LOHC) 结合的绿色氢气，并将其储存在加氢站的传统地下储罐中。加氢站安装的 Hydrogenious 释放系统负责回收和输入与 LOHC 结合的氢气。Hydrogenious 技术公司将演示如何使用 "释放箱 "从交付的 LOHC 中回收和供应氢气。该加氢站可为轿车和轻型商用车加注 700 巴的氢气，也可为公交车等车辆加注 350 巴的氢气。在埃尔兰根加氢站使用 LOHC 是 Hydrogenious 公司更广泛的 H2Sektor 试点项目的一部分，该项目因其创新性和相关性（期限为 2020 - 2022 年）而获得了巴伐利亚州经济事务和能源部的补贴。其起点是通过光伏系统产生太阳能，并通过位于埃尔兰根的 Hydrogenious 公司总部的 PEM 电解槽将其转化为绿色氢气。然后直接在 LOHC 中储存氢气。然后，一辆传统的油罐车将 LOHC 运送到新的埃尔兰根加氢站，储存在地下储罐（每个储罐 30 立方米）中，这样氢气的储存量就可以达到 1,500 公斤。如此大容量的氢气储存在加压加氢站还不多见。通过与地下储氢罐相连的释放系统，Hydrogenious 最终可提供纯度最高（符合 DIN EN 17124 或 ISO 14687 标准）的绿色氢气作为汽车燃料。Hydrogenious LOHC 技术公司使用的液态有机材料苄基甲苯在工业中作为传热介质已得到广泛认可，它具有作为氢载体的理想特性： 由于它具有阻燃性和非爆炸性，因此潜在危险极低。它的体积能量密度很高，可以像化石液体燃料一样在现有的基础设施中以环境压力和温度进行处理。脱氢后，它可以重复使用数百次来结合氢气。2022 年 5 月开始试运行，2022 年 7 月 2 日正式启用，2023 年 2 月投入使用。

Description 描述:
Two new stations in Wilmington and Ontario will be built together with three additional stations located at Toyotas facilities around LA. A heavy duty vehicle network of 5 stations. Sept 2022: Toyota, Kenworth Prove Fuel Cell Electric Truck Capabilities With Successful Completion of Truck Operations for ZANZEFF Project: Though officially concluding their duties in the ZANZEFF “Shore to Store” project on August 5, 2022, some of the trucks will remain in use as demonstration or working models, including one that will continue supporting Toyota operations in the lower LA Basin. Sept 2022: ZANZEFF project was successful, some of the trucks remain in use
将在威尔明顿和安大略新建两个加油站，并在洛杉矶附近的丰田公司设施内新建三个加油站。一个由 5 个加气站组成的重型车辆网络。2022 年 9 月：丰田、肯沃斯成功完成 ZANZEFF 项目的卡车运营，证明了燃料电池电动卡车的能力： 虽然这些卡车已于 2022 年 8 月 5 日正式结束了在 ZANZEFF "从海岸到仓库 "项目中的任务，但其中一些卡车仍将作为示范或工作模型继续使用，包括一辆将继续支持丰田在洛杉矶盆地下游的运营。2022 年 9 月：ZANZEFF 项目取得成功，部分卡车将继续使用

Description 描述:
Started in 2019 with refueling of 35 MPa for light duty vehicles, technology McPhy 2021-03: plans to upgrade with compressor of NEL for refueling 35 MPa for light duty vehicles and buses and 70 MPa for private passenger cars and garbage trucks; to start Q3 2022 July 2021: garbage truck was inaugurated Cosmhyc: The fleet already comprises 10 hydrogen utility vehicles at 350 bar, passenger cars at 700 bar and 1 garbage truck at 700 bar. During COSMHYC DEMO, project dedicated activities aim at increasing this exiting fuel cell vehicle fleet with additional utility vehicles, passenger cars, busses and forklifts. To begin with, a regional supplier will provide green hydrogen to the refuelling station by trailer. Later, green hydrogen will be produced on-site through electrolysis. This is planned as a part of CCTVI’s HySOPARC project. In addition, a filling centre will be installed for filling trailers and distributing hydrogen to other hydrogen refuelling stations or local industrial clients. This will increase the utilisation rate of the innovative compressors, allowing an optimal testing framework. 2022: upgrade to 200 kg/day, bus refuelling and 70 MPa car refueling is planned
2021-03 年：计划升级 NEL 压缩机，为轻型车辆和公共汽车加注 35 兆帕的氢气，为私人客 车和垃圾车加注 70 兆帕的氢气；2022 年第三季度开始 2021 年 7 月：垃圾车启用 Cosmhyc： 车队已包括 10 辆 350 巴的氢气多用途车、700 巴的乘用车和 1 辆 700 巴的垃圾车。在 COSMHYC DEMO 期间，项目的专门活动旨在增加现有的燃料电池车队，增加公用车、客车、公交车和叉车。首先，一家地区供应商将用拖车向加氢站提供绿色氢气。之后，将通过电解法在现场生产绿色氢气。这是 CCTVI 的 HySOPARC 项目的一部分。此外，还将安装一个加注中心，为拖车加注氢气，并将氢气分配给其他加氢站或当地的工业客户。这将提高创新型压缩机的利用率，使测试框架达到最佳状态。2022 年：计划将加氢站升级到 200 公斤/天，为公共汽车加氢，并为 70 兆帕的汽车加氢
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site with electricity from renewable energy, capacity 20 kg/day; upgrade to 200 kg/d is planned (to start 2022 Q3) first with deliverd H2, later by electrolysis on-site , too
现场使用可再生能源发电，日产量为 20 千克；计划将日产量提升至 200 千克（2022 年第三季度开始），首先使用输送的 H2，之后也在现场进行电解。
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
utility vehicles (13 FC Kangoo Symbio), FC bicycles; plans: cars, garbage truck, buses (Q3 2022)
多功能车（13 FC Kangoo Symbio）、FC 自行车；计划：汽车、垃圾车、公共汽车（2022 年第三季度）

Description 描述:
Based around the joint initiative previously known as the “Hydrogen Mobility Project”, the company eFarming GmbH & Co. KG founded by GP JOULE will now set up and operate a hydrogen production and distribution grid in North Frisia on a modular, expandable basis.  For the production of green hydrogen from wind power – which will be available for fuelling at two public filling stations – five electrolysers (225 kW each, H-TEC SYSTEMS ME 350/100)) will be installed by the end of 2019 at suitable sites, close to the wind power plants and near heat grids. Since heat is also generated in the production of hydrogen, this will also be fed into the local heat supply network. The hydrogen will be then be filled into mobile storage containers and transported by truck to the two hydrogen filling stations. Here the hydrogen will be further compressed in order to enable fuelling of the buses as required, as well as additional hydrogen-powered trucks and cars. 2020 September: inauguration of electrolyser in Boshüll July 2021 start of test operation 13.09.21 official inauguration
eFarming GmbH & Co.Ltd.公司围绕之前被称为 "氢能移动项目 "的联合倡议，于 2010 年成立。KG 将在北弗里斯兰以模块化、可扩展的方式建立并运营氢气生产和分配网络。 为了利用风能生产绿色氢气（将在两个公共加气站提供燃料），将于 2019 年底前在靠近风力发电厂和热网的合适地点安装五台电解槽（每台 225 千瓦，H-TEC SYSTEMS ME 350/100）。由于氢气生产过程中也会产生热量，这些热量也将输入当地的供热网络。然后，氢气将被注入移动存储容器，并用卡车运往两个加氢站。在这里，氢气将被进一步压缩，以便根据需要为公共汽车以及其他氢动力卡车和汽车提供燃料。2020 年 9 月：博许尔电解槽落成 2021 年 7 月开始试运行 21 年 9 月 13 日正式落成

Description 描述:
H2 production plant (production via electrolysis) and refueling station for cars, trucks and Buses are planned. Production facility is planned to start by the end of 2019. In September 2020, Ports of Auckland was granted resource consent to build and operate a hydrogen production and refuelling facility at the Waitematā port. The produced hydrogen would initially be used in various test hydrogen vehicles. At the first stage, Ports of Auckland has set up an interim hydrogen refueller, to enable the refuelling of test vehicles until the production and refuelling facility has been built.  Jan 2021 by H2H Energy installed and operate a 35/70 Mpa mobile refueller Feb 2021: Auchland Transport and Hiringa Energy work together March 2021: bus went in operation, refuelling at a temporary station June 2021: Obayashi Corporation has been selected as partner for the project:  it was announced that the Ports of Auckland and Obayashi Corporation, a Japanese construction company, are to set up a joint venture to develop the hydrogen refuelling station facility; the joint venture would also be examining opportunities to expand hydrogen production and supply at Ports of Auckland inland ports. Kiwi Rail is examining the potential for the use of hydrogen to power trains. Dec 2021: bus is refuelled at a temporary station (mobile refueller is in operation since Jan 2021) July 2022: Hyundai Xcient Fuel Cell truck was officially unveiled in its working livery by NZ Post at an event held at their Auckland Operations Centre; until refuelling stations are ready (until early 2023), the truck is refuelled with "green" H2 delivered by BOC Linde from Glenbrook facility 
计划建设 H2 生产厂（通过电解法生产）和汽车、卡车和公共汽车加气站。生产设施计划于 2019 年底启动。2020 年 9 月，奥克兰港获得资源许可，在 Waitematā 港建造并运营氢气生产和加气设施。生产出的氢气最初将用于各种氢气测试车辆。在第一阶段，奥克兰港建立了一个临时加氢装置，以便在生产和加氢设施建成之前为测试车辆加氢。2021 年 1 月由 H2H Energy 安装并运行 35/70 兆帕移动加氢器 2021 年 2 月： 2021 年 2 月： 奥克兰运输公司与 Hiringa Energy 合作 2021 年 3 月： 公交车投入运营，在临时加油站加油 2021 年 6 月： 小林公司被选为该项目的合作伙伴：据宣布，奥克兰港和日本建筑公司小林公司将成立一家合资企业，共同开发加氢站设施；该合资企业还将研究在奥克兰港内陆港口扩大氢气生产和供应的机会。奇异果铁路公司正在研究使用氢气为火车提供动力的可能性。2021 年 12 月：巴士在临时加气站加气（移动加气机自 2021 年 1 月开始运行） 2022 年 7 月：现代 Xcient 燃料电池卡车在新西兰邮政奥克兰运营中心举行的活动上正式亮相；在加气站准备就绪之前（直到 2023 年初），卡车使用中银林德从格伦布鲁克设施提供的 "绿色 "H2 加气。

A heavy duty vehicle network of 5 stations.
