Description 描述:
Using 100 percent renewable biogas from dairy manure, delivered via the natural gas pipeline system, and using a carbonate fuel cell Tri-gen system developed by FuelCell Energy, the station will produce 1,000 kg/day of renewable hydrogen as well as over two megawatts of renewable electricity for the facility.  Also plans to provide fuel at a lower pressure to enable refueling of other vehicles besides trucks, too. July 2021: Long Beach station is in operation but it is closed to public access for the first 12 months. It is only open to fleet contracted by Toyota Logistics Services.
通过天然气管道系统输送的奶牛粪便产生的 100% 可再生沼气，以及 FuelCell Energy 公司开发的碳酸盐燃料电池 Tri-gen 系统，该加气站将每天生产 1000 公斤可再生氢气，并为设施提供超过两兆瓦的可再生电力。 还计划以较低的压力提供燃料，以便为卡车以外的其他车辆加油。2021 年 7 月： 长滩站投入运营，但在最初的 12 个月内不对公众开放。只对丰田物流服务公司签约车队开放。

Description 描述:
Built and maintained by Air Products and Tirillium. Air Products provieded equipment and delivers LH2. Refulling time for 28 kg / bus 6 - 10 min.  At the time of commissioning, the station was the largest capacity hydrogen fueling station for transit buses in North America. The station can dispense up to 1,500 kilograms (kg) of hydrogen in an eight-hour time period. The station can fuel transit buses with an average of 28 kg of hydrogen per bus in six to 10 minutes per bus, while also providing back-to-back fueling continuously. The station can also fill two buses simultaneously from two fueling lanes in under 10 minutes.
由空气产品公司和 Tirillium 负责建造和维护。空气产品公司提供设备和 LH2。28 公斤/辆巴士的再充气时间为 6 - 10 分钟。 在投入使用时，该加氢站是北美最大的公交巴士加氢站。该加氢站可在 8 小时内加注多达 1,500 公斤的氢气。该加氢站可在 6 至 10 分钟内为每辆公交车平均加注 28 公斤氢气，同时还可连续提供背靠背加氢服务。该加氢站还能在 10 分钟内从两条加氢通道同时为两辆公交车加氢。

Oxford-based Ryze Hydrogen is responsible for transporting the fuel to the fuelling station.From 2023, the Mayoral Office further expects hydrogen to be even greener as it will be produced by electrolysis powered by a direct connection to an offshore windfarm. Description 描述:
Plans for a green hydrogen production plant, powered by solar energy, with 10 MW electrolysis. The plant will produce H2 for public and private transport vehicles. Green Hysland will need a total investment of around EUR 50 million, including costs of renewable power generation and equipment for green hydrogen end uses. Hydrogen will be produced from solar power on Mallorca, with the total output in distribution reaching at least 300 tonnes per year, FCH JU said. This output will be used to power 5  fuel-cell buses of the Palma EMT and 10 rental vehicles, ferries and port operations, generate heat and power for commercial and public buildings, feed into a hydrogen refuelling station and the island’s gas grid owned by Redexis. The plant is expected to start in 2021.Construction is scheduled to begin in July 2021. Electrolyser by Hydrogenics Aug 2021: construction of the solar power plant starts march 2022: 5 Solaris Urbino 12 hydrogen were ordered
计划建造一座以太阳能为动力的绿色制氢厂，电解能力为 10 兆瓦。该厂将为公共和私人交通工具生产氢气。Green Hysland 的总投资约为 5000 万欧元，其中包括可再生能源发电和绿色氢气终端用途设备的成本。FCH JU 表示，将利用马略卡岛上的太阳能生产氢气，每年的总产量至少达到 300 吨。产出的氢将用于为帕尔马 EMT 的 5 辆燃料电池公交车、10 辆租赁车辆、渡轮和港口运营提供动力，为商业和公共建筑提供热能和电能，为加氢站和 Redexis 拥有的岛上天然气网络提供动力。该工厂预计将于 2021 年开工。Hydrogenics 的电解槽 2021 年 8 月：太阳能发电厂开工建设 2022 年 3 月：订购 5 台 Solaris Urbino 12 型制氢设备

StationName 站名:

克罗地亚首个氢气站
Street1 街道1:
Ivana Lucica
伊万娜-卢西卡
Description 描述:
This hydrogen refuelling station is designed as autonomous system that uses solar energy to power PEM and alkaline electrolyzer. Water needed for electrolysis is supplied from rain collector storage tank. Photovoltaic modules of 2.02 kW are installed on the roof above H2 station. Because of its innovative shape, trademark (national level) and design (international level) of this H2 station is protected as intellectual property in CH (Switzerland), EM (European Union), NO (Norway), RU (Russian Federation), TR (Turkey), UA (Ukraine): http://www.wipo.int/designdb/hague/en/showData.jsp?&SOURCE=HAGUE&KEY=D102305&LANG=en&NO=0&TOT=46 It was designed and installed at the University of Zagreb, Faculty of Mechanical Engineering and Naval Architecture, Zagreb, Croatia. Project leader is Ankica Kovač, Ph.D. Components were provide by H2Planet. Funding company was Croatian Telecom Inc. Car manufacturer involved as project supporter is Toyota Croatia. Further plan is to install compressor in order to make it publically available for hydrogen car refuelling in order to connect Croatia to Europe hydrogen community.
该加氢站设计为自主系统，利用太阳能为 PEM 和碱性电解槽供电。电解所需的水由集雨储水罐提供。加氢站上方的屋顶上安装了 2.02 千瓦的光伏组件。由于其创新的外形，该 H2 站的商标（国家级）和设计（国际级）在 CH（瑞士）、EM（欧盟）、NO（挪威）、RU（俄罗斯联邦）、TR（土耳其）、UA（乌克兰）受到知识产权保护：http://www.wipo.int/designdb/hague/en/showData.jsp?&SOURCE=HAGUE&KEY=D102305&LANG=en&NO=0&TOT=46 它是在克罗地亚萨格勒布的萨格勒布大学机械工程和航海建筑系设计和安装的。项目负责人是 Ankica Kovač，博士。组件由 H2Planet 提供。资助公司为克罗地亚电信公司。作为项目支持者的汽车制造商是丰田克罗地亚公司。进一步的计划是安装压缩机，以便向公众提供氢气汽车加气服务，从而将克罗地亚与欧洲氢气社区连接起来。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site (PEM and AL) with electricity from renewable energy (solar power), capacity 0,5 kg/day
现场发电（PEM 和 AL），电力来自可再生能源（太阳能），发电量为 0.5 千克/天
HydrogenStorage 氢储存:
The local buffer storage technology is metal hydride with capacity of 1 kg.
当地的缓冲储存技术是容量为 1 千克的金属氢化物。
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
Currently it is possible to fill hydrogen bicycles for free. Experimental set up for filling private hydrogen car is in progress.
目前，氢能自行车可以免费充气。为私人氢能汽车充气的实验装置正在进行中。

Description 描述:
Hyundai will support the construction cost of the hydrogen refueling station while providing up to 12 fuel cell electric buses as well as their maintenance and service. Incheon International Airport will provide a site for the station and Hydrogen Energy Network will handle its construction and operation. Air Liquide Korea will provide two high-capacity hydrogen chargers and supply hydrogen gas.  29.7.21: HyNet will operate the station which will primarily serve hydrogen buses but will also be used for fuel cell passenger cars. Air Liquide supplied the high-capacity hydrogen refueling station equipment. The Group will also be the hydrogen supplier under a long-term contract. On average, it is able to serve 40 buses or 180 passenger cars per day. Leveraging on Air Liquide’s most recent technology, it will allow two buses to fill simultaneously as well as passenger cars consecutively with limited waiting time for efficient peak time management.
现代汽车将支持加氢站的建设费用，同时提供多达 12 辆燃料电池电动巴士及其维护和服务。仁川国际机场将为加氢站提供场地，氢能源网络将负责加氢站的建设和运营。液化空气韩国公司将提供两个大容量氢气充电器并供应氢气。 29.7.21：HyNet 将负责该站的运营，该站主要为氢能巴士服务，但也将用于燃料电池客车。液化空气集团提供大容量加氢站设备。根据长期合同，液化空气集团也将是氢气供应商。该加氢站平均每天可为 40 辆公交车或 180 辆乘用车加氢。利用液化空气集团的最新技术，该加氢站可同时为两辆巴士加氢，并可在有限的等待时间内连续为客车加氢，从而实现有效的高峰时段管理。

StationName 站名:
Toyota Hydrogen Center
丰田氢能中心
City 城市:
Melbourne - Altona North
墨尔本 - Altona North
Description 描述:
Hydrogen center with education center, investigation 7,4,Mio US $ in total. Education center to start in Dec 2019, refueling station end of 2020. For now, Toyota is using a mobile truck-based refueller as temporary station. The system has capacity to produce approximately 80kg of renewable hydrogen per day for use in hydrogen fuel cell vehicles. The hydrogen created will be stored in a series of high and low pressure tanks, with a 30 kW fuel cell also being installed to convert hydrogen back into electricity to power the site if needed. Open 29.3.21: Hydrogen is produced on site by a 200kW electrolyser and has the capacity to produce up to 80kg of hydrogen per day. Power for the electrolyser is drawn from a combination of an 87kW solar array, a 100kW battery storage, and mains grid, depending on what’s available at the time. The hydrogen is then stored in a bank of storage tubes at medium and high pressure to be able to refuel both the fuel-cell forklifts that Toyota uses in other parts of the Altona complex and hydrogen FCEVs, like the new Mirai FCEV. The  electrolyser and hydrogen refuelling station became fully operational in November 2021. REFUELLER SPECIFICATION (Stand Toyota 2019) Supplier: The Linde Group Compressor Type: Linear 3-Stage GH2 Discharge Pressure: Up to 900 bar at 5kg/h Delivery Pressures: 350 bar and 700 bar Pre-cooling Temp: -20 Deg C
氢气中心与教育中心，总投资 7,400,000 美元。教育中心将于 2019 年 12 月启动，加气站将于 2020 年底启动。目前，丰田正在使用移动式卡车加氢机作为临时加氢站。该系统每天可生产约 80 千克可再生氢，用于氢燃料电池汽车。产生的氢气将储存在一系列高压和低压罐中，同时还将安装一个 30 千瓦的燃料电池，以便在需要时将氢气转化为电力，为现场供电。公开 29.3.21：氢气由一个 200 千瓦的电解槽在现场生产，每天最多可生产 80 千克氢气。电解槽的电力来自 87 千瓦的太阳能电池阵列、100 千瓦的蓄电池和主电网，视当时可用情况而定。然后，氢气以中压和高压储存在一组储存管中，以便为丰田在阿尔托纳综合设施其他部分使用的燃料电池叉车和氢FCEV（如新款Mirai FCEV）加氢。电解槽和加氢站于 2021 年 11 月全面投入使用。加氢站规格（2019 年丰田展台） 供应商：林德集团 林德集团 压缩机类型：线性 3 级 GH2 线性 3 级 GH2 排气压力：5kg/h 时高达 900 巴 输出压力：350 巴和 700 巴 350 巴和 700 巴 预冷温度：-20 摄氏度

Description 描述:
Sept 2019: feasibility study starts, exact location will be determined until the end of the year 10.6.22 inauguration two dispensers (car, bus) part of a normal petrol station equiped with electric charging system, too. Following the agreement signed in 2019 between the Municipality & Metropolitan City of Venice, Eni and Toyota, the car manufacturer will put a minimum of ten Toyota Mirai on the road. Three were delivered today to Mayor Luigi Brugnaro and will be used by the Municipality of Venice. Three other cars will become part of the car fleet dedicated to the KINTO car-sharing service in the city of Venice. The remainder will be delivered in the coming months. compressor: Linde IC 90 /30-S 
2019 年 9 月：启动可行性研究，年底前确定具体位置 22 年 6 月 10 日：普通加油站的两个加油机（汽车、公交车）落成，并配备电动充电系统。根据威尼斯市政府、埃尼公司和丰田公司于 2019 年签署的协议，汽车制造商将在道路上至少投放 10 辆丰田 Mirai。今天，三辆丰田 Mirai 已交付给市长 Luigi Brugnaro，将由威尼斯市政府使用。另外三辆将成为威尼斯市 KINTO 汽车共享服务专用车队的一部分。其余车辆将在未来几个月内交付。 压缩机： 林德 IC 90 /30-S

Description 描述:
McPhy installed and commissioned the McFilling 20-350 station (also called « Starter Kit ») The McFilling 20-350 hydrogen station enables a efuelling solution to vehicles with a pressure of 350 bar, as well as a partial refueling solution (up to 60%) for vehicles requiring a refuelling pressure of 700 bar. This station will also be used to refuel the first hydrogen bus tested by the metropolis of Le Mans. The project’s partners are ARTELIA, SODEREF Développement and COLAS for the civil engineering, McPHY for the compression equipment and LINDE for the work on the hydrogen storage and supply facility
McPhy 安装并调试了 McFilling 20-350 加氢站（也称为 "启动套件"）。McFilling 20-350 加氢站可为压力为 350 巴的车辆提供加氢解决方案，也可为压力为 700 巴的车辆提供部分加氢解决方案（最多 60%）。该加气站还将用于为勒芒市测试的第一辆氢气公交车加气。该项目的合作伙伴包括负责土木工程的 ARTELIA 公司、SODEREF Développement 公司和 COLAS 公司，负责压缩设备的 McPHY 公司，以及负责氢气储存和供应设施工程的 LINDE 公司。

Goal 目标:
2021: 400 kg/d 5 buses, train tests, 10 light vehicles, 2025: 1000kg/d, 10 buses, 2 trucks, 10 light vehicles, 3 trains, H2 production by wind power and hydro power
2021 年：400 公斤/天，5 辆公共汽车，火车测试，10 辆轻型汽车，2025 年 1000 公斤/天，10 辆公共汽车，2 辆卡车，10 辆轻型汽车，3 辆火车，利用风能和水能生产 H2
Description 描述:
Hynamics, a subsidiary of EDF, which is in charge of the construction and operation. On-site production with a 1 MW electrolyser (McPhy) to produce 400kg/day hydrogen from renewable electricity. The station will produce hydrogen for buses, but also trucks and industrial utility vehicles. 13.10.21 inauguration 2.2.23 ABB and Hynamics have signed an agreement to integrate the ABB Ability OPTIMAX energy management to optimize hydrogen production costs.
法国电力公司的子公司 Hynamics 负责建设和运营。现场生产采用 1 兆瓦电解槽 (McPhy)，每天利用可再生电力生产 400 公斤氢气。该氢气站将为公共汽车生产氢气，同时也为卡车和工业车辆生产氢气。13.10.21 落成典礼 2.2.23 ABB 和 Hynamics 已签署协议，整合 ABB Ability OPTIMAX 能源管理，优化制氢成本。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site, capacity approx. 500 kg/d
现场，产能约 500 公斤/天
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
buses (5 SAFRA Businova H2 buses), planned also for utility vehicles and train

StationName 站名:
Belfort Bus Station
贝尔福汽车站
State 州/省:
Bourgogne-Franche-Comté
勃艮第-弗朗什-孔泰省
Goal 目标:
27 buses by 2025
到 2025 年达到 27 辆巴士
Description 描述:
In the first phase electrolysis with 1 MW is planned, in the second phase 2 MW. Dec 2021: 7 buses were ordered Jan 2022: McPhy gets the contract to build the HRS McFilling 350 and the electrolyser McLyzer. 800 kg/day to fuel 7 buses in 1 hour at 35 MPa, 2 Hi-flow dispensers. McPhy will deliver the equipment for the installation, consisting of a 1 MW McLyzer electrolyzer to power a McFilling 350 refueling station able to distribute up to 800 kg per day of hydrogen at 350 bar at full capacity. The station will offer two Hi-Flow terminals with the ability to fuel all 7 buses in one hour. The station will also offer a third terminal adapted to the filling of mobile storage units (tube trailers). This filling module could enable the use of low-carbon hydrogen to supply industrial uses remotely from the production site. The station is modular and configured to evolve with the growth of a project expected to go beyond this first stage. 26.6.23 5 of the 7 buses arrived, Van Hool
第一阶段计划电解 1 兆瓦，第二阶段计划电解 2 兆瓦。2021 年 12 月：订购 7 辆公共汽车 2022 年 1 月：McPhy 公司获得建造 HRS McFilling 350 和电解槽 McLyzer 的合同。每天 800 千克，在 35 兆帕的压力下 1 小时内为 7 辆公共汽车提供燃料，2 个高流量分配器。McPhy 将提供安装设备，包括一个 1 兆瓦的 McLyzer 电解槽，为 McFilling 350 加气站提供动力，该加气站在满负荷运行时可在 350 巴的压力下每天分配高达 800 公斤的氢气。加氢站将提供两个高流量终端，能够在一小时内为全部 7 辆巴士加氢。该加氢站还将提供第三个终端，用于为移动存储单元（管式拖车）加氢。该充气模块可实现低碳氢气的使用，为远离生产基地的工业用途提供氢气。加氢站采用模块化设计，可随着项目的发展而发展，预计将超越第一阶段。26.6.23 7 辆巴士中的 5 辆抵达，范霍尔
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site with electricity from renewable energy (phase 1: 1 1MW, phase 2 2 MW EL), capacity 800 kg/day, 7 buses/ hour
现场使用可再生能源供电（一期：1 1 兆瓦，二期 2 兆瓦 EL），容量 800 公斤/天，7 辆巴士/小时
VehiclesServed 服务车辆:
Dec 2021: 7 buses (Van Hool) are ordered, goal 27 buses by 2025;  third terminal designed to refill mobile storage equipment
2021 年 12 月：订购 7 辆公共汽车（Van Hool），目标是到 2025 年达到 27 辆；设计第三个终点站，为移动存储设备加注燃料

Goal 目标:
To convert the complete bus and garbadge truck fleet of Dijon
改装第戎的全部公共汽车和服装车车队
Description 描述:
1 MW electrolyser by McPhy two dispensers: 400 kg/day at 35 MPa and 400 kg/day at 35 and 70 MPa SAEJ As part of the DMSE project, green hydrogen will come from the combustion of waste in the territory by the construction of an electrolyser (1 MW McPhy). It will then be distributed by two hydrogen stations. The first, which will be located north of Dijon, will be commissioned in early 2022 and will supply a fleet of eight refuse collection vehicles and six light commercial vehicles. It will have a daily recharge capacity of 440 kg of hydrogen, which will eventually be doubled with the construction of an extension. The second station, located south of Dijon, will be commissioned in early 2023, to supply the buses in the Dijon metropolitan area with hydrogen, with a capacity of 880 kg of hydrogen per day, which can be tripled.  19 May 2021 groundbreaking Sept 2022: SAS Dijon Métropole Smart EnergHy obtains nearly 7 million euros in funding for the deployment of two green hydrogen production and distribution stations.
麦克菲公司的 1 兆瓦电解槽，两个分配器： 作为 DMSE 项目的一部分，绿色氢气将通过建造一个电解槽（1 兆瓦 McPhy）从境内的废物燃烧中获得。然后，氢气将由两个氢气站进行分配。第一个氢气站位于第戎北部，将于 2022 年初投入使用，为由 8 辆垃圾收集车和 6 辆轻型商用车组成的车队提供氢气。该加氢站的日加氢能力为 440 千克，随着加氢站的扩建，日加氢能力将翻倍。第二个加氢站位于第戎南部，将于 2023 年初投入使用，为第戎市区的公交车提供氢气，日加氢能力为 880 千克，可增加两倍。 2021 年 5 月 19 日 2022 年 9 月破土动工：SAS Dijon Métropole Smart EnergHy 获得近 700 万欧元资金，用于部署两个绿色氢气生产和配送站。

Description 描述:
China Petroleum & Chemical Corporation (“Sinopec”) and French company Air Liquide opened two hydrogen stations, West Shanghai Petrol and Hydrogen Fueling Station and Anzhi Gas and Hydrogen Fueling Station, on November 18, 2019 in Shanghai. They are the first stations in China to provide combined commercial gas and hydrogen fuel services. The two stations are secondary gas and hydrogen fueling stations; each is equipped with two gasoline tanks, two diesel tanks and four hydrogen tanks, as well as two 12-pump fuel dispensers, two four-pump 35MPa hydrogen dispensers and a reserved 70MPa hydrogen dispenser. The pipelines of the two stations were constructed per the upgraded 70MPa standard to meet the needs of both 35MPa and 70MPa car owners. Equipped with the world’s most advanced technologies, the two combined gas and hydrogen fueling stations have a daily capacity of 1,000 kilograms to serve public transportation, logistics and passenger vehicles. Each station can fuel 100 cars a day. 
2019年11月18日，中国石油化工集团公司（以下简称 "中国石化"）与法国液化空气公司在上海共同启用了两座加氢站--上海西加油加氢站和安芝加油加氢站。这两座加氢站是中国首批提供商用天然气和氢燃料组合服务的加氢站。两座加气站均为二级燃气加氢站，各配备2个汽油罐、2个柴油罐和4个氢气罐，以及2台12泵加油机、2台4泵35MPa加氢机和1台预留70MPa加氢机。两座加氢站的管道按照升级后的 70MPa 标准建造，以满足 35MPa 和 70MPa 车主的需求。这两座天然气和氢气联合加气站配备了世界上最先进的技术，日加气能力达 1000 公斤，可为公共交通、物流和客运车辆提供服务。每个加氢站每天可为 100 辆汽车加氢。

1 MW PEM electrolyser from NEL Feb 2021:  Construction on the hydrogen station is slated to begin in mid-March and should take five months to complete.  The estimated delivery date of the first hydrogen fuel  cell  bus  is  at  the end of March.    Hydrogen  will  be  temporarily  supplied  to  MTD  until  the production station is operable. August 2021: PDC Machines and Ivys Energy Solutions are deploying the station. The HRS will take hydrogen produced from a MW-scale PEM electrolyzer and dispenses to the buses at 350 bar pressure at -20 degrees C temperature for a T20 fast fill.  Oct 2021: two buses started
2021 年 2 月从 NEL 购买 1 兆瓦 PEM 电解槽：  氢气站的建设计划于 3 月中旬开始，需要 5 个月的时间完成。 第一辆氢燃料电池巴士的预计交付日期为 3 月底。   在生产站投入使用之前，将暂时向 MTD 供应氢气。2021 年 8 月： PDC Machines 和 Ivys Energy Solutions 正在部署生产站。HRS 将采用兆瓦级 PEM 电解槽生产的氢气，在零下 20 摄氏度的温度下，以 350 巴的压力向巴士分配氢气，实现 T20 快速填充。 2021 年 10 月：两辆巴士启动

Sept 2022: Everfuel will supply green hydrogen and deliver service and maintenance at the station for a minimum of 12 years. The station can be scaled to also accommodate fuelling of other fuel cell vehicles such as trucks and taxis.

Description 描述:
The project contains a renewable energy facility (51 MW) associated with a hydrogenerator (25 kg H2 / day at 350 bar) that will be directly connected to the wind turbines and will be supplied by seawater producing hydrogen from the resources natural available. The hydrogen generated will be used to replace part of the diesel vehicle fleet with hydrogen cars. The photovoltaic plants will supply the service station and the desalination plant (125 m3 / day (2.4 kW / m3)). June 15 2021: first car arrived October 2021: test driving for tourists accompanied by questionnaires that aim to collect information on the preferences, attitudes and opinions of tourists about the use of hydrogen cars in the Canary Islands; refueling probably with temporary mobile station;  station delivery is delayed due to various problems; hope to get and start it by the end of the year Jan 2022: to open February 2022, at the moment 1 Hyundai and 2 Toyota April 1st, 2022: station arrived Dec 2022: electrolyser doesn´t work, it has to return to Scotland
该项目包括一个可再生能源设施（51 兆瓦）和一个水力发电机（350 巴压力下 25 千克 H2/天），水力发电机将直接与风力涡轮机相连，并由海水供应，利用天然资源生产氢气。产生的氢气将用于用氢气汽车取代部分柴油汽车。光伏发电站将为服务站和海水淡化厂供电（125 立方米/天（2.4 千瓦/立方米））。2021 年 6 月 15 日：第一辆汽车抵达 2021 年 10 月：游客试驾，同时进行问卷调查，目的是收集游客对在加那利群岛使用氢能汽车的喜好、态度和意见；可能使用临时移动站进行加氢；由于各种问题，加氢站的交付被推迟；希望在年底前交付并开始使用 2022 年 1 月：2022 年 2 月开放，目前有 1 辆现代汽车和 2 辆丰田汽车 2022 年 4 月 1 日：加氢站抵达 2022 年 12 月：电解槽不工作，必须返回苏格兰

Description 描述:
McPhy 2 MW electrolyser platform. Refeuling for heavy duty with 35 MPa to start Q4 2021, full-size refueling with 70 MPa to start Q2 2022  Resato HRS Septemebr 2022: test operation starts October 2022: officially inaugurated The facility, which is open around the clock, enables transport companies or logistics companies, for example, to refuel their vehicles at a public filling station and thus the emission-free transport of people and goods. The refuelling of hydrogen-powered cars is also possible at this filling station. The investment volume for the plant amounts to approximately three million euros. The daily capacity of the filling station is about 450 kg. Two heavy-duty vehicles and three cars can be refuelled back-to-back.  The cost of one kg of green hydrogen is 12.85€
McPhy 2 兆瓦电解槽平台。2022 年 9 月：开始试运行 2022 年 10 月：正式启用 该设施全天候开放，使运输公司或物流公司等能够在公共加气站为其车辆加气，从而实现无排放的人员和货物运输。该加气站还可以为氢动力汽车加气。该厂的投资额约为 300 万欧元。加氢站的日加氢量约为 450 公斤。可同时为两辆重型汽车和三辆轿车加氢。 每公斤绿色氢气的成本为 12.85 欧元。

StationName 站名:
Maritime station
海事站
Goal 目标:
To refuel cars,ships, trucks and tube trailers
为汽车、轮船、卡车和管式拖车加油
Description 描述:
The features:     1.2MW PEM electrolyser (Cummins/Hydrogenics)     Two stage 950bar hydrogen compressor (Maximator)     1x dispenser for cars (700bar, -40°C) (Maximator) 	 6 -10 back-to-back is possible     1x dispenser for buses and trucks (350bar) (Maximator)  	3 back-to-back is possible     2 docks for tube trailers (unloading and filling up to 500bar)     500bar medium speed buffer hydrogen buffer     Marine bunkering location (200 & 350bar)     Electric fast chargers capable of 350A capacity of 400 kg/day could be doubled without footprint increase The tube trailer station has dual uses: To provide storage for the produced green hydrogen The additional capacity provided by the trailers enables more uptime for the onsite electrolyser, the additional hydrogen produced can either be used to refuel vehicles onsite or taken away to be used as a green alternative for industrial/refuelling activities elsewhere. High pressure boosting for shorter filling times The additional high-pressure storage onsite effectively increases the high-pressure buffer storage capacity. This enables faster refuelling times (the increased pressure/volume in the system increases the 'pushing power' of the fuel, from station to vehicle). The tube trailers can also supply a high-pressure for the onsite compressors, reducing refuelling times, and increasing back-to-back refuelling capability. Ekinetix is the full service system integrator from initial concept, permitting, system integration until turn -key delivery. (EPCM = engineering, procurement and construction management services). 2,5 years from project idea until start of station. The station was built without funding. April 2021 first refuelling May 2021 official opening
 特点     1.2MW PEM 电解槽（Cummins/Hydrogenics） 两级 950bar 氢气压缩机（Maximator） 1x 汽车分配器（700bar，-40°C）（Maximator）
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:

StationName 站名:
H2PORT
H2PORT
Street1 街道1:
Port of Valencia Terminal Europe
巴伦西亚港欧洲码头
Goal 目标:
The Port of València wants to reduce the environmental impact of its terminal machinery which represents almost 25% of the emissions.
瓦伦西亚港希望减少其码头机械对环境的影响，因为这些机械排放的废气几乎占总排放量的 25%。
Description 描述:
As a part of the European project H2PORTS, led by Fundación Valenciaport and in which the Port Authority of Valencia also participates, the Centro Nacional del Hidrógeno (CNH2) is developing a Hydrogen Refuelling Station (HRS) that will guarantee the supply of this fuel, in suitable conditions, during the simultaneous operation of the other two pilots that will be tested throughout the project: a Reach Stacker, at MSC Terminal Valencia, and a terminal tractor 4×4 at Valencia Terminal Europa, part of Grimaldi Group, both powered by fuel cells. Since each of these pilots will take place in different terminals inside the port of Valencia and taking into account that the equipment cannot circulate outside the terminals area, the HRS developed will have fixed part and a flexible and mobile solution. The fixed part will be dedicated to receiving and storing hydrogen from an external supplier and compressing it to delivery pressure. The mobile part will store the compressed hydrogen and include a hydrogen dispenser for refuelling the port machinery The HRS will consist of three main components: a low-pressure hydrogen tank into which the hydrogen supplier will discharge, a two-stage water-cooled piston hydrogen compressor with heat exchangers integrated into the system, and a mobile high-pressure hydrogen storage and supply unit, consisting of two hydrogen storage stages at 300 and 450 bar and a 350 bar dispenser for heavy vehicle with communications. In terms of technical characteristics, the HRS system will include a fixed part, which will be dedicated to receiving and storing hydrogen from an external supplier and compressing it to delivery pressure, and a mobile part, which will store compressed hydrogen and that will include a hydrogen dispenser for the refuelling of port machinery. The HRS will include three main subsystems: a low-pressure hydrogen tank on which the hydrogen supplier will discharge the molecule, a two-stage water-cooled piston hydrogen compressor with heat exchangers integrated into the system, and a mobile high-pressure storage and hydrogen supply unit, that comprises two stages of hydrogen storage at 300 and 450 bar and a heavy vehicle dispenser at 350 bar. The main objective of the project H2PORTS is to test and validate hydrogen technologies on port machinery to provide applicable and real solutions without affecting the performance and safety of port operations and producing zero local emissions. July 2022: construction started The hydrogen supply station (HRS) has been designed and built by the National Hydrogen Centre, and will include a fixed part that will be dedicated to the reception, storage and compression of hydrogen up to delivery pressure (both already installed at the Bracet de la Xità), and a mobile part that will store the compressed hydrogen and will include a hydrogen dispenser for refuelling the port machinery. Sept 2022: stationary part is already installed Jan 2023: mobile part was filled with green H2 Calvera Hydrogen has provided mobile Hydrogen Refuelling Station with dispenser, all assembled on a chassis and can work in any location. This HRS has a capacity to fill several vehicles back to back at 350 bar. 27.4.23 test of hydrogen 4x4 tractor unit started
作为由巴伦西亚港口基金会（Fundación Valenciaport）牵头、巴伦西亚港务局也参与其中的欧洲 H2PORTS 项目的一部分，国家氢能中心（CNH2）正在开发一个氢能加气站（HRS），以确保在整个项目中测试的其他两个试点项目同时运行期间，在适当的条件下供应这种燃料： 在巴伦西亚地中海航运中心码头（MSC Terminal Valencia）的 Reach Stacker 和在巴伦西亚欧罗巴码头（Valencia Terminal Europa）的码头拖拉机 4×4 均由燃料电池驱动。由于每个试点项目都将在巴伦西亚港内的不同码头进行，并考虑到设备不能在码头区域外流通，因此开发的 HRS 将有固定部分和灵活的移动解决方案。固定部分将专门用于接收和储存来自外部供应商的氢气，并将其压缩至输送压力。移动部分将储存压缩后的氢气，并包括一个为港口机械加油的氢气分配器。氢气供应系统将由三个主要部分组成：一个低压氢气罐，氢气供应商将把氢气排入罐中；一个两级水冷活塞式氢气压缩机，热交换器集成在系统中；以及一个移动式高压氢气储存和供应装置，包括两级 300 巴和 450 巴的氢气储存装置，以及一个 350 巴的分配器，供带有通信功能的重型车辆使用。就技术特点而言，HRS 系统将包括一个固定部分和一个移动部分，前者专门用于接收和储存来自外部供应商的氢气，并将其压缩到输送压力；后者将储存压缩后的氢气，并包括一个氢气分配器，用于为港口机械加油。HRS 将包括三个主要子系统：低压氢气罐，氢气供应商将在上面排放氢气分子；两级水冷活塞式氢气压缩机，热交换器集成在系统中；移动式高压储存和氢气供应装置，包括 300 巴和 450 巴的两级氢气储存和 350 巴的重型车辆加注机。H2PORTS 项目的主要目标是对港口机械上的氢技术进行测试和验证，以提供适用的实际解决方案，同时不影响港口作业的性能和安全，并实现本地零排放。2022 年 7 月：开工 氢供应站（HRS）由国家氢能中心设计和建造，将包括一个固定部分，专门用于接收、储存和压缩氢气，使其达到输送压力（这两个部分已在 Bracet de la Xità 安装），以及一个移动部分，用于储存压缩氢气，并包括一个氢气加注机，为港口机械加注氢气。2022 年 9 月：固定部分已安装完毕 2023 年 1 月：移动部分已加注绿色 H2 卡尔维拉氢气公司提供了带加注机的移动式加氢站，所有加氢站都组装在一个底盘上，可在任何地点工作。该加氢站可在 350 巴的压力下为多辆汽车背靠背加氢。27. 4. 23 开始测试氢气 4x4 牵引车装置。

Description 描述:
Use MC filling methode, currently under consideration as the future standard hydrogen fuelling protocol.  Powered entirely by solar photovoltaic panels, the refuelling station will also be the first of its kind to use two different electrolyser types housed in the same production unit. In a real-world environment first, both PEM and AEM electrolysers will be simultaneously tested, analysed, and compared. The station was delivered in Dec 2020. Construction is delayed because of Covid. The station is for research purpose only. Combination with solar energy plant. Pre-cooling to -20° only. Storage of 55 kg in two pressure levels. Jan 2022: construction delayed because of Covid restrictions, to start Mid of 2022 
使用 MC 加注方法，目前正在考虑将其作为未来的标准氢气加注协议。 该加氢站完全由太阳能光伏板供电，也是首个在同一生产单元中使用两种不同类型电解槽的加氢站。在实际环境中，将首次同时对 PEM 和 AEM 电解槽进行测试、分析和比较。电站于 2020 年 12 月交付。由于科维德公司的原因，建设被推迟。该电站仅用于研究目的。与太阳能发电站相结合。预冷温度仅为-20°。两级压力可储存 55 公斤。2022 年 1 月：因 Covid 限制而推迟建造，将于 2022 年年中启动

Description 描述:
Funding of $1 million allocated to ATCO's $2.5 million hydrogen refuelling station in Jandakot. The facility will initially provide Fortescue, ATCO and approved third parties with the opportunity to refuel hydrogen vehicles.  This would include a fleet of Toyota Mirai fuel-cell electric vehicles (FCEV) made available by Toyota Motor Corporation Australia to ATCO and Fortescue. ATCO will use its existing 260kW Proton Exchange Membrane (PEM) electrolyser to produce the hydrogen to supply the refuelling station. ATCO will continue its gas blending test work while supplying the station. The electrolyser has a maximum hydrogen production capacity of 23 tonnes per annum. The existing integrated/combined power system would be sufficient to meet hydrogen production needs. Refueller station operations are anticipated to begin in 2022. Dec 2022: start of operation
为 ATCO 位于 Jandakot 的加氢站拨款 150 万美元。该设施最初将为 Fortescue、ATCO 和经批准的第三方提供为氢能汽车加氢的机会。 这将包括澳大利亚丰田汽车公司向 ATCO 和 Fortescue 提供的丰田 Mirai 燃料电池电动汽车 (FCEV)。ATCO 将利用其现有的 260 千瓦质子交换膜（PEM）电解槽生产氢气，供应加气站。在为加气站供应氢气的同时，ATCO 将继续进行气体混合测试工作。该电解槽的最大氢气生产能力为每年 23 吨。现有的综合/组合电力系统将足以满足加氢站的需求。

Christmas Creek Mine station
圣诞溪矿山站
Street1 街道1:

Description 描述:
AUD$ 32 million renewable hydrogen mobility project The Fortescue Metals Group is to replace its existing fleet of diesel coaches at its Christmas Creek iron ore mine in the Pilbara region of Western Australia with ten full-size hydrogen fuel-cell powered coaches. New York-based Hyzon Motors has been selected as supplier of the custom build hydrogen fuel-cell coaches. The renewable hydrogen supply will be produced onsite through an electrolyser using electricity supplied by the 60 megawatt (MW) Chichester Solar Gas Hybrid project presently under construction by Alinta Energy at Fortescue’s Chichester Hub iron ore operations. A hydrogen refuelling station will be included under the project facilities. In October 2020, it was announced that BOC, a subsidiary of Linde plc, will provide the hydrogen production and refuelling infrastructure for the project:     BOC will supply two 700 kilowatt (kW) ITM electrolysers; the electrolysers will have capacity to produce up to 180 kilograms of hydrogen per day     BOC will also supply a Linde hydrogen refuelling station at the Pilbara site. The facilities are expected to be completed by early 2022. October 2021: the first Hyzon coach (bus) was presented May 2022: The facilities are expected to be completed in 2022. Dec 2022: still under construction March 2023: to be fully operational in 2023, the first 10 Hyzon buses were delivered
耗资 3200 万澳元的可再生氢能交通项目 Fortescue Metals 集团将用 10 辆全尺寸氢燃料电池客车替换其位于西澳大利亚皮尔巴拉地区圣诞溪铁矿的现有柴油客车车队。总部位于纽约的 Hyzon Motors 公司被选为定制氢燃料电池客车的供应商。可再生氢气供应将通过电解槽现场生产，电解槽使用的电力由 Alinta Energy 公司目前正在 Fortescue 公司奇切斯特枢纽铁矿石作业区建设的 60 兆瓦（MW）奇切斯特太阳能天然气混合项目提供。项目设施中还将包括一个加氢站。2020 年 10 月，林德集团的子公司 BOC 宣布将为该项目提供氢气生产和加氢基础设施：     中银集团将提供两台 700 千瓦 ITM 电解槽；电解槽每天最多可生产 180 千克氢气。中银集团还将在皮尔巴拉现场提供一座林德加氢站。这些设施预计将于 2022 年初完工。2021 年 10 月：第一辆 Hyzon 客车（公交车）亮相 2022 年 5 月：预计 2022 年竣工。2022 年 12 月：仍在建设中 2023 年 3 月：将于 2023 年全面投入运营，首批 10 辆 Hyzon 巴士已交付使用

东辉站
Street1 街道1:
location only indicative

Description 描述:
hydrogen refueling station is located at the northwest corner of JLGY-D1-2 plot (about 7700m2) north of Fenghuang 5th Road east of Jiulong Avenue. The scale is positioned as a three-level station and will be constructed in two phases: one will provide 35MPa high pressure hydrogen The intensive hydrogen refueling station for refueling services has a daily hydrogen supply capacity of approximately 500 kg. It mainly includes: 1 hydrogen long tube trailer, 1 set of unloading column, 1 set of hydrogenation complete equipment, 1 set of nitrogen manifold, 1 set of nitrogen tank, 1 chiller and container station. It can meet the hydrogen refueling demand of 30 fuel cell buses or 100 8-ton logistics fuel cell vehicles every day. In the second phase of construction, the daily hydrogen refueling capacity will be increased by 500kg/d, and a hydrogen long tube trailer, a set of unloading columns, a complete set of hydrogenation equipment and a chiller will be installed.
加氢站位于九龙大道以东凤凰五路以北 JLGY-D1-2 地块西北角（约 7700 平方米）。规模定位为三层加氢站，分两期建设：一期提供 35MPa 高压氢气 加氢服务的集约化加氢站，日供氢能力约 500 公斤。它主要包括 氢气长管拖车 1 辆、卸载柱 1 套、加氢成套设备 1 套、氮气歧管 1 套、氮气罐 1 套、制冷机 1 台和容器站。每天可满足 30 辆燃料电池公交车或 100 辆 8 吨级物流燃料电池车的加氢需求。在二期建设中，日加氢能力将增加 500kg/d，并安装一辆氢气长管拖车、一套卸载柱、一套加氢全套设备和一台制冷机。

Description 描述:
Atawey H2Spring-6-350 station produces 2kg of hydrogen per day and can deliver up to 6kg of hydrogen per day at 350 bar. This hydrogen station is made up of: - an electrolyser, which dissociates the hydrogen and oxygen atoms of water by chemical reaction using electricity - a compressor and gas cylinders to be able to store a maximum of hydrogen - a 350 bar supply hose for recharging fuel cell vehicles
Atawey H2Spring-6-350 加氢站每天生产 2 千克氢气，在 350 巴压力下每天最多可输送 6 千克氢气。该氢气站由以下部分组成 - 一个电解槽，利用电力通过化学反应解离水的氢原子和氧原子 - 一个压缩机和气瓶，能够储存最多的氢气 - 一条 350 巴的供气软管，用于为燃料电池汽车充电

科西嘉岛首个氢气站
Street1 街道1:
Route d'Antisanti
安蒂桑蒂之路
Description 描述:
Since the beginning of 2022, 7 forklifts used on the Corstyrène site have been supplied with green hydrogen. The photovoltaic plant placed on the shades of the new employee car park (with a capacity of 100 kWp) supplies 2 electrolysers which generate this hydrogen. A great pride for Corstyrene which is a precursor in Corsica. The company wants to go further, and these hydrogen stations are the first step in a more ambitious project. In addition to manufacturing and supplying green energy for the plant's fleet of forklifts and semi-trailers, Corstyrene plans to supply local authorities, transporters, and why not, once the process is industrialized, supply the sector. maritimelike the ports of Bastia and Ajaccio. Indeed, the Isle of Beauty is a ZNI (Insular Zones Non-Interconnected to the French electricity network). Hydrogen is an ideal solution for the island territory, making it possible to meet the needs for autonomy by using renewable energies. 
 自 2022 年初以来，科斯蒂雷讷生产基地使用的 7 辆叉车均已获得绿色氢气供应。安装在新员工停车场阴影处的光伏发电站（发电量为 100 kWp）为 2 个电解槽提供氢气。作为科西嘉岛的前驱企业，科苯乙烯公司对此深感自豪。公司希望走得更远，而这些氢气站是更宏伟项目的第一步。除了为工厂的叉车和半拖车制造和提供绿色能源外，Corstyrene 公司还计划为地方政府和运输商提供氢气，并在该工艺实现工业化后为海运业提供氢气。事实上，美丽岛是一个 ZNI（未与法国电网联网的海岛）。氢气是岛屿领土的理想解决方案，可通过使用可再生能源满足自治需求。
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site with electricity (100 kW) from renewable energy (solar power on-site), capacity 25 kg/day

VehiclesServed 服务车辆: 7 forklift, utility vehicles, trucks (planned)

StationName 站名:
Herten AGR
赫腾 AGR
Street1 街道1:
Im Emscherbruch
在埃姆舍采石场
Description 描述:
The project includes proton exchange membrane electrolysers (PEM), compressors, storage tanks and a high-performance filling station. The contract also contains provisions for Linde Engineering to provide maintenance and service. The electrolysers will produce around 440,000 kg of hydrogen annually. The electricity will come from the AGR waste power plant, in which municipal and commercial waste with a biogenic share of around 50 percent serves as the main fuel source. The electricity required for the production of green hydrogen is generated from energy efficiency measures implemented by AGR, so that both the existing capacity for delivering environmentally friendly electricity and environmentally friendly heat to the public grid and the electricity for the electrolyser are ensured May 2022: garbage truck starts test operation (refuelling at station Marie-Curie Street)
该项目包括质子交换膜电解槽 (PEM)、压缩机、储罐和高性能加气站。合同还包括林德工程公司提供维护和服务的条款。电解槽每年可生产约 44 万公斤氢气。电力将来自 AGR 垃圾发电厂，该发电厂的主要燃料来源是城市和商业垃圾，其中生物垃圾约占 50%。生产绿色氢气所需的电力来自 AGR 实施的节能措施，因此既能确保向公共电网输送环保电力和环保热能的现有能力，又能确保电解槽的用电 2022 年 5 月：垃圾车开始试运行（在玛丽-居里街站加气）
HydrogenSupply 氢供应:
on-site, electricity from waste power plant
现场，垃圾发电厂发电
VehiclesServed 服务车辆: 15 cars, trucks, garbage truck (for Recklinghausen)

Comments 评论:
The project is funded by the Federal Ministry of Transport and Digital Infrastructure with up to 6.2 million euros as part of the National Innovation Program for Hydrogen and Fuel Cell Technology NIP.
The garbage truck is part of the EU funded project HECTOR.
作为国家氢能和燃料电池技术创新计划（NIP）的一部分，联邦交通和数字基础设施部为该项目提供了高达 620 万欧元的资助。
该垃圾车是欧盟资助的 HECTOR 项目的一部分。

StationName 站名:
MPreis hydrogen refueling station
MPreis 加氢站
Goal 目标:
MPREIS will convert all trucks to hydrogen operation and deliver emissions-free and CO2-neutral 
MPREIS 将把所有卡车改装成氢气卡车，并提供氢气排放解决方案。
Description 描述:
Hydrogen production with elctrolysis, power-to-gas for grid stabilisation part of the EU funded project Demo4Grid: The electrolyser should regulate the electricity network of the regional electricity supplier TIWAG and heat the Therese Mölk Bakery (M Preis) For the technical implementation, ILF from Rum was brought on board and the electrolysis technology (AEL) comes from the Swiss company IHT (now Sunfire) 3,2 MW Tank manufactor for the power-to-gas plant: APL (450 k€). capacity: 50 trucks per day, 12 trucks back-to-back Fuelling of MEGC trailers to deliver H2 to other refuelling stations is prossible. The crocery company MPreis wants to exchange the delivery trucks with FC trucks. MPreis invests 13 Mio €, 9,2 Mio funding June 2021: MPreis ordered the trucks June 2022: inauguration The system developed by Linde Engineering is the first hydrogen filling station in Austria that was designed purely as a truck filling station including a trailer filling station. At the same time, according to the company, this is currently the most powerful hydrogen filling station in Europe. With the usual 350 bar in commercial vehicles, up to 40 kilograms of hydrogen can be refueled in the vehicles in ten minutes. This is a solution developed by Linde especially for Mpreis. Compressors and buffer storage are designed for processes in food logistics, in which many vehicles have to be refueled within a short space of time. The gas station is able to refuel 40 trucks and more within 24 hours with one pump. At peak times, up to 12 hydrogen trucks can be refueled within three hours.  Twin IC 90 / 60-L The hydrogen is generated directly on site: The electrolyser – according to the announcement Europe’s largest single-stack electrolysis system – has been producing green hydrogen since March. March 2023: first Hyzon truck arrived
方面，引进了来自 Rum 的 ILF 公司，电解技术 (AEL) 来自瑞士的 IHT 公司（现为 Sunfire 公司）： 产能：每天 50 辆卡车，12 辆卡车背靠背 MEGC 拖车可向其他加气站输送 H2。食品杂货公司 MPreis 希望用 FC 卡车替换送货卡车。MPreis 投资 1300 万欧元，其中 920 万欧元用于 2021 年 6 月： MPreis 订购卡车 2022 年 6 月：启用 林德工程公司开发的系统是奥地利第一个纯粹作为卡车加氢站设计的加氢站，包括拖车加氢站。同时，据该公司称，这是目前欧洲功率最大的加氢站。在商用车辆常用的 350 巴压力下，十分钟内就能为车辆加注多达 40 公斤的氢气。这是林德专门为 Mpreis 开发的解决方案。压缩机和缓冲储存器是专为食品物流过程设计的，在食品物流过程中，许多车辆必须在短时间内加氢。加油站的一个油泵可以在 24 小时内为 40 辆卡车或更多的卡车加油。在高峰期，最多可在 3 小时内为 12 辆氢气卡车加氢。Twin IC 90 / 60-L 氢气直接在现场产生： 根据公告，欧洲最大的单层电解系统--电解槽自 3 月起开始生产绿色氢气。2023 年 3 月：第一辆 Hyzon 卡车抵达。

Description 描述:
The first of FirstElement Fuel’s “high flow” stations is set to open later this year near the Port of Oakland.  Operated and built by First Element, H2 delivered by Air Liquide The objectives of this project are to advance zero-emission technology by deploying a commercial fleet of thirty (30) fuel cell electric class 8 trucks in northern California; build a hydrogen refueling station capable of providing 700-bar fuel to support the trucks; operate the truck fleet and infrastructure for a total period of 6 years; eliminate 100% of GHG and criteria pollutants associated with vehicle operations; and provide economic and public health benefits to the West Oakland disadvantaged community. The trucks will  initially be fueled with 54% renewable hydrogen with zero CI, but as hydrogen demand increases out of the EBMUD station, biogas will be considered to produce 100% renewable hydrogen onsite. Grant Amount: CARB Contribution	$11,979,914 Matching Funds	$29,203,811 Project Total	$41,183,725 July 2022: Hydrogen fueling station site plan finalized and permitting process initiated
第一元素燃料公司的第一个 "大流量 "加油站将于今年晚些时候在奥克兰港附近开业。 该项目的目标是通过在加利福尼亚州北部部署一支由 30 辆 8 级燃料电池电动卡车组成的商业车队，推动零排放技术的发展；建设一座能够为卡车提供 700 巴燃料的加氢站；运营卡车车队和基础设施共 6 年；消除与车辆运营相关的 100% 温室气体和标准污染物；并为西奥克兰贫困社区带来经济和公共卫生效益。卡车最初将使用 54% 的可再生氢气作为燃料，CI 为零，但随着 EBMUD 站对氢气需求的增加，将考虑使用沼气在现场生产 100% 的可再生氢气。资助金额： CARB 资助

Description 描述:
Two dispenser 30.8.22 Hinet Incheon Airport T2 hydrogen charging station has two chargers installed. One of them was changed to allow self-charging, and a safety device to prevent additional falling and freezing was installed in the device. Full-scale self-hydrogen charging demonstration can now be performed. In addition, separate safety management regulations for self-hydrogen charging have been prepared, and a plan has been prepared to increase driver convenience while putting safety first. For self-hydrogen charging, only drivers who have completed related safety video training at the 'Korea Gas Safety Corporation' cyber training center, an institution in charge of hydrogen safety, can conduct self-hydrogen charging at the site. Drivers who have completed the training can conduct self-charging according to the charging procedure after confirming who has completed the online training at the site, conducting actual charging training with on-site safety managers, and receiving a training certification RF card. Users of self-hydrogen refueling stations can recharge hydrogen at 8,400 won (per kg), about 5% off the average selling price of nearby hydrogen refueling stations. 
两个充电器 30.8.22 Hinet 仁川机场 T2 氢气充电站安装了两个充电器。其中一个已改为可自行充电，并安装了防止额外坠落和冻结的安全装置。现在可以进行全面的氢气自充电演示。此外，还制定了单独的自氢充电安全管理条例，并制定了在安全第一的前提下提高驾驶员便利性的计划。在自行充氢方面，只有在负责氢气安全的机构 "韩国天然气安全公社 "网络培训中心完成相关安全视频培训的驾驶员才能在现场进行自行充氢。完成培训的驾驶员在现场确认完成在线培训的人员，与现场安全管理人员一起进行实际充电培训，并领取培训认证 RF 卡后，即可按照充电程序进行自助充电。自助加氢站的用户可以 8,400 韩元（每公斤）的价格充氢，比附近加氢站的平均售价便宜约 5%。

Description 描述:
Coregas, part of Wesfarmers, is a large Australian-owned gases company and operates a hydrogen production facility embedded with the BlueScope Port Kembla steel works site. In March 2021, the company received an award of funding under Round Four of the Port Kembla Investment Fund to progress its development of a hydrogen refuelling facility adjacent to its existing hydrogen production plant. The refuelling facility will enable the introduction of hydrogen fuel cell trucks to the Illawarra-Shoalhaven region of New South Wales. The project represents a first step in the development of Port Kembla as a hydrogen hub and of a broader hydrogen ‘ecosystem’ for the Illawarra-Shoalhaven regions. The proponent anticipates the refuelling station to be operational in the first half of 2022. In July 2021, it was announced that Coregas had signed a Vehicle Supply Agreement with Hyzon Motors for the supply of two Hymax-450 hydrogen fuel cell-powered prime mover trucks, to be delivered in 2022. Dec 2021:  Haskel Hydrogen Systems Group will provide the hydrogen refuelling system to be used at the Port Kembla facility. The system will take hydrogen from the Coregas plant, compress it to 350 bar, and deliver it to a dispenser at the vehicle fuelling station 50 metres away. Hskel Geno dispenser
Wesfarmers 旗下的 Coregas 公司是澳大利亚一家大型气体公司，在 BlueScope 肯布拉港钢铁厂区内设有氢气生产设施。2021 年 3 月，该公司获得了肯布拉港投资基金（Port Kembla Investment Fund）第四轮的资助，用于在现有制氢厂附近开发加氢设施。加氢设施建成后，新南威尔士州伊拉瓦拉-肖尔黑文地区将能够引进氢燃料电池卡车。该项目标志着肯布拉港向氢气枢纽和伊拉瓦拉-肖尔黑文地区更广泛的氢气 "生态系统 "发展迈出了第一步。倡议者预计加氢站将于 2022 年上半年投入运营。2021 年 7 月，Coregas 宣布与 Hyzon Motors 签订车辆供应协议，供应两辆 Hymax-450 氢燃料电池原动力卡车，将于 2022 年交付。2021 年 12 月：Haskel Hydrogen Systems 集团将提供用于肯布拉港设施的加氢系统。该系统将从 Coregas 工厂获取氢气，将其压缩至 350 巴，并输送至 50 米外车辆加气站的加气机。Hskel Geno 加注机

StationName 站名:
Truganina modular hydrogen station
特鲁加尼纳模块化氢站
Description 描述:
H2FA is launching Australia’s first integrated modular hydrogen fuel generation and refuelling operation at its greenfield facility in Truganina, near Laverton. Founded on environmentally sustainable and low impact concepts, H2FA’s operation uses its own electrolysis assets (in island mode) to convert renewable power into green hydrogen. H2FA’s facilities will not be connected to the energy grid; rather, they will rely on the circular generation of power. H2FA is partnering with some of the world’s leading suppliers of industrial hydrogen equipment through its work with Skai Energies. H2FA will utilise Nilsson Energy (Sweden) RE8760 technology to manage the site micro-grid, allowing all facilities to operate as an island and be completely self-sufficient (fuel cells by Plug Power). Electrolyser (AEL): Green Hydrogen Systems (Denmark) compressor: Idro Meccanica  (Italy) The project includes the following key items of equipment (much of which has been ordered):     Installation of a dedicated solar array (640kW) twin-axis solar array     Alkaline electrolyser (432kW) capable of producing 40-90 kilograms (kg) of hydrogen per day, depending on weather conditions     Hydrogen fuel cell (95kW)     300kW/307kWh battery storage     Hydrogen storage tanks (300 kg capacity onsite, and 900 kg transported in)     Hydrogen compressor matched to electrolyser capacity     100% renewable-powered hydrogen production facility -14 acre site that will be used for multiple offgrid business -permit to serve A- double trucks -initially 60kgs per day but permit gained for below -permit for largest FCEV heavy vehicle HRS int the world, up to 3,000kgs per day - public use -planned for 700bar (2023) , but will be 350bar on launch The project is expected to be operational in Q4 2022. Full Development Approval permits have been granted (with refuelling capacity of up to 6,500 kg per day). Initially, the hydrogen refuelling station would be able to fuel 2-3 vehicles per day. In the longer run, the proponent indicates that the site can be upscaled to supply up to 6,500 kg of hydrogen, with capacity to fuel more than 100 vehicles per day. It is expected that the additional hydrogen supply would be transported into the site from other renewable energy generation sources. Skai Energies is acting as procurement and construction coordinator for the project utilising the Nilsson Energy (Sweden) modular energy control system.
H2FA 正在其位于拉弗顿附近的特鲁加尼纳的新建设施中启动澳大利亚首个综合模块化氢燃料生产和加注业务。H2FA 的运营以环境可持续和低影响概念为基础，利用自身的电解资产（岛屿模式）将可再生能源转化为绿色氢气。H2FA 的设施不会与能源网连接，而是依靠循环发电。通过与 Skai Energies 公司的合作，H2FA 正在与一些世界领先的工业氢气设备供应商合作。H2FA 将利用 Nilsson Energy（瑞典）的 RE8760 技术来管理现场微电网，使所有设施都能作为一个孤岛运行，完全自给自足（燃料电池由 Plug Power 提供）。电解槽 (AEL)： 绿色氢系统（丹麦）压缩机： 压缩机：Idro Meccanica（意大利 该项目包括以下关键设备（其中大部分已订购）：     安装专用太阳能电池阵（640 千瓦） 双轴太阳能电池阵 碱性电解槽（432 千瓦） 根据天气条件，每天可生产 40-90 公斤氢气 氢燃料电池（95 千瓦） 300 千瓦/307 千瓦时电池储氢器 储氢罐（现场容量 300 公斤，运输到现场容量 900 公斤） 氢燃料电池（95 千瓦） 300 千瓦/307 千瓦时电池储氢器 储氢罐（现场容量 300 公斤，运输到现场容量 900 公斤） 氢燃料电池（95 千瓦） 300 千瓦/307 千瓦时电池储氢器 氢气压缩机与电解槽容量相匹配 100% 可再生能源氢气生产设施 -占地 14 英亩，将用于多种离网业务 -获准为 A 级双卡车提供服务 -最初为每天 60 千克，但获得了低于此标准的许可 -获准为世界上最大的 FCEV 重型车辆提供 HRS，每天高达 3,000 千克 -公共用途 -计划为 700bar （2023 年），但启动时将为 350bar 该项目预计将于 2022 年第四季度投入运营。已获得全面开发审批许可（加氢能力达每天 6,500 公斤）。加氢站初期每天可为 2-3 辆汽车加氢。倡议者表示，从长远来看，加氢站的规模可以扩大到每天可为 100 多辆汽车提供燃料，供应高达 6,500 公斤的氢气。预计额外的氢气供应将从其他可再生能源发电来源运入该站点。Skai Energies 公司利用 Nilsson Energy（瑞典）模块化能源控制系统，担任该项目的采购和施工协调人。

StationName 站名:
Strasbourg
斯特拉斯堡
Street1 街道1:

布歇广场路
Description 描述:
R-Hynoca is an innovative project which aims to produce green, carbon-neutral hydrogen from local biomass. The hydrogen production is ensured by the Hynoca® process developed by Haffner Energy. This hydrogen will be recovered as a fuel for low-carbon mobility and as a resource for industry. McPhy, partner of the project for the mobility part, will provide a dual pressure station (350-750 bar) equipped with two terminals to refuel all types of hydrogen mobility:     A “Dual Pressure” station for light vehicles at 700 bar and 350 bar;     A “Hi-Flow” station for buses and trucks. This large capacity station will deliver 700 kg of green hydrogen per day, allowing the daily refuel of the equivalent of a fleet of 30 buses, or 70 light commercial vehicles, or 150 light vehicles. McPhy will also equip the site with a refueling point for pressurized hydrogen cylinders (“tube trailers”) that will be carried to be used in mobility or industrial applications elsewhere than at the point of hydrogen production. The commissioning of the station and the refueling interface is scheduled for the end of 2022. May 2022: Haffner: The initial contract provided for the assembly and installation in 2021 of a pilot module with a production capacity of 11 kg of hydrogen per hour, then those, in 2022, of two additional modules for a total production of 3 modules of 33 kg of hydrogen per hour in mid-2023. The amendment now provides for the supply to R-Hynoca of 2 modules producing a total of 30 kg of hydrogen per hour. These modules will be delivered to the R-GDS site at the end of 2023. April 2023: The Strasbourg public transport operator CTS (Compagnie des Transports Strasbourgeois) has signed a framework agreement with the Portuguese bus manufacturer CaetanoBus for the delivery of up to 60 hydrogen buses over the next five years.
R-Hynoca 是一个创新项目，旨在利用当地生物质生产碳中和的绿色氢气。Haffner Energy 公司开发的 Hynoca® 工艺确保了氢气的生产。这些氢将作为低碳交通的燃料和工业资源进行回收。McPhy 公司是该项目交通部分的合作伙伴，将提供一个双压站（350-750 巴），配备两个终端，为所有类型的氢能汽车加氢：     一个 "双压 "加氢站，为轻型汽车加氢，压力分别为 700 巴和 350 巴；一个 "高流量 "加氢站，为公共汽车和卡车加氢。这个大容量加氢站每天可输送 700 公斤绿色氢气，相当于每天为 30 辆公共汽车、70 辆轻型商用车或 150 辆轻型汽车加氢。麦克菲公司还将为加压氢气瓶（"管式拖车"）配备一个加气点，这些氢气瓶将被运往氢气生产点以外的其他地方，用于移动或工业应用。加氢站和加氢接口计划于 2022 年底投入使用。2022 年 5 月：Haffner： 最初的合同规定在 2021 年组装和安装一个试验模块，每小时可生产 11 千克氢气，然后在 2022 年组装和安装另外两个模块，到 2023 年年中总共生产 3 个模块，每小时可生产 33 千克氢气。修正案现在规定向 R-Hynoca 公司供应 2 个模块，每小时共生产 30 公斤氢气。这些模块将于 2023 年底交付 R-GDS 厂址。2023 年 4 月： 斯特拉斯堡公共交通运营商 CTS（Compagnie des Transports Strasbourgeois）与葡萄牙巴士制造商 CaetanoBus 签订了一份框架协议，将在未来五年内交付多达 60 辆氢能巴士。

Wasserstoffzentrum ENERTRAG
ENERTRAG 氢能中心
Description 描述:
The filling station from the German manufacturer Maximator has two compressor stages that allow commercial vehicles and passenger cars to fill up at 350 and 700 bar. At the beginning, a daily capacity of 750 kg of hydrogen is available, which enables 25 buses or trucks to be refueled. An expansion of the capacities to 1,600 kg per day is possible.  The first customers include the buses of the Uckermärkische Verkehrsgesellschaft, which have been converted to hydrogen drive, and the new Hyundai Xcient Fuel Cell truck, which stopped at a roadshow in Brandenburg. The hydrogen filling station is the first component of the Prenzlau hydrogen center. Plans for the hydrogen center include the installation of up to 13 megawatts of electrolysis capacity, as well as the integration of a quality control laboratory and opportunities to develop new technologies.  The station was inaugurated on December 9th, 2021. For H2 Mobility it is still under commissioning.

Description 描述:
Gathered within SAS Pôle Bourbonnais, a new entity created for the project, the three partners plan to use the Hynoca process developed by Haffner Energy to create a station dedicated to the production of green hydrogen by biomass. Ultimately, it will be able to produce up to 720 kilos of green hydrogen per day, or 250 tons per year. Ets Roussel will be responsible for supplying the installation with local biomass.  On the mobility side, the Thevenin & Ducrot group plans to deploy a distribution station. Operated under the Avia brand,  . It will be accessible to light vehicles as well as heavy vehicles. In addition, the acquisition of 13 heavy vehicles by the various partners will be added.  Excluding the acquisition of vehicles, the project budget is announced at nearly 30 million. Its commissioning is scheduled for mid-2023.  
SAS Pôle Bourbonnais 是一个为该项目而成立的新实体，三个合作伙伴聚集在一起，计划利用 Haffner Energy 公司开发的 Hynoca 工艺，建立一个利用生物质生产绿色氢气的专用站。最终，该站每天可生产 720 公斤绿色氢气，每年可生产 250 吨绿色氢气。Ets Roussel 将负责为该装置提供当地的生物质。 在交通方面，Thevenin & Ducrot 集团计划建立一个配送站。该配送站以阿维亚（Avia）品牌运营。轻型车和重型车均可使用。此外，各合作伙伴还将购置 13 辆重型车辆。 除车辆购置费外，项目预算近 3000 万美元。计划于 2023 年中期投入使用。

Description 描述:
The project includes the development and testing of two 44-tons hydrogen-electric trucks and creating a public hydrogen dispenser at a filling station. The hydrogen offered at this filling station will be exclusively “green”. Both the dispenser and the two trucks are set to be operational mid 2023. Within this project, TotalEnergies Marketing Nederland N.V. is responsible for adding a hydrogen option to the filling station. Zepp.solutions takes on the development of the trucks. Transport companies Vos Transport Group and BCTN Group are each intending to put a hydrogen-electric truck into service in their day-to-day operations. TNO will compare the performance of the trucks to alternatives. With this project, the consortium aims to accelerate  the roll-out of sustainable road transport.
该项目包括开发和测试两辆 44 吨氢电动卡车，并在一个加气站建立一个公共氢分配器。该加氢站提供的氢气将完全是 "绿色 "的。加氢站和两辆卡车将于 2023 年年中投入使用。在该项目中，荷兰道达尔能源营销公司（TotalEnergies Marketing Nederland N.V.）负责在加氢站增加氢气选项。Zepp.solutions 负责卡车的开发。运输公司 Vos Transport Group 和 BCTN Group 都打算在日常运营中使用氢电动卡车。应用科学研究组织将对这些卡车的性能与替代品进行比较。通过该项目，该联盟旨在加快可持续公路运输的推广。

Description 描述:
Two Aragonese companies with long experience in their respective fields of activity such as Arpa Equipos Móviles de Campaña and Grupo Zoilo Ríos are have come together to launch SHiE with a clear purpose, to offer comprehensive solutions for the generation, transport, storage and dispensing of green hydrogen, produced 100% from renewable resources such as photovoltaic solar energy or wind energy. Additional project: A team of researchers from the CSIC develops the first public service hydrogen generator in Spain that will use green hydrogen generated on site with solar energy. The hydrogen will be obtained through electrolyzers powered by a system of solar trackers and photovoltaic panels located at the service station itself. In addition, it will have an intelligent control system that will provide predictions of production and demand. The hydroelectric plant will have a minimum renewable production capacity of 60 kg of hydrogen per day. It will be capable of supplying trucks, buses, passenger cars and warehouses and logistics for transport and is scheduled to come into operation at the end of 2022. The new technology will be tested thanks to an agreement with the service station company Zoilo Ríos . It will be tested at the company's facilities at the El Cisne service station, on the A-2 motorway (Madrid-Barcelona), a few kilometers from Zaragoza.  In 2021: MOU with Fuison Fuel Green to build green H2 production March 2021: MoU with Fusion Fuel Green Plc to develop green hydrogen production plant Oct 2022: still not in operation Dec 2022: mobile station will be fixed there until the new 35/70 dispenser is operational at the beginning of 2023 March 2023: mobile refueller is removed to another place bidding phase has finially enden 
Arpa Equipos Móviles de Campaña 和 Grupo Zoilo Ríos 这两家阿拉贡公司在各自的业务领域拥有丰富的经验，它们联合推出 SHiE 的目的很明确，就是为绿色氢气的生产、运输、储存和分配提供全面的解决方案，这些氢气 100% 由光伏太阳能或风能等可再生资源生产。附加项目： 中船重工集团的一个研究小组开发了西班牙第一台公共服务氢气发生器，该氢气发生器将使用现场利用太阳能产生的绿色氢气。氢气将通过由服务站本身的太阳能跟踪器和光电板系统供电的电解器获得。此外，它还将配备一个智能控制系统，对生产和需求进行预测。水力发电厂的最低可再生生产能力为每天 60 公斤氢气。它将能够为卡车、公共汽车、客车、仓库和物流运输提供氢气，计划于 2022 年底投入使用。根据与服务站公司 Zoilo Ríos 签订的协议，将对新技术进行测试。新技术将在该公司位于 El Cisne 服务站的设施中进行测试，该服务站位于 A-2 高速公路（马德里-巴塞罗那）上，距离萨拉戈萨几公里。2021 年 2021 年 3 月： 与 Fuison Fuel Green 公司签署谅解备忘录，建立绿色氢气生产厂： 2022 年 10 月：仍未投入运营 2022 年 12 月：移动加气站将固定在那里，直到新的 35/70 加气机于 2023 年初投入运营 2023 年 3 月：移动加气机被转移到另一个地方 招标阶段已经结束。

Basque Hydrogen Corridor
巴斯克氢走廊
Description 描述:
The project consists of the transformation of biogas into green hydrogen, with an estimated production of 500 kg/day and that will be used to decarbonize Lurraldebus public transport, since it will be able to feed 5 Lurraldebus buses. In fact, the green H2 production plant and the hydrogen station will be located in the nearby facilities.
该项目包括将沼气转化为绿色氢气，预计日产量为 500 公斤，将用于 Lurraldebus 公共交通的脱碳，因为它可以为 5 辆 Lurraldebus 公共汽车提供燃料。事实上，绿色氢气生产厂和氢气站将设在附近的设施内。

This initiative was created by Petronor and Repsol.
巴斯克氢走廊的设计目标是在巴斯克地区建立一个氢生态系统，从而推动能源、工业、住宅和交通领域的去碳化进程。该倡议由 Petronor 和 Repsol 共同发起。

Goal 目标:
Basque Hydrogen Corridor
巴斯克氢走廊
Description 描述:
The hydrogen project at the Abanto Technology Park  will come into operation at the beginning of 2023 and includes a 2.5 MW electrolyser, a hydro generator, a hydro pipeline and a mobility park. There is a pipeline that connects the electrolyser with the park itself, about 2 kilometers long, and a mobility park will be installed in that park, which will include a hydrogen generator to supply hydrogen to both light and heavy vehicles and a plant logistics to take the hydrogen by truck to other hydrogen plants planned in the future. The planned project in Abanto will involve a total investment of approximately 32 million.
阿班托技术园区的氢气项目将于 2023 年初投入运营，包括一个 2.5 兆瓦的电解槽、一个水力发电机、一条水力管道和一个移动园区。有一条长约 2 公里的管道将电解槽与园区本身连接起来，园区内还将安装一个移动园区，其中包括一个为轻型和重型车辆提供氢气的氢气发生器，以及一个用卡车将氢气运往未来计划中的其他氢气厂的工厂物流。计划在阿班托实施的项目总投资约为 3200 万美元。

StationName 站名:
Basque Y Bilbao
巴斯克 Y 毕尔巴鄂
Street1 街道1:
location only indicative
位置仅供参考
Description 描述:
Iberdrola plans the Basque Y initiative for green hydrogen ; a corridor that includes the construction of three hydrogenerators in the logistics centers of Vitoria / Júndiz, Bilbao and Pasaia with the aim of promoting the decarbonization of heavy land transport, buses and light industrial vehicles, as well as port and airport uses in the region and the chemical industry. The project, for public use, modular and expandable, represents an investment of more than 37 million euros and includes the construction of 10 MW of electrolyzers for a total production of 4,000 kg / day of green hydrogen, as well as on-site photovoltaic plants of self-consumption that, added to the renewable energy supplied by Iberdrola, would allow these facilities to supply 100% renewable and emission-free energy
伊比德罗拉公司（Iberdrola）计划在巴斯克地区发起绿色氢气倡议，该倡议包括在维多利亚/茹恩迪兹、毕尔巴鄂和帕萨亚的物流中心建设三座氢气发电机，目的是促进重型陆路运输、公共汽车和轻型工业车辆以及该地区港口和机场用途和化工行业的脱碳。该项目为公共用途、模块化和可扩展项目，投资超过 3700 万欧元，包括建设 10 兆瓦的电解槽，每天可生产 4000 公斤绿色氢气，以及现场自用光伏电站，加上伊比利亚电力公司提供的可再生能源，这些设施可提供 100% 的可再生无排放能源。

StationName 站名:
HyVus
HyVus
Goal 目标:
power-to-H2 plant with 10 MW and station for bus fleet
10 兆瓦电力变 H2 发电厂和公交车站
Description 描述:
HyVUS project There are possible two projects or one cooperation project: 1. Iberdrola is leading the creation of a green hydrogen corridor in the Valencian Community that includes the construction of two hydroelectric plants in Valencia and Alicante, with an electrolyzer power of 5 megawatts (MW) each.The objective of the project is to generate and supply green hydrogen to fleets of heavy road transport, fleets of intercity buses and light industrial vehicles. At the same time, it could provide services to other sectors in the area that may have a need for hydrogen, such as the railroad or the chemical industry. 2. Project FRV, Vectalia: The project , presented to the Ecological Transition ministries; Industry and Science and Innovation and is positioned as a firm candidate for financing from the Next Generation EU Funds, contemplates the construction of a 10 MW hydrolysis plant powered by a photovoltaic plant and a hydrogeneration that will allow the refueling of about 80 buses , planned in the first phase.
HyVUS 项目 可能有两个项目或一个合作项目： 1. Iberdrola 公司正在牵头在巴伦西亚社区创建一条绿色氢走廊，包括在巴伦西亚和阿利坎特建造两座水电站，每座水电站的电解槽功率为 5 兆瓦 (MW)，该项目的目标是为重型公路运输车队、城际公交车队和轻型工业车辆生产和供应绿色氢气。同时，它还可以为该地区可能需要氢气的其他行业提供服务，如铁路或化工行业。2. Vectalia 的 FRV 项目： 该项目已提交给生态转型部、工业部和科学与创新部，并被定位为下一代欧盟基金资助的可靠候选项目，计划建设一个 10 兆瓦的水解厂，由一个光伏发电厂和一个水力发电厂供电，第一阶段计划为大约 80 辆公共汽车加氢。

StationName 站名:
ICB Bus station
ICB 汽车站
Description 描述:
Everfuel plans, builds and operates the station. Everfuel will also be contracted to supply locally produced hydrogen, which is a by-product of industrial manufacturing processes in the region anyway. The hydrogen that is otherwise not required is additionally offset with CO2 certificates and is therefore a climate-friendly fuel.  The planned hydrogen filling station has a capacity to refuel at least 22 fuel cell buses every day. It is fully redundant and has a modular structure. In this way, the system can easily be expanded to refuel a larger number of hydrogen buses. The entire system is designed in such a way that it can be moved to a new location in a few years.  The Hessian Ministry of Economics, Energy, Transport and Housing has funded the climate-friendly hydrogen technology with funds from the "Procurement of electric buses for local public transport in Hesse" program (HA project number is 1076/21-78). The funding for the 13 buses was 2.4 million euros, the hydrogen filling station is subsidized with up to 1.7 million euros.  11.05.23 further 10 H2 Solaris Urbino were ordered ( invest of 6.5 Mio EUR, 2.88 Mio EUR of funding
Everfuel 公司负责规划、建设和运营氢气站。Everfuel 公司还将承包供应当地生产的氢气，氢气是该地区工业生产过程中产生的副产品。这些氢气是该地区工业生产过程中产生的副产品，因此，这些不需要的氢气可以用二氧化碳证书抵消，是一种气候友好型燃料。 计划中的加氢站每天可为至少 22 辆燃料电池公交车加氢。加氢站具有完全冗余和模块化结构。这样，该系统就可以很容易地扩展，为更多的氢能公交车加氢。整个系统的设计方式使其可以在几年内搬迁到新的地点。 黑森州经济、能源、交通和住房部利用 "黑森州地方公共交通电动公交车采购 "项目（HA 项目编号为 1076/21-78）的资金为这项气候友好型氢技术提供了资助。13 辆公交车的资金为 240 万欧元，加氢站的补贴高达 170 万欧元。 23 年 5 月 11 日，又订购了 10 辆 H2 Solaris Urbino（投资 650 万欧元，资助 288 万欧元）。

Partners in the project: Ballard Power System Canadian Energy Systems Analysis Dana Inc. Emissions Reduction Alberta HTEC Suncor Alberta Motor Transport Association (AMTA) project leader Federal funding for AZETEC was provided through Natural Resources Canada’s Green Infrastructure – Electric Vehicle Infrastructure Demonstration Program, which aims to accelerate the market entry of next-generation clean energy technologies. Emissions Reduction Alberta, Ballard Power Systems and Dana Inc. also invested in the AZETEC project bringing the total funding to $9.2 million.
AZETEC 将验证两辆远程燃料电池电动卡车和配套氢燃料基础设施的设计、制造和运行，这两辆卡车将在阿尔伯塔省卡尔加里和埃德蒙顿之间运行。项目合作伙伴 Ballard Power System 加拿大能源系统分析公司 Dana Inc. 阿尔伯塔省减少排放协会 HTEC Suncor 阿尔伯塔省汽车运输协会 (AMTA) 项目负责人 AZETEC 项目的联邦资金由加拿大自然资源部的绿色基础设施--电动汽车基础设施示范项目提供，该项目旨在加速新一代清洁能源技术进入市场。艾伯塔省减排协会、巴拉德动力系统公司和德纳公司也对 AZETEC 项目进行了投资，使资金总额达到 920 万美元。

Description 描述:
The BCH2 Ports Project will feature HTEC’s higher-capacity fuelling station, initially serving heavy-duty hydrogen electric vehicles. The hydrogen-fuelling station will be located at a Parkland Corporation cardlock site located on Tsawwassen First Nation land. HTEC will also be responsible for the clean hydrogen supply for the project. In addition, the project will demonstrate four fuel-cell electric yard trucks, and two Class 8 drayage trucks that HTEC will lease to fleet operators. The fuel-cell electric trucks are being developed by Hexagon using its Type IV hydrogen-storage system and high-energy density Liion battery packs, and powered by Ballard’s innovative FCmove HD+ fuel-cell engine, designed specifically for heavy-duty mobility applications. For the duration of the pilot project, expected to begin in early 2024, these HTEC vehicles will be operated by Harbour Link Container Services, Tidewater Container Services and BC Ferries Commercial Services, which then will operate throughout the Port of Vancouver.
BCH2 港口项目将采用 HTEC 容量更大的加气站，最初将为重型氢电动汽车提供服务。加氢站将设在位于 Tsawwassen 原住民土地上的 Parkland Corporation 卡锁场地。HTEC 还将负责该项目的清洁氢供应。此外，该项目还将展示四辆燃料电池电动堆场卡车和两辆 8 级拖运卡车，HTEC 将把这些卡车租赁给车队运营商。燃料电池电动卡车由海克斯康公司利用其 IV 型储氢系统和高能量密度锂离子电池组开发，并由巴拉德公司专为重型移动应用设计的创新 FCmove HD+ 燃料电池发动机提供动力。在预计于 2024 年初开始的试点项目期间，这些 HTEC 车辆将由 Harbour Link Container Services、Tidewater Container Services 和 BC Ferries Commercial Services 运营，然后在整个温哥华港运营。

StationName 站名:
Geelong Viva Energy
吉朗万岁能源公司
Street2 街道 2:
corner Princess Hwy - Station St
转角 Princess Hwy - Station St
Description 描述:
The system MC500 PEM EL delivered by Nel is a containerized solution with a production capacity up to 1,063kg/day, and will supply fuel cell grade hydrogen directly on site. The contract has an approximate value of about EUR 4m, and the system is expected to be delivered in Q3 2023. With a capacity of delivering more than one tonne of hydrogen per day, the station (built by Air Liquide) will be able to serve 5 heavy duty vehicles per hour. It will allow two heavy duty vehicles to fill simultaneously as well as passenger cars consecutively with limited waiting time for efficient peak time management. Hydrogen can be supplied to the hydrogen refueling station either from an electrolyzer installed upstream  (2,5MW NEL)) or from the tube trailer connected to the station. The station is planned to be delivered and put in operation in 2023. The project includes a diverse group of industry partners: Toll Group, ComfortDelGro Corporation Australia (CDC), Cleanaway and Barwon Water, who have committed to seven of an initial fleet of 15 hydrogen-powered heavy vehicles that will be refuelled at the service station within the first two years. These FCEVs include road freight, public transport, municipal waste management, water treatment and general fleet.
Nel 交付的 MC500 PEM EL 系统是一个集装箱式解决方案，生产能力高达 1,063 公斤/天，可在现场直接供应燃料电池级氢气。合同价值约为 400 万欧元，系统预计将于 2023 年第三季度交付。该氢气站（由液化空气公司建造）每天可提供超过一吨的氢气，每小时可为 5 辆重型车辆提供服务。它将允许两辆重型车辆同时加氢，并允许乘用车在有限的等待时间内连续加氢，从而实现有效的高峰时间管理。加氢站可从上游安装的电解槽（2.5 兆瓦 NEL）或从与加氢站相连的管式拖车中获得氢气。加氢站计划于 2023 年交付使用。该项目包括多个行业合作伙伴： Toll Group、ComfortDelGro Corporation Australia (CDC)、Cleanaway 和 Barwon Water 承诺在最初两年内为服务站加氢的 15 辆氢动力重型车辆中的 7 辆加氢。这些 FCEV 包括公路货运、公共交通、城市废物管理、水处理和普通车队。

The station will be a part of Everfuel’s hydrogen station roll-out plan. Public funding programmes and customer commitments are key elements for realising the plan which is part of Everfuel’s Scandinavian green hydrogen fuelling strategy for trucks, buses and cars connecting the main traffic corridors in Sweden, Norway and Denmark.  The station supported by Energimyndigheten must be commissioned in 2023.

Description 描述:
The new station and hydrogen production will be located on five acres, will produce 3,250 kilograms of hydrogen a day, and can refuel as quickly as diesel and up to 24 Hydra-converted trucks each hour across four bays. The station’s low-carbon hydrogen is being produced from two on-site, 5-megawatt electrolysers with electricity coming from BC Hydro, B.C.’s main electricity utility with 31 hydroelectric facilities throughout the province. Additional critical partners include energy project delivery expert, Solaris, and industrial construction specialist, PCL Construction, with project financing support coming from Hydra’s seed funders and non-dilutive government funding including the BC Ministry of Energy, Mines and Low Carbon Innovation - Part 3 Agreement. 
新的加氢站和氢气生产占地五英亩，每天可生产 3250 公斤氢气，加氢速度可与柴油加氢速度相媲美，每小时最多可为 24 辆经过 Hydra 改装的卡车加氢，共有四个加氢间。加氢站的低碳氢气由两个 5 兆瓦的现场电解槽生产，电力来自不列颠哥伦比亚省水电公司（BC Hydro），该公司是不列颠哥伦比亚省的主要电力公司，在全省拥有 31 个水电设施。其他重要合作伙伴包括能源项目交付专家 Solaris 和工业建筑专家 PCL Construction，项目融资支持来自 Hydra 的种子基金和非摊薄型政府资金，包括不列颠哥伦比亚省能源、矿业和低碳创新部 - 第三部分协议。

Bouzas Jules Verne project
布扎斯-儒勒-凡尔纳项目
Street1 街道1:

布萨斯海港大道（Travesia de Bouzas Portuario
Street2 街道 2:
Port of Vigo
维哥港
Description 描述:
Hydrogen generation will be obtained from an electrolyser connected to the electricity grid, fed locally as far as possible by associated renewable facilities and completed by PPAs of 100% Renewable origin. The hydrogen generated will be used to fuel pilot/demonstration projects in mobility (port, fishing, automotive and naval logistics). The project will be developed in two phases to adapt it to demand, with an initial estimate of about 129 kg/day (nominal) and ending at approximately 516 kg/day (nominal). And the installation will consist of the following:     Renewable energy generation systems in self-consumption mode associated with the electrolyser (power to be determined based on the space available in the port area).     Electrolyzer (PEM or Alkaline), initially it is proposed to install a 300 Kw electrolyser with the possibility of being able to easily increase the size of the plant to approximately 1.2 Mw.     The supply of the Electrolyser includes the electrical transformer, the purified water generation unit (<1 μs) and the Hydrogen separating, drying and purifying unit.     Lung at 30 bar     Dual dispensing system for different vehicles. For heavy transport (trucks, buses or boats) the dispensing will be done at 350 bar, and for light vehicles (utility cars) there will be a 700 bar dispenser.  Main data: - Location: Port Area from Vigo (Bouzas). -Electrolyser: Alkaline 1.4 Mw. -H2 capacity (350 bar): 570 kg/day. 213 mt/year. -Refueling Capacity: > 40 refueling/day (Heavy T.). -Avoided emissions: 2,872 TmCO2/year -CAPEX: €6 million. -Employment: 4 direct permanent; 20 temporary direct; 7 indirect permanent and 35 temporary indirect. -Scheduled Commissioning: January 2024. ·         Project Singularities: -Dispensing point public. - Orientation to land and sea transport. - Industrial consumption (gray hydrogen substitution). -Cold ironing “zero emissions” The estimated budget for the first phase is €2,309,165 while the projection of the expansion of the project to reach its maximum capacity is of other €2,158,800.  September 2022: Currently, the project, which would involve an initial investment of €6M, has been presented to the “Mechanism for Recovery and Resilience” funds. The company Julio Verne Hidrógeno Puerto de Vigo, SL, has already applied for the concession and the project is in the public exhibition phase. Also, 80% of hydrogen consumption is already closed for industrial use. The plant will be operational in January 2024.
氢气将通过与电网连接的电解槽产生，尽可能由相关的可再生设施就地供给，并通过 100% 可再生能源的 PPA 完成。产生的氢气将用于流动性试点/示范项目（港口、渔业、汽车和海军物流）。该项目将分两个阶段开发，以适应需求，初步估计约为 129 公斤/天（标称），最终约为 516 公斤/天（标称）。安装的设备包括     与电解槽相关联的自耗模式可再生能源发电系统（功率将根据港区可用空间确定）。电解槽（PEM 或碱性），最初建议安装一个 300 千瓦的电解槽，并有可能将电解槽的功率轻松增至约 1.2 兆瓦。电解槽的供应包括变压器、纯水生成装置（<1 μs）和氢气分离、干燥和净化装置。肺活量 30 巴 双分配系统适用于不同车辆。对于重型运输工具（卡车、公共汽车或船只），分配器的压力为 350 巴；对于轻型运输工具（多用途汽车），分配器的压力为 700 巴。主要数据： - 位置： 从维戈（布萨斯）出发的港口区。-电解槽： 碱性 1. 4 Mw。-H2 容量（350 巴）： 570 公斤/天。213 公吨/年。-燃料容量 > 40 次/天（重型）。-避免排放 2,872吨二氧化碳/年 -CAPEX：600万欧元。-就业： 直接长期就业 4 人；直接临时就业 20 人；间接长期就业 7 人，间接临时就业 35 人。-计划投产： 2024 年 1 月。- 项目的特殊性： -公共分配点。- 面向陆运和海运。- 工业消费（灰色氢替代）。-冷烫 "零排放" 第一阶段的预计预算为 2,309,165 欧元，而项目扩建以达到最大产能的预计预算为 2,158,800 欧元。2022 年 9 月：目前，该项目已提交给 "恢复和复原机制 "基金，初期投资为 600 万欧元。Julio Verne Hidrógeno Puerto de Vigo, SL 公司已经申请了特许经营权，项目正处于公开展示阶段。此外，80% 的氢气消耗已经用于工业用途。该工厂将于 2024 年 1 月投入运营。

Description 描述:
External - public (slow fill) On Thursday, April 7, 2022, Vissers Energy Group officially opened the very first hydrogen filling station in Limburg. The new hydrogen filling point is located at Stationsstraat 90 in Horst and is suitable for refueling both passenger cars and trucks. Vissers Energy Group sees it as its task to make green hydrogen available to end users. The aim of the first hydrogen filling station is therefore to test all kinds of applications in practice together with these end users. The hydrogen station in Horst is an important first step in the further roll-out of hydrogen at the Vissers filling station network in the South of the Netherlands.

Goal 目标:
Project 117 will equip Route 117 corridor with two green hydrogen refuelling stations allowing heavy-duty trucks to connect the greater Montreal area and Abitibi-Témiscamingue
117 号项目将为 117 号公路走廊配备两个绿色加氢站，使重型卡车能够连接大蒙特利尔地区和阿比提比-泰米斯卡明盖地区
Description 描述:
Project 117 will equip Route 117 corridor with two green hydrogen refuelling stations allowing heavy-duty trucks to connect the greater Montreal area and Abitibi-Témiscamingue. These green hydrogen refuelling stations will be located in the surroundings of Val-d’Or and Saint-Jérôme and will have the capacity to refuel heavy-duty trucks with pressures of 350 bar or 700 bar. Although Project 117 is designed primarily for heavy-duty trucking, motorists who have purchased hydrogen-powered cars will also be able to refuel at these stations. The two green hydrogen refuelling stations will each have a 5 MW PEM (Proton Exchange Membrane) electrolyzer and their respective capacity can be increased according to demand growth
117 号项目将为 117 号公路走廊配备两个绿色加氢站，使重型卡车能够连接大蒙特利尔地区和阿比提比-泰米斯卡明纽省。这些绿色加氢站将位于 Val-d'Or 和 Saint-Jérôme 附近，可为压力为 350 巴或 700 巴的重型卡车加氢。虽然 117 号项目主要是为重型卡车设计的，但购买氢动力汽车的驾驶者也可以在这些加氢站加氢。这两个绿色加氢站将各配备一个 5 兆瓦 PEM（质子交换膜）电解槽，其容量可根据需求的增长而增加。

StationName 站名:
Townsville SunHQ Hydrogen Hub
汤斯维尔 SunHQ 氢气中心
Description 描述:
The initial phase (Phase 1) of the SunHQ Hydrogen Hub project involves the installation of a 1 megawatt (MW) PEM electrolyser (ordered from Plug Power)  co-located at the Townsville refinery.  The electrolyser would be powered through a behind the meter connection to the existing 121 MW solar farm.  The electrolyser would have the capacity to produce approximately 140 tonnes of hydrogen per annum (though the hydrogen demand of the five procured Hyzon trucks is approximately 91 tonnes per annum, allowing scale-up to meet third-party demand).  Ark Energy would procure five new hydrogen fuel cell heavy haulage trucks (each 140 tonnes capacity) and lease them to its sister company, Townsville Logistics Pty Ltd, for its short haul fleet operating between the Port of Townsville and the Sun Metals refinery, a 25 kilometre round-trip. There is also potential for renewable-based hydrogen use in powering up to 15 forklifts (in the 3-5 tonne range) at the Sun Metals refinery. July / Sept 2021: 5 Hyzon trucks were ordered
SunHQ Hydrogen Hub 项目的初始阶段（第一阶段）包括在汤斯维尔炼油厂安装一个 1 兆瓦 (MW) 的 PEM 电解槽（向 Plug Power 公司订购）。 该电解槽将通过与现有 121 兆瓦太阳能发电场的表后连接供电。 该电解槽每年可生产约 140 吨氢气（但采购的 5 辆 Hyzon 卡车每年的氢气需求量约为 91 吨，因此可扩大规模以满足第三方需求）。 方舟能源公司将采购 5 辆新的氢燃料电池重型运输卡车（每辆载重 140 吨），并将其租赁给其姊妹公司汤斯维尔物流私人有限公司（Townsville Logistics Pty Ltd），用于汤斯维尔港和太阳金属炼油厂之间往返 25 公里的短途运输。此外，太阳金属炼油厂还有可能使用可再生氢气为多达 15 辆叉车（3-5 吨）提供动力。2021 年 7 月/9 月：订购 5 辆 Hyzon 卡车

Description 描述:
Hydrogen is proposed to be produced using a 2-megawatt electrolyser, powered by renewable energy sourced from the South West Interconnected System. Production will be timed to occur during periods of excess solar in the grid and stored on-site. Where needed, Woodside will also use Renewable Energy Certificates. Initially, Woodside is targeting production of 235 kilograms per day of hydrogen at the Hydrogen Refueller @H2Perth, with the potential to scale up to a targeted 800 kilograms per day. Hydrogen Refueller @H2Perth will be available to industrial customers, as well as the public. Through the Program, hydrogen is targeted to be made available at a globally competitive price of A$11 per kilogram for a 10-year period.
氢气拟使用一个 2 兆瓦的电解槽生产，由西南互联系统提供的可再生能源供电。生产时间将安排在电网太阳能过剩期间，并在现场储存。必要时，伍德赛德还将使用可再生能源证书。伍德赛德最初的目标是在 Hydrogen Refueller @H2Perth 每天生产 235 公斤氢气，并有可能扩大到每天生产 800 公斤氢气。Hydrogen Refueller @H2Perth 将向工业客户提供氢气，同时也向公共事业客户提供氢气。

StationName 站名:
Brühl
布吕尔
Description 描述:
Mobile refuelling station The filling station was developed in cooperation between Westfalen Group and the Lancaster-based company NanoSUN. It is a container-based fast-fill solution for refuelling at 350 bar. Filling a fuel cell bus with the mobile hydrogen filling station takes less than 20 minutes. Pioneer Hydrogen Refuelling Station Since the filling station container can deliver up to 230 kg of hydrogen from several cylinders, 10 fuel cell buses in Turnus can be fully refuelled. The system is particularly robust because there are no components that are prone to failure. If a container is empty, it is refilled or replaced with a full container.
移动加气站 该加气站由威斯特法伦集团和位于兰开斯特的 NanoSUN 公司合作开发。它是一种基于容器的快速加氢解决方案，可在 350 巴的压力下进行加氢。使用移动式加氢站为燃料电池客车加氢不超过 20 分钟。先锋加氢站 由于加氢站的容器可以从多个气瓶中输送多达 230 千克的氢气，因此可以为特努斯的 10 辆燃料电池公交车加满氢气。该系统特别坚固耐用，因为没有容易发生故障的部件。如果一个容器空了，就会重新加满或换上一个满的容器。

StationName 站名:
Haren H2Agrar Grüne Tankstellenpark Emsland
Haren H2Agrar Grüne Tankstellenpark Emsland
Street1 街道1:
An der Autobahn
高速公路上
Description 描述:
The H2 filling station offers two pressure levels of 350 and 700 bar, so cars, buses, trucks and above all the prototypes of the H2 tractors from Fendt - as part of the H2Agrar model project - can be refueled. It is possible to refuel at 350 and 700 bar at the same time. This is made possible by a new development of a combined Schwelm H2 high-performance fuel pump. A three-stage system of hydraulic compressors is used in Haren, which generates a pressure of up to 950 bar at its peak. A storage bank system with low, medium and high pressure banks results in a storage volume of 8,970 l for approx. 275 kg of hydrogen with a total tank capacity of up to 480 kg of hydrogen per day.  Schwelm Anlagen Technik delivers the complete system from a single source: planning, compressor unit, storage, electrical engineering, control and, of course, the pump. The green hydrogen is generated in the CEC Haren by two 1 MW electrolysers from H-TEC SYSTEMS, the electricity is supplied by the Fehndorf - Lindloh wind farm with 16 ENERCON turbines in the immediate vicinity. 
H2 加气站提供 350 巴和 700 巴两种压力，因此轿车、公共汽车、卡车，尤其是作为 H2Agrar 模型项目一部分的 Fendt H2 拖拉机原型都可以在此加气。可以同时以 350 和 700 巴的压力加油。这得益于新开发的组合式 Schwelm H2 高性能燃油泵。哈伦采用了三级液压压缩机系统，其峰值压力可达 950 巴。由低压、中压和高压组成的储氢罐系统可储存 8,970 升约 275 千克的氢气，每天的储氢罐总容量可达 480 千克氢气。 施维姆设备制造技术公司（Schwelm Anlagen Technik）从单一来源提供全套系统：规划、压缩机组、存储、电气工程、控制，当然还有泵。绿色氢气由 H-TEC SYSTEMS 公司的两台 1 兆瓦电解槽在 CEC Haren 生产，电力由附近的 Fehndorf - Lindloh 风电场提供，该风电场有 16 台 ENERCON 涡轮机。

StationName 站名:
Lingen
林根
Street1 街道1:
Am Hilgenberg
在希尔根贝格
Goal 目标:
RWE and Westfalen aim to develop a hydrogen fuel station infrastructure in Germany for heavy commercial vehicles in particular. 
RWE 和 Westfalen 的目标是在德国开发氢燃料站基础设施，特别是用于重型商用车辆。
Description 描述:
RWE will supply the green hydrogen from its electrolyser infrastructure in Lingen, and the Westfalen Group will take care of setting up and operating the fuel station infrastructure. Starting in 2024, goods vehicles, buses, refuse vehicles, small trucks and passenger vehicles will be able to refuel with green hydrogen there. The facility, run by Westfalen, will also include a trailer filling station to enable tankers to deliver green hydrogen to other customers in the region. The green hydrogen for the fuel station and filling station will initially be generated in a 14-megawatt pilot electrolyser which RWE is currently constructing on the site of the Emsland gas-fired power station.
RWE 将从其位于林根的电解槽基础设施中提供绿色氢气，Westfalen 集团将负责加油站基础设施的建设和运营。从 2024 年开始，货车、公交车、垃圾车、小型卡车和客运车辆都可以在这里加注绿色氢气。该设施由 Westfalen 公司运营，还将包括一个拖车加气站，以便油罐车将绿色氢气运送给该地区的其他客户。燃料站和加气站所需的绿色氢气最初将由 RWE 目前正在 Emsland 燃气发电站所在地建造的 14 兆瓦试验电解槽生成。

Goal 目标:
To refuel the hydrogen bus fleet of 52 buses for Rostocker transport company rebus
为罗斯托克运输公司 rebus 的 52 辆氢气巴士加注燃料
Description 描述:
The project comprises the planning, construction, operation and maintenance of two hydrogen filling stations at the rebus bus depots in Güstrow and Bad Doberan. In addition, APEX will be given a mandate to provide the two filling stations with green hydrogen. rebus is a bus company based in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany. The filling stations are expected to be operational by the beginning of 2024 and will become the property of rebus upon completion. rebus plans to procure and operate 47 fuel cell low-floor solo buses in the 12-meter variant and five additional fuel cell articulated buses in the 18-meter variant. Delivery of the first hydrogen bus is expected in early 2024. Subsequently, further buses will be delivered monthly, so that the hydrogen-powered bus fleet is scheduled to be complete with 52 vehicles at the beginning of 2025.
该项目包括在 Güstrow 和 Bad Doberan 的公交车站规划、建设、运营和维护两个加氢站。此外，APEX 还将负责向这两个加氢站提供绿色氢气。Rebus 是一家位于德国梅克伦堡-前波莫瑞州的公交公司。rebus 计划采购并运营 47 辆 12 米长的燃料电池低地板单人客车和另外 5 辆 18 米长的燃料电池铰接客车。首辆氢能巴士预计将于 2024 年初交付。随后，每月将交付更多的巴士，因此氢动力巴士车队计划在 2025 年初完成 52 辆车的交付。

Description 描述:
The new station will include two hydrogen refueling lanes with dispensers for heavy-duty vehicles such as commercial and municipal trucks, and Air Products’ own truck fleet, with a filling time on par with conventionally fueled heavy-duty trucks. In addition, the station also will have two fueling positions for light-duty hydrogen fuel cell cars. The state-of-the-art, high-capacity, high-efficiency station is scheduled to open in early 2025 and will be available to retail customers. Using proprietary compression technology, the station will have a capacity of up to six tonnes of hydrogen per day. It will be located in Northeast Edmonton near Air Products’ transformative new $1.6 billion (CAD) net-zero hydrogen energy complex.
新加氢站将包括两条加氢通道，加氢机可供重型车辆（如商业和市政卡车）以及空气产品公司自己的卡车车队使用，加氢时间与传统燃料重型卡车相同。此外，加气站还将为轻型氢燃料电池汽车设置两个加气位。这座先进的高容量、高效率加氢站计划于 2025 年初投入使用，并向零售客户开放。该加氢站采用专有压缩技术，每天可加氢六吨。该站将位于埃德蒙顿东北部，靠近空气产品公司耗资 16 亿美元（加元）新建的净零氢气能源综合设施。

StationName 站名:
Lorient
洛里昂
Street1 街道1:
Bd Yves Demaine
Bd Yves Demaine
Description 描述:
Station was ordered in December 2022 Groundbreaking on May 9, 2023 This station will supply vehicles in fast charge and the 19 hydrogen buses, soon to be deployed by Lorient Agglomération, simultaneously in slow charge, a first for a large capacity station in France. Unclear 19 or 5 H2 buses. The hydrogen for the Lorient depot will be sourced from Buléon, where Lhyfe, a leading company in green hydrogen production, is constructing its second production site. The hydrogen production will utilize electricity from six nearby wind turbines. By 2030, its entire fleet of buses and waterbuses will transition from all-diesel to bio-NGV (80% of the fleet) or renewable hydrogen (20% of the fleet, including a passenger ship).
2022 年 12 月订购，2023 年 5 月 9 日破土动工 该加氢站将为车辆提供快速充电服务，并同时为 19 辆氢能公交车提供慢速充电服务，这在法国的大容量加氢站中尚属首次。不清楚是 19 辆还是 5 辆氢公交车。洛里昂车库的氢气将从布勒翁（Buléon）供应，绿色氢气生产领域的领先企业 Lhyfe 正在该地建设第二个生产基地。氢气生产将利用附近六台风力涡轮机的电力。到 2030 年，整个巴士和水上巴士车队将从全柴油过渡到生物 NGV（占车队的 80%）或可再生氢（占车队的 20%，包括一艘客轮）。
